243 
244 void Spell::EffectInstaKill(SpellEffectIndex /*eff_idx*/)
245 {
246  if (!unitTarget || !unitTarget->IsAlive())
247  return;
248 
249  if (m_caster == unitTarget) // prevent interrupt message
250  finish();
251 
252  WorldObject* caster = GetCastingObject(); // we need the original casting object
253 
254  WorldPacket data(SMSG_SPELLINSTAKILLLOG, (8 + 8 + 4));
255  data << (caster && caster->GetTypeId() != TYPEID_GAMEOBJECT ? m_caster->GetObjectGuid() : ObjectGuid()); // Caster GUID
256  data << unitTarget->GetObjectGuid(); // Victim GUID
257  data << uint32(m_spellInfo->Id);
258  m_caster->SendMessageToSet(data, true);
259 
260  Unit::DealDamage(m_caster, unitTarget, unitTarget->GetHealth(), nullptr, INSTAKILL, SPELL_SCHOOL_MASK_NORMAL, m_spellInfo, false);
261 }
262 
263 void Spell::EffectEnvironmentalDMG(SpellEffectIndex eff_idx)
264 {
265  uint32 absorb = 0;
266  int32 resist = 0;
267 
268  // Note: this hack with damage replace required until GO casting not implemented
269  // environment damage spells already have around enemies targeting but this not help in case nonexistent GO casting support
270  // currently each enemy selected explicitly and self cast damage, we prevent apply self casted spell bonuses/etc
271  damage = m_spellInfo->CalculateSimpleValue(eff_idx);
272 
273  m_caster->CalculateDamageAbsorbAndResist(m_caster, GetSpellSchoolMask(m_spellInfo), SPELL_DIRECT_DAMAGE, damage, &absorb, &resist, false, !m_spellInfo->HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR_EX5_NO_PARTIAL_RESISTS));
274 
275  Unit::SendSpellNonMeleeDamageLog(m_trueCaster, m_caster, m_spellInfo->Id, damage, GetSpellSchoolMask(m_spellInfo), absorb, resist, false, 0, false);
276  if (m_caster->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_PLAYER)
277  ((Player*)m_caster)->EnvironmentalDamage(DAMAGE_FIRE, damage);
278 }
279 
280 void Spell::EffectSchoolDMG(SpellEffectIndex eff_idx)
281 {
282  if (unitTarget && unitTarget->IsAlive())
283  {
284  switch (m_spellInfo->SpellFamilyName)
285  {
286  case SPELLFAMILY_GENERIC:
287  {
288  switch (m_spellInfo->Id) // better way to check unknown
289  {
290  case 35181: // Al'ar - Dive Bomb
291  if (unitTarget->GetObjectGuid() == m_targets.getUnitTargetGuid()) // summons two adds
292  unitTarget->CastSpell(nullptr, 39110, TRIGGERED_OLD_TRIGGERED);
293  // [[fallthrough]]
294  // Meteor like spells (divided damage to targets)
295  case 24340: case 26558: case 28884: // Meteor
296  case 36837: case 38903: case 41276: // Meteor
297  case 57467: // Meteor
298  case 26789: // Shard of the Fallen Star
299  case 40810: case 43267: case 43268: // Saber Lash
300  case 42384: // Brutal Swipe
301  case 64422: case 64688: // Sonic Screech
302  case 70492: case 72505: // Ooze Eruption
303  case 71904: // Chaos Bane
304  case 72624: case 72625: // Ooze Eruption
305  {
306  uint32 count = 0;
307  for (TargetList::const_iterator ihit = m_UniqueTargetInfo.begin(); ihit != m_UniqueTargetInfo.end(); ++ihit)
308  if (ihit->effectHitMask & (1 << eff_idx))
309  ++count;
310 
311  damage /= count; // divide to all targets
312  break;
313  }
314  // percent from health with min
315  case 25599: // Thundercrash
316  {
317  damage = unitTarget->GetHealth() / 2;
318  if (damage < 200)
319  damage = 200;
320  break;
321  }
322  case 33666: // Sonic Boom - Normal
323  case 38795: // Sonic Boom - Heroic
324  {
325  damage = (unitTarget->GetMaxHealth() * (m_spellInfo->Id == 33666 ? 90 : 95)) / 100;
326  break;
327  }
328  case 33671: // Shatter - Gruul
329  {
330  float x, y, z;
331  unitTarget->GetPosition(x, y, z);
332  damage = (20 - m_caster->GetDistance(x, y, z, DIST_CALC_COMBAT_REACH))*(damage / 20);
333  break;
334  }
335  // Intercept (warrior spell trigger)
336  case 20253:
337  case 61491:
338  {
339  damage += uint32(m_caster->GetTotalAttackPowerValue(BASE_ATTACK) * 0.12f);
340  break;
341  }
342  // percent max target health
343  case 29142: // Eyesore Blaster
344  case 35139: // Throw Boom's Doom
345  case 49882: // Leviroth Self-Impale
346  case 55269: // Deathly Stare
347  {
348  damage = damage * unitTarget->GetMaxHealth() / 100;
349  break;
350  }
351  // Lightning Strike
352  case 37841:
353  if (unitTarget->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_PLAYER && unitTarget->HasAura(37830)) // Repolarized Magneto Sphere
354  ((Player*)unitTarget)->KilledMonsterCredit(21910);
355  break;
356  // Cataclysmic Bolt
357  case 38441:
358  {
359  damage = unitTarget->GetMaxHealth() / 2;
360  break;
361  }
362  case 38977: // Spore Quake Effect
363  if (roll_chance_i(33))
364  m_caster->CastSpell(unitTarget, 39002, TRIGGERED_OLD_TRIGGERED); // Spore Quake Knockdown
365  break;
366  case 39384:
367  {
368  if (eff_idx == 0)
369  {
370  if (unitTarget->GetFaction() == 1690)
371  damage = 10000;
372  else
373  damage = 0;
374  }
375  else
376  {
377  if (unitTarget->GetFaction() == 1689)
378  damage = 10000;
379  else
380  damage = 0;
381  }
382  break;
383  }
384  case 40065: // Apexis Reprisal
385  {
386  damage = unitTarget->GetMaxHealth() / 3;
387  break;
388  }
389  case 43657: // Electrical Storm - Akil'zon
390  {
391  if (Aura* aura = m_caster->GetAura(43648, EFFECT_INDEX_1))
392  damage *= aura->GetAuraTicks();
393  break;
394  }
395  // Touch the Nightmare
396  case 50341:
397  {
398  if (eff_idx == EFFECT_INDEX_2)
399  damage = int32(unitTarget->GetMaxHealth() * 0.3f);
400  break;
401  }
402  // Tympanic Tantrum
403  case 62775:
404  {
405  damage = unitTarget->GetMaxHealth() / 10;
406  break;
407  }
408  // Hand of Rekoning (name not have typos ;) )
409  case 67485:
410  damage += uint32(0.5f * m_caster->GetTotalAttackPowerValue(BASE_ATTACK));
411  break;
412  // Magic Bane normal (Forge of Souls - Bronjahm)
413  case 68793:
414  {
415  damage += uint32(unitTarget->GetMaxPower(POWER_MANA) / 2);
416  damage = std::min(damage, 10000);
417  break;
418  }
419  // Magic Bane heroic (Forge of Souls - Bronjahm)
420  case 69050:
421  {
422  damage += uint32(unitTarget->GetMaxPower(POWER_MANA) / 2);
423  damage = std::min(damage, 15000);
424  break;
425  }
426  }
427  break;
428  }
429  case SPELLFAMILY_WARRIOR:
430  {
431  // Bloodthirst
432  if (m_spellInfo->SpellFamilyFlags & uint64(0x40000000000))
433  {
434  damage = uint32(damage * (m_caster->GetTotalAttackPowerValue(BASE_ATTACK)) / 100);
435  }
436  // Shield Slam
437  else if ((m_spellInfo->SpellFamilyFlags & uint64(0x0000020000000000)) && m_spellInfo->Category == 1209)
438  damage += int32(m_caster->GetShieldBlockValue());
439  // Revenge ${$m1+$AP*0.310} to ${$M1+$AP*0.310}
440  else if (m_spellInfo->SpellFamilyFlags & uint64(0x0000000000000400))
441  damage += uint32(m_caster->GetTotalAttackPowerValue(BASE_ATTACK) * 0.310f);
442  // Heroic Throw ${$m1+$AP*.50}
443  else if (m_spellInfo->SpellFamilyFlags & uint64(0x0000000100000000))
444  damage += uint32(m_caster->GetTotalAttackPowerValue(BASE_ATTACK) * 0.5f);
445  // Shattering Throw ${$m1+$AP*.50}
446  else if (m_spellInfo->SpellFamilyFlags & uint64(0x0040000000000000))
447  damage += uint32(m_caster->GetTotalAttackPowerValue(BASE_ATTACK) * 0.5f);
448  // Shockwave ${$m3/100*$AP}
449  else if (m_spellInfo->SpellFamilyFlags & uint64(0x0000800000000000))
450  {
451  int32 pct = m_caster->CalculateSpellEffectValue(unitTarget, m_spellInfo, EFFECT_INDEX_2);
452  if (pct > 0)
453  damage += int32(m_caster->GetTotalAttackPowerValue(BASE_ATTACK) * pct / 100);
454  break;
455  }
456  // Thunder Clap
457  else if (m_spellInfo->SpellFamilyFlags & uint64(0x0000000000000080))
458  {
459  damage += int32(m_caster->GetTotalAttackPowerValue(BASE_ATTACK) * 12 / 100);
460  }
461  break;
462  }
463  case SPELLFAMILY_WARLOCK:
464  {
465  // Incinerate Rank 1 & 2
466  if ((m_spellInfo->SpellFamilyFlags & uint64(0x00004000000000)) && m_spellInfo->SpellIconID == 2128)
467  {
468  // Incinerate does more dmg (dmg*0.25) if the target have Immolate debuff.
469  // Check aura state for speed but aura state set not only for Immolate spell
470  if (unitTarget->HasAuraState(AURA_STATE_CONFLAGRATE))
471  {
472  Unit::AuraList const& RejorRegr = unitTarget->GetAurasByType(SPELL_AURA_PERIODIC_DAMAGE);
473  for (auto i : RejorRegr)
474  {
475  // Immolate
476  if (i->GetSpellProto()->SpellFamilyName == SPELLFAMILY_WARLOCK &&
477  (i->GetSpellProto()->SpellFamilyFlags & uint64(0x00000000000004)))
478  {
479  damage += damage / 4;
480  break;
481  }
482  }
483  }
484  }
485  // Shadowflame
486  else if (m_spellInfo->SpellFamilyFlags & uint64(0x0001000000000000))
487  {
488  // Apply DOT part
489  switch (m_spellInfo->Id)
490  {
491  case 47897: m_caster->CastSpell(unitTarget, 47960, TRIGGERED_OLD_TRIGGERED); break;
492  case 61290: m_caster->CastSpell(unitTarget, 61291, TRIGGERED_OLD_TRIGGERED); break;
493  default:
494  sLog.outError("Spell::EffectDummy: Unhandeled Shadowflame spell rank %u", m_spellInfo->Id);
495  break;
496  }
497  }
498  // Conflagrate - consumes Immolate or Shadowflame
499  else if (m_spellInfo->TargetAuraState == AURA_STATE_CONFLAGRATE)
500  {
501  Aura const* aura = nullptr; // found req. aura for damage calculation
502 
503  Unit::AuraList const& mPeriodic = unitTarget->GetAurasByType(SPELL_AURA_PERIODIC_DAMAGE);
504  for (auto i : mPeriodic)
505  {
506  // for caster applied auras only
507  if (i->GetSpellProto()->SpellFamilyName != SPELLFAMILY_WARLOCK ||
508  i->GetCasterGuid() != m_caster->GetObjectGuid())
509  continue;
510 
511  // Immolate
512  if (i->GetSpellProto()->IsFitToFamilyMask(uint64(0x0000000000000004)))
513  {
514  aura = i; // it selected always if exist
515  break;
516  }
517 
518  // Shadowflame
519  if (i->GetSpellProto()->IsFitToFamilyMask(uint64(0x0000000000000000), 0x00000002))
520  aura = i; // remember but wait possible Immolate as primary priority
521  }
522 
523  // found Immolate or Shadowflame
524  if (aura)
525  {
526  int32 damagetick = aura->GetModifier()->m_amount;
527  damage += damagetick * 4;
528 
529  // Glyph of Conflagrate
530  if (!m_caster->HasAura(56235))
531  unitTarget->RemoveAurasByCasterSpell(aura->GetId(), m_caster->GetObjectGuid());
532  break;
533  }
534  }
535  break;
536  }
537  case SPELLFAMILY_PRIEST:
538  {
539  // Improved Mind Blast (Mind Blast in shadow form bonus)
540  if (m_caster->GetShapeshiftForm() == FORM_SHADOW && (m_spellInfo->SpellFamilyFlags & uint64(0x00002000)))
541  {
542  Unit::AuraList const& ImprMindBlast = m_caster->GetAurasByType(SPELL_AURA_ADD_FLAT_MODIFIER);
543  for (auto i : ImprMindBlast)
544  {
545  if (i->GetSpellProto()->SpellFamilyName == SPELLFAMILY_PRIEST &&
546  (i->GetSpellProto()->SpellIconID == 95))
547  {
548  int chance = i->GetSpellProto()->CalculateSimpleValue(EFFECT_INDEX_1);
549  if (roll_chance_i(chance))
550  // Mind Trauma
551  m_caster->CastSpell(unitTarget, 48301, TRIGGERED_OLD_TRIGGERED);
552  break;
553  }
554  }
555  }
556  break;
557  }
558  case SPELLFAMILY_DRUID:
559  {
560  // Ferocious Bite
561  if (m_caster->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_PLAYER && (m_spellInfo->SpellFamilyFlags & uint64(0x000800000)) && m_spellInfo->SpellVisual[0] == 6587)
562  {
563  // converts up to 30 points of energy into ($f1+$AP/410) additional damage
564  float ap = m_caster->GetTotalAttackPowerValue(BASE_ATTACK);
565  float multiple = ap / 410 + m_spellInfo->DmgMultiplier[eff_idx];
566  damage += int32(m_caster->GetComboPoints() * ap * 7 / 100);
567  uint32 energy = m_caster->GetPower(POWER_ENERGY);
568  uint32 used_energy = energy > 30 ? 30 : energy;
569  damage += int32(used_energy * multiple);
570  m_caster->SetPower(POWER_ENERGY, energy - used_energy);
571  break;
572  }
573 
574  // L5 Arcane Charge - Promenade Sentinal 23394
575  if (m_spellInfo->Id == 41360)
576  {
577  damage = unitTarget->GetMaxHealth();
578  break;
579  }
580  break;
581  }
582  case SPELLFAMILY_ROGUE:
583  {
584  // Envenom
585  if (m_caster->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_PLAYER && (m_spellInfo->SpellFamilyFlags & uint64(0x800000000)))
586  {
587  // consume from stack dozes not more that have combo-points
588  if (uint32 combo = m_caster->GetComboPoints())
589  {
590  Aura* poison = nullptr;
591  // Lookup for Deadly poison (only attacker applied)
592  Unit::AuraList const& auras = unitTarget->GetAurasByType(SPELL_AURA_PERIODIC_DAMAGE);
593  for (auto aura : auras)
594  {
595  if (aura->GetSpellProto()->SpellFamilyName == SPELLFAMILY_ROGUE &&
596  (aura->GetSpellProto()->SpellFamilyFlags & uint64(0x10000)) &&
597  aura->GetCasterGuid() == m_caster->GetObjectGuid())
598  {
599  poison = aura;
600  break;
601  }
602  }
603  // count consumed deadly poison doses at target
604  if (poison)
605  {
606  bool needConsume = true;
607  uint32 spellId = poison->GetId();
608  uint32 doses = poison->GetStackAmount();
609  if (doses > combo)
610  doses = combo;
611 
612  // Master Poisoner
613  Unit::AuraList const& auraList = ((Player*)m_caster)->GetAurasByType(SPELL_AURA_MOD_DURATION_OF_EFFECTS_BY_DISPEL);
614  for (auto iter : auraList)
615  {
616  if (iter->GetSpellProto()->SpellFamilyName == SPELLFAMILY_ROGUE && iter->GetSpellProto()->SpellIconID == 1960)
617  {
618  if (int32 chance = iter->GetSpellProto()->CalculateSimpleValue(EFFECT_INDEX_2))
619  if (roll_chance_i(chance))
620  needConsume = false;
621 
622  break;
623  }
624  }
625 
626  if (needConsume)
627  unitTarget->RemoveAuraHolderFromStack(spellId, doses, m_caster->GetObjectGuid());
628 
629  damage *= doses;
630  damage += int32(((Player*)m_caster)->GetTotalAttackPowerValue(BASE_ATTACK) * 0.09f * doses);
631  }
632  // Eviscerate and Envenom Bonus Damage (item set effect)
633  if (m_caster->GetDummyAura(37169))
634  damage += m_caster->GetComboPoints() * 40;
635  }
636  }
637  // Eviscerate
638  else if ((m_spellInfo->SpellFamilyFlags & uint64(0x00020000)) && m_caster->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_PLAYER)
639  {
640  if (uint32 combo = m_caster->GetComboPoints())
641  {
642  float ap = m_caster->GetTotalAttackPowerValue(BASE_ATTACK);
643  damage += irand(int32(ap * combo * 0.03f), int32(ap * combo * 0.07f));
644 
645  // Eviscerate and Envenom Bonus Damage (item set effect)
646  if (m_caster->GetDummyAura(37169))
647  damage += combo * 40;
648  }
649  }
650  break;
651  }
652  case SPELLFAMILY_HUNTER:
653  {
654  // Gore
655  if (m_spellInfo->SpellIconID == 1578)
656  {
657  if (m_caster->HasAura(57627)) // Charge 6 sec post-affect
658  damage *= 2;
659  }
660  // Steady Shot
661  else if (m_spellInfo->SpellFamilyFlags & uint64(0x100000000))
662  {
663  bool found = false;
664 
665  // check dazed affect
666  Unit::AuraList const& decSpeedList = unitTarget->GetAurasByType(SPELL_AURA_MOD_DECREASE_SPEED);
667  for (Unit::AuraList::const_iterator iter = decSpeedList.begin(); iter != decSpeedList.end(); ++iter)
668  {
669  if ((*iter)->GetSpellProto()->SpellIconID == 15 && (*iter)->GetSpellProto()->Dispel == 0)
670  {
671  found = true;
672  break;
673  }
674  }
675 
676  if (found)
677  damage += CalculateSpellEffectValue(eff_idx, unitTarget);
678 
679  int32 base = irand((int32)m_caster->GetBaseWeaponDamage(RANGED_ATTACK, MINDAMAGE), (int32)m_caster->GetBaseWeaponDamage(RANGED_ATTACK, MAXDAMAGE));
680  damage += int32(float(base) / m_caster->GetAttackTime(RANGED_ATTACK) * 2800);
681  }
682  break;
683  }
684  case SPELLFAMILY_PALADIN:
685  {
686  // Judgement of Righteousness - receive benefit from Spell Damage and Attack power
687  if (m_spellInfo->Id == 20187)
688  {
689  float ap = m_caster->GetTotalAttackPowerValue(BASE_ATTACK);
690  int32 holy = m_caster->SpellBaseDamageBonusDone(GetSpellSchoolMask(m_spellInfo));
691  if (holy < 0)
692  holy = 0;
693  damage += int32(ap * 0.2f) + int32(holy * 32 / 100);
694  }
695  // Judgement of Vengeance/Corruption ${1+0.22*$SPH+0.14*$AP} + 10% for each application of Holy Vengeance/Blood Corruption on the target
696  else if ((m_spellInfo->SpellFamilyFlags & uint64(0x800000000)) && m_spellInfo->SpellIconID == 2292)
697  {
698  uint32 debuf_id;
699  switch (m_spellInfo->Id)
700  {
701  case 53733: debuf_id = 53742; break;// Judgement of Corruption -> Blood Corruption
702  case 31804: debuf_id = 31803; break;// Judgement of Vengeance -> Holy Vengeance
703  default: return;
704  }
705 
706  float ap = m_caster->GetTotalAttackPowerValue(BASE_ATTACK);
707  int32 holy = m_caster->SpellBaseDamageBonusDone(GetSpellSchoolMask(m_spellInfo));
708  if (holy < 0)
709  holy = 0;
710  damage += int32(ap * 0.14f) + int32(holy * 22 / 100);
711  // Get stack of Holy Vengeance on the target added by caster
712  uint32 stacks = 0;
713  Unit::AuraList const& auras = unitTarget->GetAurasByType(SPELL_AURA_PERIODIC_DAMAGE);
714  for (auto aura : auras)
715  {
716  if ((aura->GetId() == debuf_id) && aura->GetCasterGuid() == m_caster->GetObjectGuid())
717  {
718  stacks = aura->GetStackAmount();
719  break;
720  }
721  }
722  // + 10% for each application of Holy Vengeance on the target
723  if (stacks)
724  damage += damage * stacks * 10 / 100;
725  }
726  // Avenger's Shield ($m1+0.07*$SPH+0.07*$AP) - ranged sdb for future
727  else if (m_spellInfo->SpellFamilyFlags & uint64(0x0000000000004000))
728  {
729  float ap = m_caster->GetTotalAttackPowerValue(BASE_ATTACK);
730  int32 holy = m_caster->SpellBaseDamageBonusDone(GetSpellSchoolMask(m_spellInfo));
731  if (holy < 0)
732  holy = 0;
733  damage += int32(ap * 0.07f) + int32(holy * 7 / 100);
734  }
735  // Hammer of Wrath ($m1+0.15*$SPH+0.15*$AP) - ranged type sdb future fix
736  else if (m_spellInfo->SpellFamilyFlags & uint64(0x0000008000000000))
737  {
738  float ap = m_caster->GetTotalAttackPowerValue(BASE_ATTACK);
739  int32 holy = m_caster->SpellBaseDamageBonusDone(GetSpellSchoolMask(m_spellInfo));
740  if (holy < 0)
741  holy = 0;
742  damage += int32(ap * 0.15f) + int32(holy * 15 / 100);
743  }
744  // Hammer of the Righteous
745  else if (m_spellInfo->SpellFamilyFlags & uint64(0x0004000000000000))
746  {
747  // Add main hand dps * effect[2] amount
748  float average = (m_caster->GetFloatValue(UNIT_FIELD_MINDAMAGE) + m_caster->GetFloatValue(UNIT_FIELD_MAXDAMAGE)) / 2;
749  int32 count = m_caster->CalculateSpellEffectValue(unitTarget, m_spellInfo, EFFECT_INDEX_2);
750  damage += count * int32(average * IN_MILLISECONDS) / m_caster->GetAttackTime(BASE_ATTACK);
751  }
752  // Shield of Righteousness
753  else if (m_spellInfo->SpellFamilyFlags & uint64(0x0010000000000000))
754  {
755  damage += int32(m_caster->GetShieldBlockValue());
756  }
757  // Judgement
758  else if (m_spellInfo->Id == 54158)
759  {
760  // [1 + 0.25 * SPH + 0.16 * AP]
761  damage += int32(m_caster->GetTotalAttackPowerValue(BASE_ATTACK) * 0.16f);
762  }
763  break;
764  }
765  }
766 
767  if (damage >= 0)
768  m_damagePerEffect[eff_idx] = CalculateSpellEffectDamage(unitTarget, damage);
769  }
770 }
771 
772 void Spell::EffectDummy(SpellEffectIndex eff_idx)
773 {
774  // selection by spell family
775  switch (m_spellInfo->SpellFamilyName)
776  {
777  case SPELLFAMILY_GENERIC:
778  {
779  switch (m_spellInfo->Id)
780  {
781  case 3360: // Curse of the Eye
782  {
783  if (unitTarget)
784  m_caster->CastSpell(unitTarget, ((unitTarget->getGender() == GENDER_MALE) ? 10651 : 10653), TRIGGERED_OLD_TRIGGERED);
785 
786  return;
787  }
788  case 7671: // Transformation (human<->worgen)
789  {
790  if (unitTarget) // Transform Visual
791  unitTarget->CastSpell(unitTarget, 24085, TRIGGERED_OLD_TRIGGERED);
792 
793  return;
794  }
795  case 8063: // Deviate Fish
796  {
797  if (m_caster->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_PLAYER)
798  {
799  // 8064 = Sleepy | 8065 = Invigorate | 8066 = Shrink | 8067 = Party Time! | 8068 = Healthy Spirit
800  const uint32 spell_list[5] = {8064, 8065, 8066, 8067, 8068};
801  m_caster->CastSpell(m_caster, spell_list[urand(0, 4)], TRIGGERED_OLD_TRIGGERED, nullptr);
802  }
803 
804  return;
805  }
806  case 8213: // Savory Deviate Delight
807  {
808  if (m_caster->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_PLAYER)
809  m_caster->CastSpell(m_caster, (urand(0, 1)
810  ? (m_caster->getGender() == GENDER_MALE ? 8219 : 8220) // Flip Out - ninja
811  : (m_caster->getGender() == GENDER_MALE ? 8221 : 8222)), TRIGGERED_OLD_TRIGGERED, nullptr); // Yaaarrrr - pirate
812 
813  return;
814  }
815  case 8344: // Gnomish Universal Remote (ItemID: 7506)
816  {
817  if (m_CastItem && unitTarget)
818  {
819  // 8345 - Control the machine | 8346 = Malfunction the machine (root) | 8347 = Taunt/enrage the machine
820  const uint32 spell_list[3] = { 8345, 8346, 8347 };
821  m_caster->CastSpell(unitTarget, spell_list[urand(0, 2)], TRIGGERED_OLD_TRIGGERED, m_CastItem);
822  }
823 
824  return;
825  }
826  case 8606: //Summon Cyclonian
827  {
828  if (!(m_targets.m_targetMask & TARGET_FLAG_DEST_LOCATION))
829  return;
830 
831  float x, y, z;
832  m_targets.getDestination(x, y, z); // database loaded coordinates due to target type
833  m_caster->SummonCreature(6239, x, y, z, 0.0f, TEMPSPAWN_TIMED_OOC_DESPAWN, 30 * IN_MILLISECONDS);
834 
835  return;
836  }
837  case 9012: // Attract Rift Spawn
838  {
839  if (!unitTarget || !unitTarget->HasAura(9032))
840  return;
841 
842  unitTarget->CastSpell(unitTarget, 9010, TRIGGERED_NONE);
843  return;
844  }
845  case 9976: // Polly Eats the E.C.A.C.
846  {
847  if (unitTarget && unitTarget->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_UNIT)
848  {
849  // Summon Polly Jr.
850  unitTarget->CastSpell(unitTarget, 9998, TRIGGERED_OLD_TRIGGERED);
851  ((Creature*)unitTarget)->ForcedDespawn(100);
852  }
853 
854  return;
855  }
856  case 10254: // Stone Dwarf Awaken Visual
857  {
858  if (m_caster->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_UNIT) // see spell 10255 (aura dummy)
859  {
860  m_caster->clearUnitState(UNIT_STAT_ROOT);
861  m_caster->RemoveFlag(UNIT_FIELD_FLAGS, UNIT_FLAG_IMMUNE_TO_PLAYER | UNIT_FLAG_IMMUNE_TO_NPC | UNIT_FLAG_UNINTERACTIBLE);
862  }
863 
864  return;
865  }
866  case 12975: // Last Stand
867  {
868  int32 healthModSpellBasePoints0 = int32(m_caster->GetMaxHealth() * 0.3);
869  m_caster->CastCustomSpell(m_caster, 12976, &healthModSpellBasePoints0, nullptr, nullptr, TRIGGERED_OLD_TRIGGERED, nullptr);
870 
871  return;
872  }
873  case 13006: // Gnomish Shrink Ray (ItemID: 10716)
874  {
875  if (unitTarget && m_CastItem)
876  {
877  uint32 roll = urand(0, 99);
878  // These rates are hella random; someone feel free to correct them
879  if (roll < 3) // Whole party will grow
880  m_caster->CastSpell(m_caster, 13004, TRIGGERED_OLD_TRIGGERED);
881  else if (roll < 6) // Whole party will shrink
882  m_caster->CastSpell(m_caster, 13010, TRIGGERED_OLD_TRIGGERED);
883  else if (roll < 9) // Whole enemy 'team' will grow
884  m_caster->CastSpell(unitTarget, 13004, TRIGGERED_OLD_TRIGGERED);
885  else if (roll < 12) // Whole enemy 'team' will shrink
886  m_caster->CastSpell(unitTarget, 13010, TRIGGERED_OLD_TRIGGERED);
887  else if (roll < 24) // Caster will shrink
888  m_caster->CastSpell(m_caster, 13003, TRIGGERED_OLD_TRIGGERED);
889  else // Enemy target will shrink
890  m_caster->CastSpell(unitTarget, 13003, TRIGGERED_OLD_TRIGGERED);
891  }
892 
893  return;
894  }
895  case 13120: // Net-O-Matic
896  {
897  if (unitTarget && m_CastItem)
898  {
899  uint32 roll = urand(0, 99);
900  if (roll < 2) // 2% for 30 sec self root (off-like chance unknown)
901  m_caster->CastSpell(unitTarget, 16566, TRIGGERED_OLD_TRIGGERED, m_CastItem);
902  else if (roll < 4) // 2% for 20 sec root, charge to target (off-like chance unknown)
903  m_caster->CastSpell(unitTarget, 13119, TRIGGERED_OLD_TRIGGERED, m_CastItem);
904  else // normal root
905  m_caster->CastSpell(unitTarget, 13099, TRIGGERED_OLD_TRIGGERED, m_CastItem);
906  }
907 
908  return;
909  }
910  case 13180: // Gnomish Mind Control Cap (ItemID: 10726)
911  {
912  if (unitTarget && m_CastItem)
913  {
914  uint32 roll = urand(0, 9);
915  if (roll == 1 && unitTarget->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_PLAYER)
916  unitTarget->CastSpell(m_caster, 13181, TRIGGERED_OLD_TRIGGERED, m_CastItem);
917  else if (roll)
918  m_caster->CastSpell(unitTarget, 13181, TRIGGERED_OLD_TRIGGERED, m_CastItem);
919  }
920 
921  return;
922  }
923  case 13489:
924  {
925  if (unitTarget)
926  unitTarget->CastSpell(unitTarget, 14744, TRIGGERED_OLD_TRIGGERED);
927 
928  return;
929  }
930  case 13567: // Dummy Trigger
931  {
932  // can be used for different aura triggering, so select by aura
933  if (m_triggeredByAuraSpell && unitTarget)
934  {
935  switch (m_triggeredByAuraSpell->Id)
936  {
937  case 26467: // Persistent Shield
938  m_caster->CastCustomSpell(unitTarget, 26470, &damage, nullptr, nullptr, TRIGGERED_OLD_TRIGGERED);
939  break;
940  default:
941  sLog.outError("EffectDummy: Non-handled case for spell 13567 for triggered aura %u", m_triggeredByAuraSpell->Id);
942  break;
943  }
944  }
945 
946  return;
947  }
948  case 14537: // Six Demon Bag
949  {
950  if (unitTarget)

4493  if (PetAura const* petSpell = sSpellMgr.GetPetAura(m_spellInfo->Id, eff_idx))
4494  {
4495  m_caster->AddPetAura(petSpell);
4496  return;
4497  }
4498 
4499  // Script based implementation. Must be used only for not good for implementation in core spell effects
4500  // So called only for not processed cases
4501  bool libraryResult = false;
4502  if (gameObjTarget)
4503  libraryResult = sScriptDevAIMgr.OnEffectDummy(m_caster, m_spellInfo->Id, eff_idx, gameObjTarget, m_originalCasterGUID);
4504  else if (unitTarget && unitTarget->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_UNIT)
4505  libraryResult = sScriptDevAIMgr.OnEffectDummy(m_caster, m_spellInfo->Id, eff_idx, (Creature*)unitTarget, m_originalCasterGUID);
4506  else if (itemTarget)
4507  libraryResult = sScriptDevAIMgr.OnEffectDummy(m_caster, m_spellInfo->Id, eff_idx, itemTarget, m_originalCasterGUID);
4508 
4509  if (libraryResult || (!unitTarget && !gameObjTarget))
4510  return;
4511 
4512  // Previous effect might have started script
4513  if (!ScriptMgr::CanSpellEffectStartDBScript(m_spellInfo, eff_idx))
4514  return;
4515 
4516  auto& data = SpellTargetMgr::GetSpellTargetingData(m_spellInfo->Id);
4517  SpellTargetImplicitType effectTargetType = data.implicitType[eff_idx];
4518 
4519  DEBUG_FILTER_LOG(LOG_FILTER_SPELL_CAST, "Spell ScriptStart spellid %u in EffectDummy", m_spellInfo->Id);
4520  if (effectTargetType == TARGET_TYPE_UNIT || effectTargetType == TARGET_TYPE_UNIT_DEST)
4521  m_trueCaster->GetMap()->ScriptsStart(SCRIPT_TYPE_SPELL, m_spellInfo->Id, m_trueCaster, unitTarget);
4522  else if (effectTargetType == TARGET_TYPE_GAMEOBJECT || (effectTargetType == TARGET_TYPE_LOCK && gameObjTarget))
4523  m_trueCaster->GetMap()->ScriptsStart(SCRIPT_TYPE_SPELL, m_spellInfo->Id, m_trueCaster, gameObjTarget);
4524 }

4559 void Spell::EffectClearQuest(SpellEffectIndex eff_idx)
4560 {
4561  if (m_caster->GetTypeId() != TYPEID_PLAYER)
4562  return;
4563 
4564  Player* player = (Player*)m_caster;
4565 
4566  uint32 quest_id = m_spellInfo->EffectMiscValue[eff_idx];
4567 
4568  if (!sObjectMgr.GetQuestTemplate(quest_id))
4569  {
4570  sLog.outError("Spell::EffectClearQuest spell entry %u attempt clear quest entry %u but this quest does not exist.", m_spellInfo->Id, quest_id);
4571  return;
4572  }
4573 
4574  // remove quest possibly in quest log (is that expected?)
4575  for (uint16 slot = 0; slot < MAX_QUEST_LOG_SIZE; ++slot)
4576  {
4577  uint32 quest = player->GetQuestSlotQuestId(slot);
4578 
4579  if (quest == quest_id)
4580  {
4581  player->SetQuestSlot(slot, 0);
4582  // ignore unequippable quest items in this case, it will still be equipped
4583  player->TakeQuestSourceItem(quest_id, false);
4584  }
4585  }
4586 
4587  player->SetQuestStatus(quest_id, QUEST_STATUS_NONE);
4588  player->getQuestStatusMap()[quest_id].m_rewarded = false;
4589 }

4591 void Spell::EffectForceCast(SpellEffectIndex effIndex)
4592 {
4593  if (!unitTarget)
4594  return;
4595 
4596  uint32 triggered_spell_id = m_spellInfo->EffectTriggerSpell[effIndex];
4597 
4598  // normal case
4599  SpellEntry const* spellInfo = sSpellTemplate.LookupEntry<SpellEntry>(triggered_spell_id);
4600 
4601  if (!spellInfo)
4602  {
4603  sLog.outError("EffectForceCast of spell %u: triggering unknown spell id %i", m_spellInfo->Id, triggered_spell_id);
4604  return;
4605  }
4606 
4607  int32 basePoints = damage;
4608 
4609  SpellCastTargets targets;
4610 
4611  switch (m_spellInfo->EffectImplicitTargetA[effIndex])
4612  {
4613  case TARGET_LOCATION_UNIT_MINION_POSITION: break; // confirmed by 31348 nothing is forwarded
4614  default:
4615  if (m_spellInfo->Effect[effIndex] == SPELL_EFFECT_FORCE_CAST_2)
4616  targets.setUnitTarget(m_caster);
4617  else if (IsSpellRequireTarget(spellInfo))
4618  targets.setUnitTarget(unitTarget);
4619  break;
4620  }
4621 
4622  if (spellInfo->Targets & TARGET_FLAG_DEST_LOCATION)
4623  {
4624  if (m_targets.m_targetMask & TARGET_FLAG_DEST_LOCATION)
4625  {
4626  float x, y, z;
4627  m_targets.getDestination(x, y, z);
4628  targets.setDestination(x, y, z);
4629  }
4630  else if (unitTarget)
4631  {
4632  float x, y, z;
4633  unitTarget->GetPosition(x, y, z);
4634  targets.setDestination(x, y, z);
4635  }
4636  }
4637 
4638  // spell effect 141 needs to be cast as custom with basePoints
4639  if (m_spellInfo->Effect[effIndex] == SPELL_EFFECT_FORCE_CAST_WITH_VALUE)
4640  unitTarget->CastCustomSpell(targets, spellInfo, &basePoints, &basePoints, &basePoints, TRIGGERED_OLD_TRIGGERED, nullptr, nullptr, ObjectGuid(), m_spellInfo);
4641  else
4642  unitTarget->CastSpell(targets, spellInfo, TRIGGERED_OLD_TRIGGERED, nullptr, nullptr, ObjectGuid(), m_spellInfo);
4643 }
4644 
4645 void Spell::EffectTriggerSpell(SpellEffectIndex effIndex)
4646 {
4647  uint32 triggered_spell_id = m_spellInfo->EffectTriggerSpell[effIndex];
4648 
4649  // special cases
4650  switch (triggered_spell_id)
4651  {
4652  case 23209: // Terrordale Haunting Spirit
4653  if (urand(1, 100) > 55)
4654  return;
4655  break;
4656  case 23253: // Terrordale Haunting Spirit
4657  if (urand(1, 100) > 35)
4658  return;
4659  break;
4660  // Flame Wreath: Explosion
4661  case 29950:
4662  m_caster->RemoveAurasDueToSpellByCancel(29947);
4663  return;
4664  case 41967: // Priest Shadowfiend (34433) - handled in spell script
4665  case 47531: // Dismiss pet - suppress error
4666  return;
4667  case 53258: // Empower Rune Weapon
4668  {
4669  // remove cooldown of frost/death, undead/blood activated in main spell
4670  if (unitTarget->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_PLAYER)
4671  {
4672  bool res1 = ((Player*)unitTarget)->ActivateRunes(RUNE_FROST, 2);
4673  bool res2 = ((Player*)unitTarget)->ActivateRunes(RUNE_DEATH, 2);
4674  if (res1 || res2)
4675  ((Player*)unitTarget)->ResyncRunes();
4676  }
4677  return;
4678  }
4679  case 58832: // Mirror Image
4680  {
4681  // Glyph of Mirror Image
4682  if (m_caster->HasAura(63093))
4683  m_caster->CastSpell(m_caster, 65047, TRIGGERED_OLD_TRIGGERED, m_CastItem, nullptr, m_originalCasterGUID);
4684  break;
4685  }
4686  }
4687 
4688  // normal case
4689  SpellEntry const* spellInfo = sSpellTemplate.LookupEntry<SpellEntry>(triggered_spell_id);
4690  if (!spellInfo)
4691  {
4692  // No previous Effect might have started a script
4693  bool startDBScript = unitTarget && ScriptMgr::CanSpellEffectStartDBScript(m_spellInfo, effIndex);
4694  if (startDBScript)
4695  {
4696  DEBUG_FILTER_LOG(LOG_FILTER_SPELL_CAST, "Spell ScriptStart spellid %u in EffectTriggerSpell", m_spellInfo->Id);
4697  startDBScript = m_caster->GetMap()->ScriptsStart(SCRIPT_TYPE_SPELL, m_spellInfo->Id, m_caster, unitTarget);
4698  }
4699 
4700  if (!startDBScript)
4701  sLog.outError("EffectTriggerSpell of spell %u: triggering unknown spell id %i", m_spellInfo->Id, triggered_spell_id);
4702  return;
4703  }
4704 
4705  // select formal caster for triggered spell
4706  Unit* caster = m_caster;
4707 
4708  // some triggered spells require specific equipment
4709  if (spellInfo->EquippedItemClass >= 0 && m_caster->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_PLAYER)
4710  {
4711  // main hand weapon required
4712  if (spellInfo->HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR_EX3_REQUIRES_MAIN_HAND_WEAPON))
4713  {
4714  Item* item = ((Player*)m_caster)->GetWeaponForAttack(BASE_ATTACK, true, false);
4715 
4716  // skip spell if no weapon in slot or broken
4717  if (!item)
4718  return;
4719 
4720  // skip spell if weapon not fit to triggered spell
4721  if (!item->IsFitToSpellRequirements(spellInfo))
4722  return;
4723  }
4724 
4725  // offhand hand weapon required
4726  if (spellInfo->HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR_EX3_REQUIRES_OFFHAND_WEAPON))
4727  {
4728  Item* item = ((Player*)m_caster)->GetWeaponForAttack(OFF_ATTACK, true, false);
4729 
4730  // skip spell if no weapon in slot or broken
4731  if (!item)
4732  return;
4733 
4734  // skip spell if weapon not fit to triggered spell
4735  if (!item->IsFitToSpellRequirements(spellInfo))
4736  return;
4737  }
4738  }
4739 
4740  SpellCastTargets targets;
4741 
4742  switch (m_spellInfo->EffectImplicitTargetA[effIndex])
4743  {
4744  case TARGET_LOCATION_UNIT_MINION_POSITION: break; // confirmed by 31348 nothing is forwarded
4745  default:
4746  if (IsSpellRequireTarget(spellInfo))
4747  targets.setUnitTarget(unitTarget);
4748  break;
4749  }
4750 
4751  if (spellInfo->Targets & TARGET_FLAG_DEST_LOCATION)
4752  {
4753  if (m_targets.m_targetMask & TARGET_FLAG_DEST_LOCATION)
4754  {
4755  float x, y, z;
4756  m_targets.getDestination(x, y, z);
4757  targets.setDestination(x, y, z);
4758  }
4759  else if (unitTarget)
4760  {
4761  float x, y, z;
4762  unitTarget->GetPosition(x, y, z);
4763  targets.setDestination(x, y, z);
4764  }
4765  }
4766 
4767  caster->CastSpell(targets, spellInfo, TRIGGERED_OLD_TRIGGERED, m_CastItem, nullptr, m_originalCasterGUID, m_spellInfo);
4768 }

4770 void Spell::EffectTriggerMissileSpell(SpellEffectIndex effIndex)
4771 {

4774  // normal case

4786  m_spellInfo->Id, effIndex, triggered_spell_id);
4787  return;

4798  else
4799  targets.setUnitTarget(unitTarget);
4800  }
4801  else if (gameObjTarget)

4810  }
4811  else
4812  m_caster->CastSpell(targets, spellInfo, TRIGGERED_OLD_TRIGGERED, m_CastItem, nullptr, m_originalCasterGUID, m_spellInfo);
4813 }

4815 void Spell::EffectJump(SpellEffectIndex eff_idx)
4816 {
4817  if (!m_trueCaster->IsUnit())
4818  return;
4819 
4820  if (m_caster->IsTaxiFlying())
4821  return;
4822 
4823  // Init dest coordinates
4824  Position pos;
4825  if (m_targets.m_targetMask & TARGET_FLAG_DEST_LOCATION)
4826  {
4827  pos = m_targets.getDestination();
4828 
4829  if (m_spellInfo->EffectImplicitTargetA[eff_idx] == TARGET_LOCATION_UNIT_BACK)
4830  {
4831  // explicit cast data from client or server-side cast
4832  // some spell at client send caster
4833  Unit* pTarget = nullptr;
4834  if (m_targets.getUnitTarget() && m_targets.getUnitTarget() != m_caster)
4835  pTarget = m_targets.getUnitTarget();
4836  else if (m_caster->GetVictim())
4837  pTarget = m_caster->GetVictim();
4838  else if (m_caster->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_PLAYER)
4839  pTarget = m_caster->GetMap()->GetUnit(((Player*)m_caster)->GetSelectionGuid());
4840 
4841  pos.o = pTarget ? pTarget->GetOrientation() : m_caster->GetOrientation();
4842  }
4843  else
4844  pos.o = m_caster->GetOrientation();
4845  }
4846  else if (unitTarget)
4847  {
4848  unitTarget->GetContactPoint(m_caster, pos.x, pos.y, pos.z, CONTACT_DISTANCE);
4849  pos.o = m_caster->GetOrientation();
4850  }
4851  else if (gameObjTarget)
4852  {
4853  gameObjTarget->GetContactPoint(m_caster, pos.x, pos.y, pos.z, CONTACT_DISTANCE);
4854  pos.o = m_caster->GetOrientation();
4855  }
4856  else
4857  {
4858  sLog.outError("Spell::EffectJump - unsupported target mode for spell ID %u", m_spellInfo->Id);
4859  return;
4860  }
4861 
4862  // Try to normalize Z coord because GetContactPoint do nothing with Z axis
4863  m_caster->UpdateAllowedPositionZ(pos.x, pos.y, pos.z);
4864 
4865  float runSpeed = baseMoveSpeed[MOVE_RUN];
4866  if (m_caster->IsCreature())
4867  runSpeed *= static_cast<Creature*>(m_caster)->GetCreatureInfo()->SpeedRun;
4868 
4869  float multiplier = m_spellInfo->EffectMultipleValue[eff_idx];
4870  if (multiplier <= 0.0f)
4871  multiplier = 1.0f;
4872 
4873  float horizontalSpeed = std::min(runSpeed * 3.0f * multiplier, std::max(28.0f, m_caster->GetSpeed(MOVE_RUN) * 4.0f));
4874  float dist = sqrt(m_caster->GetDistance2d(pos.x, pos.y, DIST_CALC_NONE));
4875 
4876  float duration = dist / horizontalSpeed;
4877  float durationSqr = duration * duration;
4878  float minHeight = m_spellInfo->EffectMiscValue[eff_idx] ? m_spellInfo->EffectMiscValue[eff_idx] / 10.0f : 0.5f; // Lower bound is blizzlike
4879  float maxHeight = m_spellInfo->EffectMiscValueB[eff_idx] ? m_spellInfo->EffectMiscValueB[eff_idx] / 10.0f : 1000.0f; // Upper bound is unknown
4880  float height;
4881  if (durationSqr < minHeight * 8 / Movement::gravity)
4882  height = minHeight;
4883  else if (durationSqr > maxHeight * 8 / Movement::gravity)
4884  height = maxHeight;
4885  else
4886  height = Movement::gravity * durationSqr / 8;
4887 
4888  float verticalSpeed = std::sqrt(2 * Movement::gravity * height);
4889  m_caster->GetMotionMaster()->MoveJumpFacingVerticalSpeed(pos, horizontalSpeed, verticalSpeed, EVENT_JUMP);
4890 }

5038  case 2:

5040  m_caster->CastSpell(m_caster, 36901, TRIGGERED_OLD_TRIGGERED);
5041  break;
5042  case 3:
5043  // Increase the size
5044  m_caster->CastSpell(m_caster, 36895, TRIGGERED_OLD_TRIGGERED);
5045  break;
5046  case 4:
5047  // Transform
5048  {
5049  if (((Player*)m_caster)->GetTeam() == ALLIANCE)
5050  m_caster->CastSpell(m_caster, 36897, TRIGGERED_OLD_TRIGGERED);
5051  else
5052  m_caster->CastSpell(m_caster, 36899, TRIGGERED_OLD_TRIGGERED);
5053  break;
5054  }
5055  }
5056  }
5057  }
5058  }
5059 }

5094 void Spell::EffectPowerDrain(SpellEffectIndex eff_idx)
5095 {
5096  if (m_spellInfo->EffectMiscValue[eff_idx] < 0 || m_spellInfo->EffectMiscValue[eff_idx] >= MAX_POWERS)
5097  return;
5098 
5099  Powers powerType = Powers(m_spellInfo->EffectMiscValue[eff_idx]);
5100 
5101  if (!unitTarget)
5102  return;
5103  if (!unitTarget->IsAlive())
5104  return;
5105  if (unitTarget->GetPowerType() != powerType)
5106  return;
5107  if (damage < 0)
5108  return;
5109 
5110  uint32 curPower = unitTarget->GetPower(powerType);
5111 
5112  // add spell damage bonus
5113  damage = m_caster->SpellDamageBonusDone(unitTarget, m_spellSchoolMask, m_spellInfo, uint32(damage), SPELL_DIRECT_DAMAGE);
5114  damage = unitTarget->SpellDamageBonusTaken(m_caster, m_spellSchoolMask, m_spellInfo, uint32(damage), SPELL_DIRECT_DAMAGE);
5115 
5116  uint32 power = damage;
5117 
5118  power -= unitTarget->GetResilienceRatingDamageReduction(power, SpellDmgClass(m_spellInfo->DmgClass), false, powerType);
5119 
5120  int32 new_damage;
5121  if (curPower < power)
5122  new_damage = curPower;
5123  else
5124  new_damage = power;
5125 
5126  unitTarget->ModifyPower(powerType, -new_damage);
5127 
5128  float gainMultiplier = 1.0f;
5129 
5130  // Do not gain power from self drain or when power types don't match
5131  if (m_caster->GetPowerType() == powerType && m_caster != unitTarget)
5132  {
5133  gainMultiplier = m_spellInfo->EffectMultipleValue[eff_idx];
5134 
5135  if (Player* modOwner = m_caster->GetSpellModOwner())
5136  modOwner->ApplySpellMod(m_spellInfo->Id, SPELLMOD_MULTIPLE_VALUE, gainMultiplier);
5137  }
5138 
5139  m_spellLog.AddLog(uint32(SPELL_EFFECT_POWER_DRAIN), unitTarget->GetPackGUID(), new_damage, uint32(powerType), gainMultiplier);
5140 
5141  if (int32 gain = int32(new_damage * gainMultiplier))
5142  m_caster->EnergizeBySpell(m_caster, m_spellInfo, gain, powerType, false);
5143 }

5148  StartEvents_Event(m_trueCaster->GetMap(), m_spellInfo->EffectMiscValue[effectIndex], m_trueCaster, m_eventTarget, true);

5151 void Spell::EffectPowerBurn(SpellEffectIndex eff_idx)
5152 {
5153  if (m_spellInfo->EffectMiscValue[eff_idx] < 0 || m_spellInfo->EffectMiscValue[eff_idx] >= MAX_POWERS)
5154  return;
5155 
5156  Powers powertype = Powers(m_spellInfo->EffectMiscValue[eff_idx]);
5157 
5158  if (!unitTarget)
5159  return;
5160  if (!unitTarget->IsAlive())
5161  return;
5162  if (unitTarget->GetPowerType() != powertype)
5163  return;
5164  if (damage < 0)
5165  return;
5166 
5167  // burn x% of target's mana, up to maximum of 2x% of caster's mana (Mana Burn)
5168  if (m_spellInfo->ManaCostPercentage)
5169  {
5170  int32 maxdamage = m_caster->GetMaxPower(powertype) * damage * 2 / 100;
5171  damage = unitTarget->GetMaxPower(powertype) * damage / 100;
5172  if (damage > maxdamage)
5173  damage = maxdamage;
5174  }
5175 
5176  int32 curPower = int32(unitTarget->GetPower(powertype));
5177 
5178  int32 power = damage;
5179 
5180  power -= unitTarget->GetResilienceRatingDamageReduction(uint32(power), SpellDmgClass(m_spellInfo->DmgClass), false, powertype);
5181 
5182  int32 new_damage = (curPower < power) ? curPower : power;
5183 
5184  unitTarget->ModifyPower(powertype, -new_damage);
5185  float multiplier = m_spellInfo->EffectMultipleValue[eff_idx];
5186 
5187  if (Player* modOwner = m_caster->GetSpellModOwner())
5188  modOwner->ApplySpellMod(m_spellInfo->Id, SPELLMOD_MULTIPLE_VALUE, multiplier);
5189 
5190  new_damage = int32(new_damage * multiplier);
5191 
5192  m_damagePerEffect[eff_idx] = CalculateSpellEffectDamage(unitTarget, new_damage);
5193  m_spellLog.AddLog(uint32(SPELL_EFFECT_POWER_BURN), unitTarget->GetPackGUID(), new_damage, uint32(powertype), multiplier);
5194 }
5195 
5196 void Spell::EffectHeal(SpellEffectIndex eff_idx)
5197 {
5198  if (unitTarget && unitTarget->IsAlive() && damage >= 0)
5199  {
5200  // Try to get original caster
5201  Unit* caster = GetAffectiveCaster();
5202  if (!caster)
5203  return;
5204 
5205  int32 addhealth = damage;
5206 
5207  // Seal of Light proc
5208  if (m_spellInfo->Id == 20167)
5209  {
5210  float ap = caster->GetTotalAttackPowerValue(BASE_ATTACK);
5211  int32 holy = caster->SpellBaseHealingBonusDone(GetSpellSchoolMask(m_spellInfo));
5212  if (holy < 0)
5213  holy = 0;
5214  addhealth += int32(ap * 0.15) + int32(holy * 15 / 100);
5215  }
5216  // Death Pact (percent heal)
5217  else if (m_spellInfo->Id == 48743)
5218  addhealth = addhealth * unitTarget->GetMaxHealth() / 100;
5219  // Swiftmend - consumes Regrowth or Rejuvenation
5220  else if (m_spellInfo->TargetAuraState == AURA_STATE_SWIFTMEND && unitTarget->HasAuraState(AURA_STATE_SWIFTMEND))
5221  {
5222  Unit::AuraList const& RejorRegr = unitTarget->GetAurasByType(SPELL_AURA_PERIODIC_HEAL);
5223  // find most short by duration
5224  Aura* targetAura = nullptr;
5225  for (auto i : RejorRegr)
5226  {
5227  if (i->GetSpellProto()->SpellFamilyName == SPELLFAMILY_DRUID &&
5228  // Regrowth or Rejuvenation 0x40 | 0x10
5229  (i->GetSpellProto()->SpellFamilyFlags & uint64(0x0000000000000050)))
5230  {
5231  if (!targetAura || i->GetAuraDuration() < targetAura->GetAuraDuration())
5232  targetAura = i;
5233  }
5234  }
5235 
5236  if (!targetAura)
5237  {
5238  sLog.outError("Target (GUID: %u TypeId: %u) has aurastate AURA_STATE_SWIFTMEND but no matching aura.", unitTarget->GetGUIDLow(), unitTarget->GetTypeId());
5239  return;
5240  }
5241  int idx = 0;
5242  while (idx < 3)
5243  {
5244  if (targetAura->GetSpellProto()->EffectApplyAuraName[idx] == SPELL_AURA_PERIODIC_HEAL)
5245  break;
5246  ++idx;
5247  }
5248 
5249  int32 tickheal = targetAura->GetModifier()->m_amount;
5250  int32 tickcount = GetSpellDuration(targetAura->GetSpellProto()) / targetAura->GetSpellProto()->EffectAmplitude[idx];
5251 
5252  // Glyph of Swiftmend
5253  if (!caster->HasAura(54824))
5254  unitTarget->RemoveAurasByCasterSpell(targetAura->GetId(), targetAura->GetCasterGuid());
5255 
5256  addhealth += tickheal * tickcount;
5257  }
5258  else if (m_spellInfo->SpellFamilyName == SPELLFAMILY_POTION)
5259  {
5260  if (m_caster->HasAura(17619)) // Alchemists stone
5261  addhealth *= 1.4f; // increase healing by 40%
5262  }
5263  else
5264  {
5265  switch (m_spellInfo->Id)
5266  {
5267  // Crusader Enchant: Holy Strength amount decrease by 4% each level after 60
5268  case 20007:
5269  {
5270  if (GetCaster()->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_PLAYER && GetCaster()->GetLevel() > 60)
5271  addhealth = int32(addhealth * (1 - (((float(GetCaster()->GetLevel()) - 60) * 4) / 100)));
5272  break;
5273  }
5274  // Vessel of the Naaru (Vial of the Sunwell trinket)
5275  case 45064:
5276  {
5277  // Amount of heal - depends from stacked Holy Energy
5278  int damageAmount = 0;
5279  Unit::AuraList const& mDummyAuras = m_caster->GetAurasByType(SPELL_AURA_DUMMY);
5280  for (auto mDummyAura : mDummyAuras)
5281  if (mDummyAura->GetId() == 45062)
5282  damageAmount += mDummyAura->GetModifier()->m_amount;
5283  if (damageAmount)
5284  m_caster->RemoveAurasDueToSpell(45062);
5285 
5286  addhealth += damageAmount;
5287  break;
5288 
5289  }
5290  case 67486: // Runic Healing Injector
5291  case 67489: // Healing Potion Injector
5292  {
5293  Player* player = (Player*)unitTarget;
5294  if (player->HasSkill(SKILL_ENGINEERING))
5295  addhealth += int32(addhealth * 0.25);
5296  break;
5297  }
5298  }
5299  }
5300 
5301  // Chain Healing
5302  if (m_spellInfo->SpellFamilyName == SPELLFAMILY_SHAMAN && m_spellInfo->SpellFamilyFlags & uint64(0x0000000000000100))
5303  {
5304  if (unitTarget == m_targets.getUnitTarget())
5305  {
5306  // check for Riptide
5307  Aura* riptide = unitTarget->GetAura(SPELL_AURA_PERIODIC_HEAL, SPELLFAMILY_SHAMAN, uint64(0x0), 0x00000010, caster->GetObjectGuid());
5308  if (riptide)
5309  {
5310  addhealth += addhealth / 4;
5311  unitTarget->RemoveAurasDueToSpell(riptide->GetId());
5312  }
5313  }
5314  }
5315 
5316  addhealth = caster->SpellHealingBonusDone(unitTarget, m_spellInfo, addhealth, HEAL);
5317  addhealth = unitTarget->SpellHealingBonusTaken(caster, m_spellInfo, addhealth, HEAL);
5318 
5319  m_healingPerEffect[eff_idx] = addhealth;
5320  }
5321 }

5364 void Spell::EffectHealthLeech(SpellEffectIndex eff_idx)
5365 {

5367  return;

5369  return;
5370

5372  return;
5373 
5374  DEBUG_FILTER_LOG(LOG_FILTER_SPELL_CAST, "HealthLeech :%i", damage);
5375 
5376  uint32 curHealth = unitTarget->GetHealth();
5377  damage = m_caster->SpellNonMeleeDamageLog(unitTarget, m_spellInfo->Id, damage);
5378  if ((int32)curHealth < damage)
5379  damage = curHealth;
5380 
5381  float multiplier = m_spellInfo->EffectMultipleValue[eff_idx];
5382 
5383  if (Player* modOwner = m_caster->GetSpellModOwner())
5384  modOwner->ApplySpellMod(m_spellInfo->Id, SPELLMOD_MULTIPLE_VALUE, multiplier);
5385 
5386  int32 heal = int32(damage * multiplier);
5387  if (m_caster->IsAlive())
5388  {
5389  heal = m_caster->SpellHealingBonusTaken(m_caster, m_spellInfo, heal, HEAL);
5390 
5391  uint32 absorb = 0;
5392  m_caster->CalculateHealAbsorb(heal, &absorb);
5393 
5394  m_caster->DealHeal(m_caster, heal - absorb, m_spellInfo, false, absorb);
5395  }

5397 
5398 bool Spell::DoCreateItem(SpellEffectIndex eff_idx, uint32 itemtype, bool reportError)
5399 {
5400  if (!unitTarget || unitTarget->GetTypeId() != TYPEID_PLAYER)
5401  return false;
5402 
5403  Player* player = (Player*)unitTarget;
5404 
5405  uint32 newitemid = itemtype;
5406  ItemPrototype const* pProto = ObjectMgr::GetItemPrototype(newitemid);
5407  if (!pProto)
5408  {
5409  if (reportError)
5410  player->SendEquipError(EQUIP_ERR_ITEM_NOT_FOUND, nullptr, nullptr);
5411  return false;
5412  }
5413 
5414  uint32 num_to_add = damage;
5415 
5416  if (num_to_add < 1)
5417  num_to_add = 1;
5418  if (num_to_add > pProto->GetMaxStackSize())
5419  num_to_add = pProto->GetMaxStackSize();
5420 
5421  // init items_count to 1, since 1 item will be created regardless of specialization
5422  int items_count = 1;
5423  // the chance to create additional items
5424  float additionalCreateChance = 0.0f;
5425  // the maximum number of created additional items
5426  uint8 additionalMaxNum = 0;
5427  // get the chance and maximum number for creating extra items
5428  if (canCreateExtraItems(player, m_spellInfo->Id, additionalCreateChance, additionalMaxNum))
5429  {
5430  // roll with this chance till we roll not to create or we create the max num
5431  while (roll_chance_f(additionalCreateChance) && items_count <= additionalMaxNum)
5432  ++items_count;
5433  }
5434 
5435  // really will be created more items
5436  num_to_add *= items_count;
5437 
5438  // can the player store the new item?
5439  ItemPosCountVec dest;
5440  uint32 no_space = 0;
5441  InventoryResult msg = player->CanStoreNewItem(NULL_BAG, NULL_SLOT, dest, newitemid, num_to_add, &no_space);
5442  if (msg != EQUIP_ERR_OK)
5443  {
5444  // convert to possible store amount
5445  if (msg == EQUIP_ERR_INVENTORY_FULL || msg == EQUIP_ERR_CANT_CARRY_MORE_OF_THIS)
5446  num_to_add -= no_space;
5447 
5448  // ignore mana gem case (next effect will recharge existing example)
5449  if (eff_idx == EFFECT_INDEX_0 && m_spellInfo->Effect[EFFECT_INDEX_1] == SPELL_EFFECT_DUMMY)
5450  return false;
5451 
5452  // if not created by another reason from full inventory or unique items amount limitation
5453  if (reportError)
5454  player->SendEquipError(msg, nullptr, nullptr, newitemid);
5455  return false;
5456  }
5457 
5458  if (num_to_add)
5459  {
5460  // create the new item and store it
5461  Item* pItem = player->StoreNewItem(dest, newitemid, true, Item::GenerateItemRandomPropertyId(newitemid));
5462 
5463  // was it successful? return error if not
5464  if (!pItem)
5465  {
5466  if (reportError)
5467  player->SendEquipError(EQUIP_ERR_ITEM_NOT_FOUND, nullptr, nullptr);
5468  return false;
5469  }
5470 
5471  // set the "Crafted by ..." property of the item
5472  if (pItem->GetProto()->Class != ITEM_CLASS_CONSUMABLE && pItem->GetProto()->Class != ITEM_CLASS_QUEST)
5473  pItem->SetGuidValue(ITEM_FIELD_CREATOR, player->GetObjectGuid());
5474 
5475  // send info to the client
5476  player->SendNewItem(pItem, num_to_add, true, true);
5477 
5478  // we succeeded in creating at least one item, so a levelup is possible
5479  player->UpdateCraftSkill(m_spellInfo->Id);
5480  }
5481  return true;
5482 }
5483

5580 void Spell::EffectEnergize(SpellEffectIndex eff_idx)
5581 {
5582  if (!unitTarget)
5583  return;
5584  if (!unitTarget->IsAlive())
5585  return;
5586 
5587  if (m_spellInfo->EffectMiscValue[eff_idx] < 0 || m_spellInfo->EffectMiscValue[eff_idx] >= MAX_POWERS)
5588  return;
5589 
5590  Powers power = Powers(m_spellInfo->EffectMiscValue[eff_idx]);
5591 
5592  // Some level depends spells
5593  int level_multiplier = 0;
5594  int level_diff = 0;
5595  switch (m_spellInfo->Id)
5596  {
5597  case 5530:
5598  if (m_caster->getClass() == CLASS_ROGUE) // Warrior and rogue use same spell, on rogue not supposed to give resource, WTF game devs?!
5599  return;
5600  break;
5601  case 9512: // Restore Energy
5602  level_diff = m_caster->GetLevel() - 40;
5603  level_multiplier = 2;
5604  break;
5605  case 24571: // Blood Fury
5606  level_diff = m_caster->GetLevel() - 60;
5607  level_multiplier = 10;
5608  break;
5609  case 24532: // Burst of Energy
5610  level_diff = m_caster->GetLevel() - 60;
5611  level_multiplier = 4;
5612  break;
5613  case 48542: // Revitalize (mana restore case)
5614  case 63375: // Improved Stormstrike
5615  case 68082: // Glyph of Seal of Command
5616  damage = damage * unitTarget->GetCreateMana() / 100;
5617  break;
5618  case 67487: // Mana Potion Injector
5619  case 67490: // Runic Mana Injector
5620  {
5621  if (unitTarget->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_PLAYER)
5622  {
5623  Player* player = (Player*)unitTarget;
5624  if (player->HasSkill(SKILL_ENGINEERING))
5625  damage += int32(damage * 0.25);
5626  }
5627  break;
5628  }
5629  default:
5630  break;
5631  }
5632 
5633  if (m_spellInfo->SpellFamilyName == SPELLFAMILY_POTION)
5634  {
5635  if (m_caster->HasAura(17619)) // Alchemists stone
5636  damage *= 1.4f; // increase healing by 40%
5637  }
5638 
5639  if (level_diff > 0)
5640  damage -= level_multiplier * level_diff;
5641 
5642  if (damage < 0)
5643  return;
5644 
5645  if (unitTarget->GetMaxPower(power) == 0)
5646  return;
5647 
5648  m_caster->EnergizeBySpell(unitTarget, m_spellInfo, damage, power);
5649 
5650  // Mad Alchemist's Potion
5651  if (m_spellInfo->Id == 45051)
5652  {
5653  // find elixirs on target
5654  uint32 elixir_mask = 0;
5655  Unit::SpellAuraHolderMap& Auras = unitTarget->GetSpellAuraHolderMap();
5656  for (auto& Aura : Auras)
5657  {
5658  uint32 spell_id = Aura.second->GetId();
5659  if (uint32 mask = sSpellMgr.GetSpellElixirMask(spell_id))
5660  elixir_mask |= mask;
5661  }
5662 
5663  // get available elixir mask any not active type from battle/guardian (and flask if no any)
5664  elixir_mask = (elixir_mask & ELIXIR_FLASK_MASK) ^ ELIXIR_FLASK_MASK;
5665 
5666  // get all available elixirs by mask and spell level
5667  std::vector<uint32> elixirs;
5668  SpellElixirMap const& m_spellElixirs = sSpellMgr.GetSpellElixirMap();
5669  for (const auto& m_spellElixir : m_spellElixirs)
5670  {
5671  if (m_spellElixir.second & elixir_mask)
5672  {
5673  if (m_spellElixir.second & (ELIXIR_UNSTABLE_MASK | ELIXIR_SHATTRATH_MASK))
5674  continue;
5675 
5676  SpellEntry const* spellInfo = sSpellTemplate.LookupEntry<SpellEntry>(m_spellElixir.first);
5677  if (spellInfo && (spellInfo->spellLevel < m_spellInfo->spellLevel || spellInfo->spellLevel > unitTarget->GetLevel()))
5678  continue;
5679 
5680  elixirs.push_back(m_spellElixir.first);
5681  }
5682  }
5683 
5684  if (!elixirs.empty())
5685  {
5686  // cast random elixir on target
5687  uint32 rand_spell = urand(0, elixirs.size() - 1);
5688  m_caster->CastSpell(unitTarget, elixirs[rand_spell], TRIGGERED_OLD_TRIGGERED, m_CastItem);
5689  }
5690  }
5691 }
5692 
5693 void Spell::EffectEnergisePct(SpellEffectIndex eff_idx)
5694 {
5695  if (!unitTarget)
5696  return;
5697  if (!unitTarget->IsAlive())
5698  return;
5699 
5700  if (m_spellInfo->EffectMiscValue[eff_idx] < 0 || m_spellInfo->EffectMiscValue[eff_idx] >= MAX_POWERS)
5701  return;
5702 
5703  Powers power = Powers(m_spellInfo->EffectMiscValue[eff_idx]);
5704 
5705  uint32 maxPower = unitTarget->GetMaxPower(power);
5706  if (maxPower == 0)
5707  return;
5708 
5709  uint32 gain = damage * maxPower / 100;
5710  m_caster->EnergizeBySpell(unitTarget, m_spellInfo, gain, power);
5711 }
5712 
5713 void Spell::SendLoot(ObjectGuid guid, LootType loottype, LockType lockType)
5714 {
5715  switch (guid.GetHigh())
5716  {
5717  case HIGHGUID_GAMEOBJECT:
5718  {
5719  if (gameObjTarget)
5720  {
5721  switch (gameObjTarget->GetGoType())
5722  {
5723  case GAMEOBJECT_TYPE_DOOR:
5724  case GAMEOBJECT_TYPE_BUTTON:
5725  case GAMEOBJECT_TYPE_QUESTGIVER:
5726  case GAMEOBJECT_TYPE_SPELL_FOCUS:
5727  case GAMEOBJECT_TYPE_GOOBER:
5728  case GAMEOBJECT_TYPE_FLAGSTAND:
5729  gameObjTarget->Use(m_caster);
5730  return;
5731 
5732  case GAMEOBJECT_TYPE_CHEST:
5733  gameObjTarget->Use(m_caster);
5734  // Don't return, let loots been taken
5735  break;
5736 
5737  case GAMEOBJECT_TYPE_TRAP:
5738  switch (lockType)
5739  {
5740  case LOCKTYPE_NONE:
5741  case LOCKTYPE_DISARM_TRAP:
5742  case LOCKTYPE_OPEN_ATTACKING:
5743  gameObjTarget->SetLootState(GO_ACTIVATED);
5744  return;
5745  default:
5746  sLog.outError("Spell::SendLoot unhandled locktype %u for GameObject trap (entry %u) for spell %u.", lockType, gameObjTarget->GetEntry(), m_spellInfo->Id);
5747  return;
5748  }
5749  default:
5750  sLog.outError("Spell::SendLoot unhandled GameObject type %u (entry %u) for spell %u.", gameObjTarget->GetGoType(), gameObjTarget->GetEntry(), m_spellInfo->Id);
5751  return;
5752  }
5753 
5754  if (m_caster->GetTypeId() != TYPEID_PLAYER)
5755  return;
5756 
5757  Loot*& loot = gameObjTarget->m_loot;
5758  if (!loot)
5759  {
5760  loot = new Loot((Player*)m_caster, gameObjTarget, loottype);
5761  TakeCastItem();
5762  }
5763  loot->ShowContentTo((Player*)m_caster);
5764  }
5765  break;
5766  }
5767 
5768  case HIGHGUID_ITEM:
5769  {
5770  if (itemTarget)
5771  {
5772  Loot*& loot = itemTarget->m_loot;
5773  if (!loot)
5774  {
5775  loot = new Loot((Player*)m_caster, itemTarget, loottype);
5776  TakeCastItem();
5777  }
5778  loot->ShowContentTo((Player*)m_caster);
5779  }
5780 
5781  break;
5782  }
5783  default:
5784  sLog.outError("Spell::SendLoot unhandled Object type %s for spell %u.", guid.GetString().c_str(), m_spellInfo->Id);
5785  break;
5786  }
5787 }
5788 
5789 void Spell::EffectOpenLock(SpellEffectIndex eff_idx)
5790 {
5791  if (!m_caster || m_caster->GetTypeId() != TYPEID_PLAYER)
5792  {
5793  DEBUG_LOG("WORLD: Open Lock - No Player Caster!");
5794  return;
5795  }
5796 
5797  Player* player = (Player*)m_caster;
5798 
5799  uint32 lockId;
5800 
5801  // Get lockId
5802  if (gameObjTarget)
5803  {
5804  lockId = gameObjTarget->GetGOInfo()->GetLockId();
5805  }
5806  else if (itemTarget)
5807  {
5808  lockId = itemTarget->GetProto()->LockID;
5809  }
5810  else
5811  {
5812  DEBUG_LOG("WORLD: Open Lock - No GameObject/Item Target!");
5813  return;
5814  }
5815 
5816  // not allow use skill grow at item base open
5817  if (!m_CastItem && m_effectSkillInfo[eff_idx].skillId != SKILL_NONE)
5818  {
5819  // update skill if really known
5820  if (uint32 pureSkillValue = player->GetSkillValuePure(m_effectSkillInfo[eff_idx].skillId))
5821  {
5822  if (gameObjTarget && !gameObjTarget->m_loot)
5823  {
5824  // Allow one skill-up until respawned
5825  if (!gameObjTarget->IsInSkillupList(player))
5826  {
5827  player->UpdateGatherSkill(m_effectSkillInfo[eff_idx].skillId, pureSkillValue, m_effectSkillInfo[eff_idx].reqSkillValue);
5828  gameObjTarget->AddToSkillupList(player);
5829  }
5830  }
5831  else if (itemTarget && !itemTarget->m_loot)
5832  {
5833  // Do one skill-up
5834  player->UpdateGatherSkill(m_effectSkillInfo[eff_idx].skillId, pureSkillValue, m_effectSkillInfo[eff_idx].reqSkillValue);
5835  }
5836  }
5837  }
5838 
5839  // mark item as unlocked
5840  if (itemTarget)
5841  {
5842  itemTarget->SetFlag(ITEM_FIELD_FLAGS, ITEM_DYNFLAG_UNLOCKED);
5843 
5844  // only send loot if owner is player, else client sends release anyway
5845  if (itemTarget->GetOwnerGuid() == m_caster->GetObjectGuid())
5846  {
5847  SendLoot(itemTarget->GetObjectGuid(), LOOT_SKINNING, LockType(m_spellInfo->EffectMiscValue[eff_idx]));
5848  m_spellLog.AddLog(uint32(SPELL_EFFECT_OPEN_LOCK), itemTarget->GetPackGUID());
5849  }
5850  }
5851  else
5852  {
5853  SendLoot(gameObjTarget->GetObjectGuid(), LOOT_SKINNING, LockType(m_spellInfo->EffectMiscValue[eff_idx]));
5854  m_spellLog.AddLog(uint32(SPELL_EFFECT_OPEN_LOCK), gameObjTarget->GetPackGUID());
5855  }
5856 }
5857 
5858 void Spell::EffectSummonChangeItem(SpellEffectIndex eff_idx)
5859 {
5860  if (m_caster->GetTypeId() != TYPEID_PLAYER)
5861  return;
5862 
5863  Player* player = (Player*)m_caster;
5864 
5865  // applied only to using item
5866  if (!m_CastItem)
5867  return;
5868 
5869  // ... only to item in own inventory/bank/equip_slot
5870  if (m_CastItem->GetOwnerGuid() != player->GetObjectGuid())
5871  return;
5872 
5873  uint32 newitemid = m_spellInfo->EffectItemType[eff_idx];
5874  if (!newitemid)
5875  return;
5876 
5877  Item* oldItem = m_CastItem;
5878 
5879  if (m_CastItem)
5880  m_CastItem->SetUsedInSpell(false);
5881  // prevent crash at access and unexpected charges counting with item update queue corrupt
5882  ClearCastItem();
5883 
5884  uint32 curItemCount = player->GetItemCount(newitemid, true);
5885 
5886  if (Item* newItem = player->ConvertItem(oldItem, newitemid))
5887  {
5888  player->ItemAddedQuestCheck(newItem->GetEntry(), newItem->GetCount());
5889 
5890  // Push packet to client so it knows we've created an item and quest can show objective update
5891  player->SendNewItem(newItem, newItem->GetCount() - curItemCount, true, false);
5892  }
5893 }

5895 void Spell::EffectProficiency(SpellEffectIndex /*eff_idx*/)
5896 {
5897  if (m_caster->GetTypeId() != TYPEID_PLAYER)
5898  return;
5899  Player* player = static_cast<Player*>(m_caster);
5900 
5901  uint32 subClassMask = m_spellInfo->EquippedItemSubClassMask;
5902  if (m_spellInfo->EquippedItemClass == ITEM_CLASS_WEAPON && !(player->GetWeaponProficiency() & subClassMask))
5903  {
5904  player->AddWeaponProficiency(subClassMask);
5905  player->SendProficiency(ITEM_CLASS_WEAPON, player->GetWeaponProficiency());
5906  }
5907  if (m_spellInfo->EquippedItemClass == ITEM_CLASS_ARMOR && !(player->GetArmorProficiency() & subClassMask))
5908  {
5909  player->AddArmorProficiency(subClassMask);
5910  player->SendProficiency(ITEM_CLASS_ARMOR, player->GetArmorProficiency());
5911  }
5912 }

5925 void Spell::EffectSummonType(SpellEffectIndex eff_idx)
5926 {
5927  uint32 prop_id = m_spellInfo->EffectMiscValueB[eff_idx];
5928  SummonPropertiesEntry const* summon_prop = sSummonPropertiesStore.LookupEntry(prop_id);
5929  if (!summon_prop)
5930  {
5931  sLog.outError("EffectSummonType: Unhandled summon type %u", prop_id);
5932  return;
5933  }
5934 
5935  // Get casting object
5936  WorldObject* realCaster = GetCastingObject();
5937  if (!realCaster)
5938  {
5939  sLog.outError("EffectSummonType: No Casting Object found for spell %u, (caster = %s)", m_spellInfo->Id, m_trueCaster->GetGuidStr().c_str());
5940  return;
5941  }
5942 
5943  Unit* responsibleCaster = m_originalCaster;
5944  if (realCaster->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_GAMEOBJECT)
5945  responsibleCaster = ((GameObject*)realCaster)->GetOwner();
5946 
5947  // Expected Amount: TODO - there are quite some exceptions (like totems, engineering dragonlings..)
5948  uint32 amount = 1;
5949  uint32 health = 0; // totems have HP in base points
5950  uint32 unk = 0; // no idea what it means, but 4000-25000 cant be right for summon count
5951  uint32 creatureLevel = 0;
5952  if (prop_id == 121 || summon_prop->Title == UNITNAME_SUMMON_TITLE_TOTEM)
5953  {
5954  health = damage;
5955  }
5956  else
5957  {
5958  switch (summon_prop->Group)
5959  {
5960  case SUMMON_PROP_GROUP_CONTROLLABLE:
5961  unk = damage;
5962  break;
5963  default:
5964  if (m_spellInfo->Id == 18662 || m_spellInfo->Id == 1122)
5965  creatureLevel = damage;
5966  else
5967  amount = damage > 0 ? damage : 1; // old code
5968  break;
5969  }
5970  }
5971 
5972  // basepoints of SUMMON_PROP_GROUP_VEHICLE is often a spellId, set amount to 1
5973  if (summon_prop->Group == SUMMON_PROP_GROUP_VEHICLE || summon_prop->Group == SUMMON_PROP_GROUP_UNCONTROLLABLE_VEHICLE || summon_prop->Group == SUMMON_PROP_GROUP_CONTROLLABLE)
5974  amount = 1;
5975 
5976  // basepoints of summoned critters are unk - set amount to 1
5977  if (summon_prop->Slot == SUMMON_PROP_SLOT_CRITTER)
5978  amount = 1;
5979 
5980  if (m_CastItem)
5981  {
5982  ItemPrototype const* proto = m_CastItem->GetProto();
5983  if (proto && proto->RequiredSkill == SKILL_ENGINEERING && proto->InventoryType == INVTYPE_TRINKET)
5984  amount = 1;
5985  }
5986 
5987  // Expected Level
5988  WorldObject* petInvoker = responsibleCaster ? responsibleCaster : m_trueCaster;
5989  uint32 level = 0;
5990  // Everything considered as guardian or critter pets uses its creature template level by default (may change depending on SpellEffect params)
5991  if (summon_prop->Title == UNITNAME_SUMMON_TITLE_COMPANION || m_ignoreOwnerLevel || summon_prop->Flags & SUMMON_PROP_FLAG_USE_CREATURE_LEVEL)
5992  {
5993  if (CreatureInfo const* cInfo = ObjectMgr::GetCreatureTemplate(m_spellInfo->EffectMiscValue[eff_idx]))
5994  level = urand(cInfo->MinLevel, cInfo->MaxLevel);
5995  else
5996  {
5997  sLog.outError("Spell Effect EFFECT_SUMMON (%u) - no creature template found for summoned NPC %u (spell id %u, effIndex %u)", m_spellInfo->Effect[eff_idx], m_spellInfo->EffectMiscValue[eff_idx], m_spellInfo->Id, eff_idx);
5998  return;
5999  }
6000  }
6001  else // Use invoker level in all other cases (to be confirmed)
6002  {
6003  if (CreatureInfo const* cInfo = ObjectMgr::GetCreatureTemplate(m_spellInfo->EffectMiscValue[eff_idx]))
6004  level = std::max(std::min(petInvoker->GetLevel(), cInfo->MaxLevel), cInfo->MinLevel);
6005  else
6006  {
6007  sLog.outError("Spell Effect EFFECT_SUMMON (%u) - no creature template found for summoned NPC %u (spell id %u, effIndex %u)", m_spellInfo->Effect[eff_idx], m_spellInfo->EffectMiscValue[eff_idx], m_spellInfo->Id, eff_idx);
6008  return;
6009  }
6010  }
6011 
6012  if (!petInvoker->IsPlayer())
6013  {
6014  // If EffectMultipleValue <= 0, pets have their calculated level modified by EffectMultipleValue
6015  if (m_spellInfo->EffectMultipleValue[eff_idx] <= 0) // TODO: Check if instead of using level variable, should not use 0 in this check
6016  {
6017  uint32 resultLevel = std::max(level + m_spellInfo->EffectMultipleValue[eff_idx], 0.0f);
6018 
6019  // Result level should be a valid level for creatures
6020  if (resultLevel > 0 && resultLevel <= DEFAULT_MAX_CREATURE_LEVEL)
6021  level = resultLevel;
6022  }
6023  }
6024  // engineering trinkets do not scale with skill in wotlk
6025 
6026  CreatureSummonPositions summonPositions;
6027  summonPositions.resize(amount, CreaturePosition());
6028 
6029  // Set middle position
6030  if (m_targets.m_targetMask & TARGET_FLAG_DEST_LOCATION)
6031  m_targets.getDestination(summonPositions[0].x, summonPositions[0].y, summonPositions[0].z);
6032  else
6033  {
6034  realCaster->GetPosition(summonPositions[0].x, summonPositions[0].y, summonPositions[0].z);
6035  // TODO - Is this really an error?
6036  sLog.outDebug("Spell Effect EFFECT_SUMMON (%u) - summon without destination (spell id %u, effIndex %u)", m_spellInfo->Effect[eff_idx], m_spellInfo->Id, eff_idx);
6037  }
6038 
6039  // Set summon positions
6040  float radius = GetSpellRadius(sSpellRadiusStore.LookupEntry(m_spellInfo->EffectRadiusIndex[eff_idx]));
6041  CreatureSummonPositions::iterator itr = summonPositions.begin();
6042  for (++itr; itr != summonPositions.end(); ++itr) // In case of multiple summons around position for not-fist positions
6043  {
6044  if (m_targets.m_targetMask & TARGET_FLAG_DEST_LOCATION || radius > 1.0f)
6045  {
6046  realCaster->GetRandomPoint(summonPositions[0].x, summonPositions[0].y, summonPositions[0].z, radius, itr->x, itr->y, itr->z);
6047  if (realCaster->GetMap()->GetHitPosition(summonPositions[0].x, summonPositions[0].y, summonPositions[0].z, itr->x, itr->y, itr->z, m_caster->GetPhaseMask(), -0.5f))
6048  realCaster->UpdateAllowedPositionZ(itr->x, itr->y, itr->z);
6049  }
6050  else // Get a point near the caster
6051  {
6052  realCaster->GetClosePoint(itr->x, itr->y, itr->z, 0.0f, radius, frand(0.0f, 2 * M_PI_F));
6053  if (realCaster->GetMap()->GetHitPosition(summonPositions[0].x, summonPositions[0].y, summonPositions[0].z, itr->x, itr->y, itr->z, m_caster->GetPhaseMask(), -0.5f))
6054  realCaster->UpdateAllowedPositionZ(itr->x, itr->y, itr->z);
6055  }
6056  }
6057 
6058  bool summonResult = false;
6059  switch (summon_prop->Group)
6060  {
6061  // faction handled later on, or loaded from template
6062  case SUMMON_PROP_GROUP_WILD:
6063  case SUMMON_PROP_GROUP_FRIENDLY:
6064  {
6065  switch (summon_prop->Title) // better from known way sorting summons by AI types
6066  {
6067  case UNITNAME_SUMMON_TITLE_NONE:
6068  {
6069  // those are classical totems - effectbasepoints is their hp and not summon ammount!
6070  // 121: 23035, battlestands
6071  // 647: 52893, Anti-Magic Zone (npc used)
6072  if (prop_id == 121 || prop_id == 647)
6073  summonResult = DoSummonTotem(summonPositions, eff_idx);
6074  else
6075  {
6076  switch (m_spellInfo->Id) // unable to distinguish based on prop_id, therefore spell by spell override
6077  {
6078  case 38544: // summon marmot, gives control of marmot pet
6079  summonResult = DoSummonPossessed(summonPositions, summon_prop, eff_idx, level);
6080  break;
6081  default:
6082  summonResult = DoSummonWild(summonPositions, summon_prop, eff_idx, level);
6083  break;
6084  }
6085  }
6086  break;
6087  }
6088  case UNITNAME_SUMMON_TITLE_PET:
6089  case UNITNAME_SUMMON_TITLE_MINION:
6090  case UNITNAME_SUMMON_TITLE_RUNEBLADE:
6091  summonResult = DoSummonGuardian(summonPositions, summon_prop, eff_idx, level);
6092  break;
6093  case UNITNAME_SUMMON_TITLE_GUARDIAN:
6094  {
6095  if (prop_id == 61)
6096  {
6097  // Totem cases
6098  if (CreatureInfo const* cInfo = ObjectMgr::GetCreatureTemplate(m_spellInfo->EffectMiscValue[eff_idx]))
6099  {
6100  if (cInfo->CreatureType == CREATURE_TYPE_TOTEM)
6101  {
6102  summonResult = DoSummonTotem(summonPositions, eff_idx);
6103  break;
6104  }
6105  }
6106  else
6107  return;
6108  }
6109 
6110  summonResult = DoSummonGuardian(summonPositions, summon_prop, eff_idx, level);
6111  break;
6112  }
6113  case UNITNAME_SUMMON_TITLE_CONSTRUCT:
6114  {
6115  if (prop_id == 2913) // Scrapbot
6116  summonResult = DoSummonWild(summonPositions, summon_prop, eff_idx, level);
6117  else
6118  summonResult = DoSummonGuardian(summonPositions, summon_prop, eff_idx, level);
6119  break;
6120  }
6121  case UNITNAME_SUMMON_TITLE_TOTEM:
6122  summonResult = DoSummonTotem(summonPositions, eff_idx, summon_prop->Slot);
6123  break;
6124  case UNITNAME_SUMMON_TITLE_COMPANION:
6125  // slot 6 set for critters that can help to player in fighting
6126  if (summon_prop->Slot == SUMMON_PROP_SLOT_QUEST_PLAYERS_ONLY)
6127  summonResult = DoSummonGuardian(summonPositions, summon_prop, eff_idx, level);
6128  else
6129  summonResult = DoSummonCritter(summonPositions, summon_prop, eff_idx, level);
6130  break;
6131  case UNITNAME_SUMMON_TITLE_OPPONENT:
6132  case UNITNAME_SUMMON_TITLE_VEHICLE:
6133  case UNITNAME_SUMMON_TITLE_MOUNT:
6134  case UNITNAME_SUMMON_TITLE_LIGHTWELL:
6135  case UNITNAME_SUMMON_TITLE_BUTLER:
6136  summonResult = DoSummonWild(summonPositions, summon_prop, eff_idx, level);
6137  break;
6138  default:
6139  sLog.outError("EffectSummonType: Unhandled summon title %u", summon_prop->Title);
6140  break;
6141  }
6142  break;
6143  }
6144  case SUMMON_PROP_GROUP_PETS:
6145  {
6146  summonResult = DoSummonGuardian(summonPositions, summon_prop, eff_idx, level);
6147  break;
6148  }
6149  case SUMMON_PROP_GROUP_CONTROLLABLE:
6150  {
6151  summonResult = DoSummonPossessed(summonPositions, summon_prop, eff_idx, level);
6152  break;
6153  }
6154  case SUMMON_PROP_GROUP_VEHICLE:
6155  case SUMMON_PROP_GROUP_UNCONTROLLABLE_VEHICLE:
6156  {
6157  summonResult = DoSummonVehicle(summonPositions, summon_prop, eff_idx, level);
6158  break;
6159  }
6160  default:
6161  sLog.outError("EffectSummonType: Unhandled summon group type %u", summon_prop->Group);
6162  break;
6163  }
6164 
6165  if (!summonResult)
6166  return; // No further handling required
6167 
6168  Creature* caster = nullptr;
6169  if (m_originalCaster)
6170  {
6171  if (m_originalCaster->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_UNIT)
6172  caster = static_cast<Creature*>(m_originalCaster);
6173  }
6174  else if (m_trueCaster && m_trueCaster->IsCreature())
6175  caster = static_cast<Creature*>(m_trueCaster);
6176 
6177  for (itr = summonPositions.begin(); itr != summonPositions.end(); ++itr)
6178  {
6179  Creature* creature = itr->creature;
6180  MANGOS_ASSERT(creature || itr != summonPositions.begin());
6181  if (!creature)
6182  {
6183  sLog.outError("EffectSummonType: Expected to have %u NPCs summoned, but some failed (Spell id %u)", amount, m_spellInfo->Id);
6184  continue;
6185  }
6186 
6187  if (summon_prop->FactionId)
6188  creature->setFaction(summon_prop->FactionId);
6189  // Else set faction to summoner's faction for pet-like summoned
6190  else if ((summon_prop->Flags & SUMMON_PROP_FLAG_USE_SUMMONER_FACTION) || !creature->IsTemporarySummon())
6191  creature->setFaction(petInvoker->GetFaction());
6192 
6193  if (summon_prop->Flags & SUMMON_PROP_FLAG_JOIN_SUMMONERS_SPAWN_GROUP && petInvoker->IsControlledByPlayer())
6194  {
6195  creature->SetFlag(UNIT_FIELD_FLAGS, UNIT_FLAG_PLAYER_CONTROLLED);
6196  creature->setFaction(petInvoker->GetFaction());
6197  }
6198 
6199  if (!itr->processed)
6200  {
6201  m_trueCaster->GetMap()->Add(itr->creature);
6202 
6203  creature->AIM_Initialize();
6204 
6205  // Notify original caster if not done already
6206  if (caster && caster->AI())
6207  caster->AI()->JustSummoned(itr->creature);
6208  }
6209  else if (m_originalCaster && m_originalCaster != m_trueCaster && m_originalCaster->AI())
6210  {
6211  // original caster is provided by script so we have to notify it as its not done in Object::SummonCreature
6212  m_originalCaster->AI()->JustSummoned(itr->creature);
6213  }
6214 
6215  OnSummon(creature);
6216 
6217  m_spellLog.AddLog(uint32(SPELL_EFFECT_SUMMON), creature->GetPackGUID());
6218 
6219  if (summon_prop->Flags & SUMMON_PROP_FLAG_ATTACK_SUMMONER && m_caster)
6220  if (m_caster->CanEnterCombat() && creature->CanEnterCombat() && creature->CanAttack(m_caster))
6221  creature->AI()->AttackStart(m_caster);
6222 
6223  if (summon_prop->Flags & SUMMON_PROP_FLAG_HELP_WHEN_SUMMONED_IN_COMBAT && m_caster)
6224  {
6225  if (m_caster->CanEnterCombat() && creature->CanEnterCombat() && creature->CanAssist(m_caster))
6226  {
6227  if (!m_caster->CanHaveThreatList())
6228  {
6229  for (auto& ref : m_caster->getHostileRefManager())
6230  if (Unit* victim = ref.getSource()->getOwner())
6231  if (creature->CanAttack(victim))
6232  creature->AddThreat(victim);
6233  }
6234  else
6235  {
6236  for (auto ref : m_caster->getThreatManager().getThreatList())
6237  if (Unit* victim = ref->getTarget())
6238  if (creature->CanAttack(victim))
6239  creature->AddThreat(victim);
6240  }
6241 
6242  if (!creature->getThreatManager().isThreatListEmpty())
6243  creature->AI()->AttackClosestEnemy();
6244  }
6245  }
6246 
6247  if (summon_prop->Flags & SUMMON_PROP_FLAG_ONLY_VISIBLE_TO_SUMMONER)
6248  creature->SetOnlyVisibleTo(m_trueCaster->GetObjectGuid());
6249 
6250  if (summon_prop->Flags & SUMMON_PROP_FLAG_CANNOT_DISMISS_PET && creature->IsPet())
6251  static_cast<Pet*>(creature)->SetDismissDisabled();
6252  }
6253 }

6255 bool Spell::DoSummonWild(CreatureSummonPositions& list, SummonPropertiesEntry const* prop, SpellEffectIndex effIdx, uint32 level)
6256 {
6257  MANGOS_ASSERT(!list.empty() && prop);
6258 
6259  uint32 creature_entry = m_spellInfo->EffectMiscValue[effIdx];
6260  CreatureInfo const* cInfo = ObjectMgr::GetCreatureTemplate(creature_entry);
6261  if (!cInfo)
6262  {
6263  sLog.outErrorDb("Spell::DoSummonWild: creature entry %u not found for spell %u.", creature_entry, m_spellInfo->Id);
6264  return false;
6265  }
6266 
6267  TempSpawnType summonType = (m_duration == 0) ? TEMPSPAWN_DEAD_DESPAWN : TEMPSPAWN_TIMED_OR_DEAD_DESPAWN;
6268 
6269  uint32 phaseMask = m_trueCaster->GetPhaseMask();
6270  if (prop->Flags & SUMMON_PROP_FLAG_IGNORE_SUMMONERS_PHASE)
6271  phaseMask = GetPhaseMaskOverride();
6272 
6273  Unit* summonInvoker = m_caster;
6274  if (m_trueCaster->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_GAMEOBJECT)
6275  summonInvoker = static_cast<GameObject*>(m_trueCaster)->GetOwner();
6276 
6277  for (auto& itr : list)
6278  if (Creature* summon = WorldObject::SummonCreature(TempSpawnSettings(m_trueCaster, creature_entry, itr.x, itr.y, itr.z, m_trueCaster->GetOrientation(), summonType, m_duration, false,
6279  IsSpellSetRun(m_spellInfo), 0, 0, 0, false, false, m_spellInfo->Id, -1, level), m_trueCaster->GetMap(), phaseMask))
6280  {
6281  itr.creature = summon;
6282  itr.processed = true;
6283 
6284  switch(m_spellInfo->Id)
6285  {
6286  case 1122: // Warlock Infernal - requires custom code - generalized in WOTLK
6287  {
6288  // Enslave demon effect, without mana cost and cooldown
6289  summon->CastSpell(nullptr, 22707, TRIGGERED_OLD_TRIGGERED); // short root spell on infernal from sniffs
6290  m_caster->CastSpell(summon, 20882, TRIGGERED_OLD_TRIGGERED);
6291  summon->AI()->DoCastSpellIfCan(nullptr, 19483, CAST_TRIGGERED | CAST_AURA_NOT_PRESENT);
6292  summon->CastSpell(nullptr, 22764, TRIGGERED_NONE); // aggro spell
6293  break;
6294  }
6295  }
6296 
6297  if (prop->Group == SUMMON_PROP_GROUP_FRIENDLY && summonInvoker) // for example 54359
6298  {
6299  if (summonInvoker->IsPlayerControlled())
6300  summon->SetFlag(UNIT_FIELD_FLAGS, UNIT_FLAG_PLAYER_CONTROLLED);
6301 
6302  summon->setFaction(summonInvoker->GetFaction());
6303  summon->SetOwnerGuid(summonInvoker->GetObjectGuid());
6304  }
6305  }
6306  else
6307  return false;
6308 
6309  return true;
6310 }

6312 bool Spell::DoSummonCritter(CreatureSummonPositions& list, SummonPropertiesEntry const* prop, SpellEffectIndex effIdx, uint32 /*level*/)
6313 {
6314  MANGOS_ASSERT(!list.empty() && prop);
6315 
6316  // ATM only first position is supported for summoning
6317  uint32 pet_entry = m_spellInfo->EffectMiscValue[effIdx];
6318  CreatureInfo const* cInfo = ObjectMgr::GetCreatureTemplate(pet_entry);
6319  if (!cInfo)
6320  {
6321  sLog.outErrorDb("Spell::DoSummonCritter: creature entry %u not found for spell %u.", pet_entry, m_spellInfo->Id);
6322  return false;
6323  }
6324 
6325  Pet* old_critter = m_caster->GetMiniPet();
6326 
6327  // for same pet just despawn (player unsummon command)
6328  if (m_caster->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_PLAYER && old_critter && old_critter->GetEntry() == pet_entry)
6329  {
6330  m_caster->RemoveMiniPet();
6331  return false;
6332  }
6333 
6334  // despawn old pet before summon new
6335  if (old_critter)
6336  m_caster->RemoveMiniPet();
6337 
6338  // for (CreatureSummonPositions::iterator itr = list.begin(); itr != list.end(); ++itr)
6339  CreatureCreatePos pos(m_caster->GetMap(), list[0].x, list[0].y, list[0].z, m_caster->GetOrientation(), m_caster->GetPhaseMask());
6340 
6341  // summon new pet
6342  Pet* critter = new Pet(MINI_PET);
6343 
6344 
6345  if (!critter->Create(m_caster->GetMap()->GenerateLocalLowGuid(HIGHGUID_PET), pos, cInfo, pet_entry))
6346  {
6347  sLog.outError("Spell::EffectSummonCritter, spellid %u: no such creature entry %u", m_spellInfo->Id, pet_entry);
6348  delete critter;
6349  return false;
6350  }
6351 
6352  critter->SetLoading(true);
6353 
6354  // itr!
6355  list[0].creature = critter;
6356 
6357  critter->SetRespawnCoord(pos);
6358 
6359  // critter->SetName(""); // generated by client
6360  critter->SetOwnerGuid(m_caster->GetObjectGuid());
6361  critter->setFaction(m_caster->GetFaction());
6362  critter->SetUInt32Value(UNIT_CREATED_BY_SPELL, m_spellInfo->Id);
6363  critter->SelectLevel(); // some summoned critters have different from 1 DB data for level/hp
6364  const CreatureInfo* info = critter->GetCreatureInfo();
6365  // Some companions have additional UNIT_FLAG_SPAWNING (0x2), perphaps coming from template, so add template flags
6366  critter->SetUInt32Value(UNIT_FIELD_FLAGS, info->UnitFlags);
6367  critter->SetUInt32Value(UNIT_NPC_FLAGS, info->NpcFlags);// some companions may have quests, so they need npc flags
6368  critter->InitPetCreateSpells(); // some companions may have spells (e.g. disgusting oozeling)
6369  if (m_duration > 0) // set timer for unsummon
6370  critter->SetDuration(m_duration);
6371 
6372  m_caster->SetMiniPet(critter);
6373 
6374  if (m_caster->HasFlag(UNIT_FIELD_FLAGS, UNIT_FLAG_PLAYER_CONTROLLED))
6375  critter->SetFlag(UNIT_FIELD_FLAGS, UNIT_FLAG_PLAYER_CONTROLLED);
6376 
6377  // NOTE: All companions should have these (creatureinfo needs to be tuned accordingly before we can remove these two lines):
6378  critter->SetImmuneToNPC(true);
6379  critter->SetImmuneToPlayer(true);
6380  critter->SetLoading(false);
6381 
6382  // NOTE: Do not set PvP flags (confirmed) for companions.
6383 
6384  critter->SetByteFlag(UNIT_FIELD_BYTES_2, 1, UNIT_BYTE2_FLAG_UNK5);
6385 
6386  return true;
6387 }
