6389 bool Spell::DoSummonGuardian(CreatureSummonPositions& list, SummonPropertiesEntry const* prop, SpellEffectIndex effIdx, uint32 level)
6390 {
6391  MANGOS_ASSERT(!list.empty() && prop);
6392 
6393  uint32 pet_entry = m_spellInfo->EffectMiscValue[effIdx];
6394  CreatureInfo const* cInfo = ObjectMgr::GetCreatureTemplate(pet_entry);
6395  if (!cInfo)
6396  {
6397  sLog.outErrorDb("Spell::DoSummonGuardian: creature entry %u not found for spell %u.", pet_entry, m_spellInfo->Id);
6398  return false;
6399  }
6400 
6401  PetType petType = prop->Title == UNITNAME_SUMMON_TITLE_COMPANION ? PROTECTOR_PET : GUARDIAN_PET;
6402 
6403  // second direct cast unsummon guardian(s) (guardians without like functionality have cooldown > spawn time)
6404  if (!m_IsTriggeredSpell && m_caster->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_PLAYER && (prop->Flags & SUMMON_PROP_FLAG_DO_NOT_TOGGLE) == 0)
6405  {
6406  bool found = false;
6407  // including protector
6408  while (Pet* old_summon = m_caster->FindGuardianWithEntry(pet_entry))
6409  {
6410  old_summon->Unsummon(PET_SAVE_AS_DELETED, m_caster);
6411  found = true;
6412  }
6413 
6414  if (found && !(m_spellInfo->DurationIndex && m_spellInfo->Category))
6415  return false;
6416  }
6417 
6418  // protectors allowed only in single amount
6419  if (petType == PROTECTOR_PET)
6420  if (Pet* old_protector = m_caster->GetProtectorPet())
6421  old_protector->Unsummon(PET_SAVE_AS_DELETED, m_caster);
6422 
6423  bool initCharm = false;
6424 
6425  // in another case summon new
6426  for (auto& itr : list)
6427  {
6428  Pet* spawnCreature = new Pet(petType);
6429 
6430  CreatureCreatePos pos(m_caster->GetMap(), itr.x, itr.y, itr.z, -m_caster->GetOrientation(), m_caster->GetPhaseMask());
6431 
6432  uint32 pet_number = sObjectMgr.GeneratePetNumber();
6433  if (!spawnCreature->Create(m_caster->GetMap()->GenerateLocalLowGuid(HIGHGUID_PET), pos, cInfo, pet_entry))
6434  {
6435  sLog.outError("Spell::DoSummonGuardian: can't create creature entry %u for spell %u.", pet_entry, m_spellInfo->Id);
6436  delete spawnCreature;
6437  return false;
6438  }
6439 
6440  spawnCreature->SetLoading(true);
6441 
6442  itr.creature = spawnCreature;
6443 
6444  spawnCreature->SetRespawnCoord(pos);
6445 
6446  if (m_duration > 0)
6447  spawnCreature->SetDuration(m_duration);
6448 
6449  CreatureInfo const* cInfo2 = spawnCreature->GetCreatureInfo();
6450 
6451  // spawnCreature->SetName(""); // generated by client
6452  spawnCreature->SetOwnerGuid(m_caster->GetObjectGuid());
6453  spawnCreature->SetUInt32Value(UNIT_FIELD_FLAGS, cInfo2->UnitFlags);
6454  spawnCreature->SetUInt32Value(UNIT_NPC_FLAGS, cInfo2->NpcFlags);
6455  spawnCreature->setFaction(m_caster->GetFaction());
6456  spawnCreature->SetUInt32Value(UNIT_FIELD_PET_NAME_TIMESTAMP, 0);
6457  spawnCreature->SetUInt32Value(UNIT_CREATED_BY_SPELL, m_spellInfo->Id);
6458 
6459  spawnCreature->SetCanModifyStats(true);
6460  spawnCreature->InitStatsForLevel(level);
6461 
6462  if (m_caster->HasFlag(UNIT_FIELD_FLAGS, UNIT_FLAG_PLAYER_CONTROLLED))
6463  spawnCreature->SetFlag(UNIT_FIELD_FLAGS, UNIT_FLAG_PLAYER_CONTROLLED);
6464 
6465  if (m_caster->IsImmuneToNPC())
6466  spawnCreature->SetImmuneToNPC(true);
6467 
6468  if (m_caster->IsImmuneToPlayer())
6469  spawnCreature->SetImmuneToPlayer(true);
6470 
6471  if (m_caster->IsPvP())
6472  spawnCreature->SetPvP(true);
6473 
6474  if (m_caster->IsPvPFreeForAll())
6475  spawnCreature->SetPvPFreeForAll(true);
6476 
6477  if (m_caster->IsPvPSanctuary())
6478  spawnCreature->SetPvPSanctuary(true);
6479 
6480  // must be before controllable guardian block
6481  if (CharmInfo* charmInfo = spawnCreature->GetCharmInfo())
6482  charmInfo->SetPetNumber(pet_number, false);
6483 
6484  if (prop->Group == SUMMON_PROP_GROUP_PETS || prop->Title == UNITNAME_SUMMON_TITLE_PET)
6485  {
6486  // controllable guardians
6487  spawnCreature->SetControllableGuardian();
6488  if (spawnCreature->GetCreatureInfo()->SpellList)
6489  spawnCreature->SetSpellList(cInfo->SpellList);
6490  else // legacy compatibility
6491  spawnCreature->SetSpellList(cInfo->Entry * 100 + 0);
6492 
6493  spawnCreature->InitializeSpellsForControllableGuardian(prop->Flags & SUMMON_PROP_FLAG_SAVE_PET_AUTOCAST);
6494 
6495  m_caster->SetPet(spawnCreature); // last guardian will be left in field
6496  spawnCreature->SetOwnerGuid(m_caster->GetObjectGuid());
6497 
6498  initCharm = true;
6499  }
6500 
6501  if (prop->Flags & SUMMON_PROP_FLAG_DO_NOT_FOLLOW_MOUNTED_SUMMONER)
6502  spawnCreature->SetNoMountedFollow();
6503 
6504  spawnCreature->SetLoading(false);
6505  m_caster->AddGuardian(spawnCreature);
6506 
6507  spawnCreature->SetByteFlag(UNIT_FIELD_BYTES_2, 1, UNIT_BYTE2_FLAG_UNK5);
6508 
6509  m_caster->GetMap()->Add(static_cast<Creature*>(spawnCreature));
6510 
6511  spawnCreature->AIM_Initialize();
6512 
6513  itr.processed = true;
6514  }
6515 
6516  if (initCharm && m_caster->IsPlayer())
6517  static_cast<Player*>(m_caster)->PetSpellInitialize();
6518 
6519  return true;
6520 }

6522 bool Spell::DoSummonTotem(CreatureSummonPositions& list, SpellEffectIndex eff_idx, uint8 slot_dbc)
6523 {
6524  // DBC store slots starting from 1, with no slot 0 value)
6525  int slot = slot_dbc ? slot_dbc - 1 : TOTEM_SLOT_NONE;
6526 
6527  // unsummon old totem
6528  if (slot < MAX_TOTEM_SLOT)
6529  if (Totem* OldTotem = m_caster->GetTotem(TotemSlot(slot)))
6530  OldTotem->UnSummon();
6531 
6532  // FIXME: Setup near to finish point because GetObjectBoundingRadius set in Create but some Create calls can be dependent from proper position
6533  // if totem have creature_template_addon.auras with persistent point for example or script call
6534 
6535  CreatureCreatePos pos(m_caster->GetMap(), list[0].x, list[0].y, list[0].z, m_caster->GetOrientation(), m_caster->GetPhaseMask());
6536 
6537  CreatureInfo const* cinfo = ObjectMgr::GetCreatureTemplate(m_spellInfo->EffectMiscValue[eff_idx]);
6538  if (!cinfo)
6539  {
6540  sLog.outErrorDb("Creature entry %u does not exist but used in spell %u totem summon.", m_spellInfo->Id, m_spellInfo->EffectMiscValue[eff_idx]);
6541  return false;
6542  }
6543 
6544  Totem* pTotem = new Totem;
6545  list[0].creature = pTotem;
6546 
6547  if (!pTotem->Create(m_caster->GetMap()->GenerateLocalLowGuid(HIGHGUID_UNIT), pos, cinfo, m_caster))
6548  {
6549  delete pTotem;
6550  return false;
6551  }
6552 
6553  pTotem->SetRespawnCoord(pos);
6554 
6555  if (slot < MAX_TOTEM_SLOT)
6556  m_caster->_AddTotem(TotemSlot(slot), pTotem);
6557 
6558  // pTotem->SetName(""); // generated by client
6559  pTotem->SetOwnerGuid(m_caster->GetObjectGuid());
6560  pTotem->setFaction(m_caster->GetFaction());
6561  pTotem->SetLevel(m_caster->GetLevel());
6562  pTotem->SetTypeBySummonSpell(m_spellInfo); // must be after Create call where m_spells initialized
6563 
6564  pTotem->SetDuration(m_duration);
6565 
6566  if (damage) // if not spell info, DB values used
6567  {
6568  pTotem->SetMaxHealth(damage);
6569  pTotem->SetHealth(damage);
6570  }
6571 
6572  pTotem->SetUInt32Value(UNIT_CREATED_BY_SPELL, m_spellInfo->Id);
6573 
6574  if (m_caster->HasFlag(UNIT_FIELD_FLAGS, UNIT_FLAG_PLAYER_CONTROLLED))
6575  pTotem->SetFlag(UNIT_FIELD_FLAGS, UNIT_FLAG_PLAYER_CONTROLLED);
6576 
6577  if (m_caster->IsImmuneToNPC())
6578  pTotem->SetImmuneToNPC(true);
6579 
6580  if (m_caster->IsImmuneToPlayer())
6581  pTotem->SetImmuneToPlayer(true);
6582 
6583  if (m_caster->IsPvP())
6584  pTotem->SetPvP(true);
6585 
6586  if (m_caster->IsPvPFreeForAll())
6587  pTotem->SetPvPFreeForAll(true);
6588 
6589  if (m_caster->IsPvPSanctuary())
6590  pTotem->SetPvPSanctuary(true);
6591 
6592  // sending SMSG_TOTEM_CREATED before add to map (done in Summon)
6593  if (slot < MAX_TOTEM_SLOT && m_caster->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_PLAYER)
6594  {
6595  WorldPacket data(SMSG_TOTEM_CREATED, 1 + 8 + 4 + 4);
6596  data << uint8(slot);
6597  data << pTotem->GetObjectGuid();
6598  data << uint32(m_duration);
6599  data << uint32(m_spellInfo->Id);
6600  ((Player*)m_caster)->SendDirectMessage(data);
6601  }
6602 
6603  pTotem->Summon(m_caster);
6604  OnSummon(pTotem);
6605  m_spellLog.AddLog(uint32(SPELL_EFFECT_SUMMON), pTotem->GetPackGUID());
6606 
6607  return false;
6608 }

6627 bool Spell::DoSummonPet(CreatureSummonPositions& list, SummonPropertiesEntry const* prop, SpellEffectIndex effIdx)
6628 {
6629  MANGOS_ASSERT(!list.empty() && prop);
6630 
6631  if (m_caster->GetPetGuid())
6632  return false;
6633 
6634  uint32 pet_entry = m_spellInfo->EffectMiscValue[effIdx];
6635  CreatureInfo const* cInfo = ObjectMgr::GetCreatureTemplate(pet_entry);
6636  if (!cInfo)
6637  {
6638  sLog.outErrorDb("Spell::DoSummonPet: creature entry %u not found for spell %u.", pet_entry, m_spellInfo->Id);
6639  return false;
6640  }
6641 
6642  Pet* spawnCreature = new Pet();
6643 
6644  Player* _player = nullptr;
6645 
6646  Position spawnPos(list[0].x, list[0].y, list[0].z, m_caster->GetOrientation());
6647 
6648  // set timer for unsummon
6649  if (m_duration > 0)
6650  spawnCreature->SetDuration(m_duration);
6651 
6652  if (m_caster->IsPlayer())
6653  {
6654  _player = static_cast<Player*>(m_caster);
6655 
6656  if (spawnCreature->LoadPetFromDB(_player, spawnPos, pet_entry))
6657  {
6658  // Summon in dest location
6659  if (m_targets.m_targetMask & TARGET_FLAG_DEST_LOCATION)
6660  spawnCreature->Relocate(m_targets.m_destPos.x, m_targets.m_destPos.y, m_targets.m_destPos.z, -m_caster->GetOrientation());
6661  list[0].creature = spawnCreature;
6662  return true;
6663  }
6664  }
6665 
6666  spawnCreature->setPetType(SUMMON_PET);
6667 
6668  // Summon in dest location
6669  CreatureCreatePos pos(m_caster->GetMap(), spawnPos.x, spawnPos.y, spawnPos.z, -m_caster->GetOrientation(), m_caster->GetPhaseMask());
6670 
6671  if (!(m_targets.m_targetMask & TARGET_FLAG_DEST_LOCATION))
6672  pos = CreatureCreatePos(m_caster, -m_caster->GetOrientation());
6673 
6674  Map* map = m_caster->GetMap();
6675  uint32 pet_number = sObjectMgr.GeneratePetNumber();
6676  if (!spawnCreature->Create(map->GenerateLocalLowGuid(HIGHGUID_PET), pos, cInfo, pet_number))
6677  {
6678  sLog.outErrorDb("Spell::EffectSummon: can't create creature with entry %u for spell %u", cInfo->Entry, m_spellInfo->Id);
6679  delete spawnCreature;
6680  return false;
6681  }
6682 
6683  spawnCreature->SetLoading(true);
6684 
6685  // Level of pet summoned
6686  uint32 level = std::max(m_caster->GetLevel() + m_spellInfo->EffectMultipleValue[effIdx], 1.0f);
6687 
6688  spawnCreature->SetRespawnCoord(pos);
6689 
6690  spawnCreature->SetOwnerGuid(m_caster->GetObjectGuid());
6691  spawnCreature->setFaction(m_caster->GetFaction());
6692  spawnCreature->SetUInt32Value(UNIT_FIELD_PET_NAME_TIMESTAMP, 0);
6693  spawnCreature->SetUInt32Value(UNIT_CREATED_BY_SPELL, m_spellInfo->Id);
6694 
6695  spawnCreature->SetCanModifyStats(true);
6696  spawnCreature->InitStatsForLevel(level);
6697 
6698  if (CharmInfo* charmInfo = spawnCreature->GetCharmInfo())
6699  charmInfo->SetPetNumber(pet_number, (m_caster->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_PLAYER && spawnCreature->isControlled()));
6700 
6701  // spawnCreature->SetName(""); // generated by client
6702 
6703  if (m_caster->HasFlag(UNIT_FIELD_FLAGS, UNIT_FLAG_PLAYER_CONTROLLED))
6704  spawnCreature->SetFlag(UNIT_FIELD_FLAGS, UNIT_FLAG_PLAYER_CONTROLLED);
6705 
6706  m_caster->SetPet(spawnCreature);
6707 
6708  if (m_caster->IsImmuneToNPC())
6709  spawnCreature->SetImmuneToNPC(true);
6710 
6711  if (m_caster->IsImmuneToPlayer())
6712  spawnCreature->SetImmuneToPlayer(true);
6713 
6714  if (m_caster->IsPvP())
6715  spawnCreature->SetPvP(true);
6716 
6717  if (m_caster->IsPvPFreeForAll())
6718  spawnCreature->SetPvPFreeForAll(true);
6719 
6720  if (m_caster->IsPvPSanctuary())
6721  spawnCreature->SetPvPSanctuary(true);
6722 
6723  map->Add((Creature*)spawnCreature);
6724  spawnCreature->AIM_Initialize();
6725 
6726  spawnCreature->InitPetCreateSpells();
6727  spawnCreature->InitLevelupSpellsForLevel();
6728 
6729  if (_player)
6730  {
6731  spawnCreature->AI()->SetReactState(REACT_DEFENSIVE);
6732  ((Player*)m_caster)->PetSpellInitialize();
6733  if (m_caster->getClass() != CLASS_PRIEST)
6734  spawnCreature->SavePetToDB(PET_SAVE_AS_CURRENT, _player);
6735  }
6736  spawnCreature->SetLoading(false);
6737 
6738  // Notify original caster if not done already
6739  if (m_caster->AI())
6740  m_caster->AI()->JustSummoned(spawnCreature);
6741 
6742  list[0].creature = spawnCreature;
6743  list[0].processed = true;
6744  return true;
6745 }

6747 bool Spell::DoSummonVehicle(CreatureSummonPositions& list, SummonPropertiesEntry const* prop, SpellEffectIndex effIdx, uint32 /*level*/)
6748 {
6749  MANGOS_ASSERT(!list.empty() && prop);
6750 
6751  uint32 creatureEntry = m_spellInfo->EffectMiscValue[effIdx];
6752  CreatureInfo const* cInfo = ObjectMgr::GetCreatureTemplate(creatureEntry);
6753  if (!cInfo)
6754  {
6755  sLog.outErrorDb("Spell::DoSummonVehicle: creature entry %u not found for spell %u.", creatureEntry, m_spellInfo->Id);
6756  return false;
6757  }
6758 
6759  TempSpawnSettings spawnSettings(m_caster, creatureEntry, list[0].x, list[0].y, list[0].z, m_caster->GetOrientation(), (m_duration == 0) ? TEMPSPAWN_CORPSE_DESPAWN : TEMPSPAWN_TIMED_OOC_OR_CORPSE_DESPAWN, m_duration);
6760  spawnSettings.spellId = m_spellInfo->Id;
6761  spawnSettings.ownerGuid = m_caster->GetObjectGuid();
6762  if (prop->FactionId)
6763  spawnSettings.faction = prop->FactionId;
6764  Creature* spawnCreature = WorldObject::SummonCreature(spawnSettings, m_caster->GetMap(), m_caster->GetPhaseMask());
6765 
6766  if (!spawnCreature)
6767  {
6768  sLog.outError("Spell::DoSummonVehicle: creature entry %u for spell %u could not be summoned.", creatureEntry, m_spellInfo->Id);
6769  return false;
6770  }
6771 
6772  list[0].creature = spawnCreature;
6773 
6774  // Board the caster right after summoning
6775  int32 basePoints = m_spellInfo->CalculateSimpleValue(effIdx);
6776  bool executed = false;
6777  if (basePoints > MAX_VEHICLE_SEAT)
6778  {
6779  SpellEntry const* controlSpellEntry = sSpellTemplate.LookupEntry<SpellEntry>(basePoints);
6780  if (controlSpellEntry && IsSpellHaveAura(controlSpellEntry, SPELL_AURA_CONTROL_VEHICLE))
6781  {
6782  m_caster->CastSpell(spawnCreature, controlSpellEntry, TRIGGERED_OLD_TRIGGERED);
6783  executed = true;
6784  }
6785  }
6786  else
6787  {
6788  if (basePoints > 0 && basePoints < MAX_VEHICLE_SEAT)
6789  m_caster->CastCustomSpell(spawnCreature, SPELL_RIDE_VEHICLE_HARDCODED, &basePoints, nullptr, nullptr, TRIGGERED_OLD_TRIGGERED);
6790  else
6791  m_caster->CastSpell(spawnCreature, SPELL_RIDE_VEHICLE_HARDCODED, TRIGGERED_OLD_TRIGGERED);
6792  }
6793 
6794  // If the boarding failed...
6795  if (!spawnCreature->HasAuraType(SPELL_AURA_CONTROL_VEHICLE))
6796  {
6797  spawnCreature->ForcedDespawn();
6798  return false;
6799  }
6800 
6801  list[0].processed = true;
6802  return true;
6803 }

6827 void Spell::EffectDispel(SpellEffectIndex eff_idx)
6828 {
6829  if (!unitTarget)
6830  return;
6831 
6832  // Fill possible dispel list
6833  std::list <std::pair<SpellAuraHolder*, uint32> > dispelList;
6834 
6835  // Create dispel mask by dispel type
6836  uint32 dispelMask = GetDispellMask(DispelType(m_spellInfo->EffectMiscValue[eff_idx]));
6837  Unit::SpellAuraHolderMap const& auras = unitTarget->GetSpellAuraHolderMap();
6838  for (Unit::SpellAuraHolderMap::const_iterator itr = auras.begin(); itr != auras.end(); ++itr)
6839  {
6840  SpellAuraHolder* holder = itr->second;
6841 
6842  if (holder->GetSpellProto()->Id == 29448)
6843  continue;
6844 
6845  if (holder->IsDispellableByMask(dispelMask, m_caster, m_spellInfo))
6846  dispelList.push_back(std::pair<SpellAuraHolder*, uint32>(holder, holder->GetStackAmount()));
6847  }
6848  std::list<std::pair<SpellAuraHolder*, uint32> > successList;
6849  std::list <uint32> failList;
6850  ProcessDispelList(dispelList, successList, failList);
6851  EvaluateResultLists(successList, failList);
6852 }
6853 
6854 void Spell::EffectDispelMechanic(SpellEffectIndex eff_idx)
6855 {
6856  if (!unitTarget)
6857  return;
6858 
6859  uint32 mechanic = m_spellInfo->EffectMiscValue[eff_idx];
6860 
6861  // Fill possible dispel list
6862  std::list <std::pair<SpellAuraHolder*, uint32> > dispelList;
6863 
6864  Unit::SpellAuraHolderMap& Auras = unitTarget->GetSpellAuraHolderMap();
6865  for (Unit::SpellAuraHolderMap::iterator iter = Auras.begin(); iter != Auras.end(); ++iter)
6866  if (iter->second->HasMechanic(mechanic))
6867  dispelList.push_back(std::pair<SpellAuraHolder*, uint32>(iter->second, iter->second->GetStackAmount()));
6868  std::list<std::pair<SpellAuraHolder*, uint32> > successList;
6869  std::list <uint32> failList;
6870  ProcessDispelList(dispelList, successList, failList);
6871  EvaluateResultLists(successList, failList);
6872 }
6873 
6874 void Spell::ProcessDispelList(std::list <std::pair<SpellAuraHolder*, uint32> >& dispelList, std::list<std::pair<SpellAuraHolder*, uint32> >& successList, std::list <uint32>& failList)
6875 {
6876  // Ok if exist some buffs for dispel try dispel it
6877  if (!dispelList.empty())
6878  {
6879  // some spells have effect value = 0 and all from its by meaning expect 1
6880  if (!damage)
6881  damage = 1;
6882 
6883  // Dispel N = damage buffs (or while exist buffs for dispel)
6884  for (int32 count = 0; count < damage && !dispelList.empty(); ++count)
6885  {
6886  // Random select buff for dispel
6887  std::list<std::pair<SpellAuraHolder*, uint32> >::iterator dispel_itr = dispelList.begin();
6888  std::advance(dispel_itr, urand(0, dispelList.size() - 1));
6889 
6890  SpellAuraHolder* holder = dispel_itr->first;
6891 
6892  dispel_itr->second -= 1;
6893 
6894  // remove entry from dispel_list if nothing left in stack
6895  if (dispel_itr->second == 0)
6896  dispelList.erase(dispel_itr);
6897 
6898  SpellEntry const* spellInfo = holder->GetSpellProto();
6899  // Base dispel chance
6900  // TODO: possible chance depend from spell level??
6901  int32 miss_chance = 0;
6902  // Apply dispel mod from aura caster
6903  if (Unit* caster = holder->GetCaster())
6904  {
6905  if (Player* modOwner = caster->GetSpellModOwner())
6906  modOwner->ApplySpellMod(spellInfo->Id, SPELLMOD_RESIST_DISPEL_CHANCE, miss_chance);
6907  miss_chance += caster->GetTotalAuraModifier(SPELL_AURA_MOD_DISPEL_RESIST);
6908  }
6909  // Try dispel
6910  if (roll_chance_i(miss_chance))
6911  failList.push_back(spellInfo->Id);
6912  else
6913  {
6914  bool foundDispelled = false;
6915  for (std::list<std::pair<SpellAuraHolder*, uint32> >::iterator success_iter = successList.begin(); success_iter != successList.end(); ++success_iter)
6916  {
6917  if (success_iter->first->GetId() == holder->GetId() && success_iter->first->GetCasterGuid() == holder->GetCasterGuid())
6918  {
6919  success_iter->second += 1;
6920  foundDispelled = true;
6921  break;
6922  }
6923  }
6924  if (!foundDispelled)
6925  successList.push_back(std::pair<SpellAuraHolder*, uint32>(holder, 1));
6926  }
6927  }
6928  }
6929 }
6930 
6931 void Spell::EvaluateResultLists(std::list<std::pair<SpellAuraHolder*, uint32> >& successList, std::list <uint32>& failList)
6932 {
6933  // Send success log and really remove auras
6934  if (!successList.empty())
6935  {
6936  int32 count = successList.size();
6937  WorldPacket data(SMSG_SPELLDISPELLOG, 8 + 8 + 4 + 1 + 4 + count * 5);
6938  data << unitTarget->GetPackGUID(); // Victim GUID
6939  data << m_caster->GetPackGUID(); // Caster GUID
6940  data << uint32(m_spellInfo->Id); // Dispel spell id
6941  data << uint8(0); // not used
6942  data << uint32(count); // count
6943  for (std::list<std::pair<SpellAuraHolder*, uint32> >::iterator j = successList.begin(); j != successList.end(); ++j)
6944  {
6945  SpellAuraHolder* dispelledHolder = j->first;
6946  data << uint32(dispelledHolder->GetId()); // Spell Id
6947  data << uint8(0); // 0 - dispelled !=0 cleansed
6948  unitTarget->RemoveAuraHolderDueToSpellByDispel(dispelledHolder->GetId(), m_spellInfo->Id, j->second, dispelledHolder->GetCasterGuid(), m_caster);
6949  }
6950  m_caster->SendMessageToSet(data, true);
6951 
6952  // On success dispel
6953  // Devour Magic
6954  if (m_spellInfo->SpellFamilyName == SPELLFAMILY_WARLOCK && m_spellInfo->Category == SPELLCATEGORY_DEVOUR_MAGIC)
6955  {
6956  int32 heal_amount = m_spellInfo->CalculateSimpleValue(EFFECT_INDEX_1);
6957  m_caster->CastCustomSpell(nullptr, 19658, &heal_amount, nullptr, nullptr, TRIGGERED_OLD_TRIGGERED);
6958  }
6959  }
6960  // Send fail log to client
6961  if (!failList.empty())
6962  {
6963  // Failed to dispel
6964  WorldPacket data(SMSG_DISPEL_FAILED, 8 + 8 + 4 + 4 * failList.size());
6965  data << m_caster->GetObjectGuid(); // Caster GUID
6966  data << unitTarget->GetObjectGuid(); // Victim GUID
6967  data << uint32(m_spellInfo->Id); // Dispel spell id
6968  for (uint32& j : failList)
6969  data << uint32(j); // Spell Id
6970  m_caster->SendMessageToSet(data, true);
6971  }
6972 }

6986 void Spell::EffectDistract(SpellEffectIndex /*eff_idx*/)
6987 {
6988  // Check for possible target
6989  if (!unitTarget || unitTarget->IsInCombat())
6990  return;
6991 
6992  // target must be OK to do this
6993  if (unitTarget->hasUnitState(UNIT_STAT_CAN_NOT_REACT))
6994  return;
6995 
6996  unitTarget->clearUnitState(UNIT_STAT_MOVING);
6997 
6998  if (unitTarget->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_UNIT)
6999  unitTarget->GetMotionMaster()->MoveDistract(damage * IN_MILLISECONDS);
7000

7002  unitTarget->SetFacingTo(orientation);

7004  unitTarget->SetOrientation(orientation);
7005 }

7007 void Spell::EffectPickPocket(SpellEffectIndex /*eff_idx*/)
7008 {
7009  if (m_caster->GetTypeId() != TYPEID_PLAYER)
7010  return;
7011 
7012  // victim must be creature and attackable
7013  if (!unitTarget || unitTarget->GetTypeId() != TYPEID_UNIT || !m_caster->CanAttackNow(unitTarget))
7014  return;
7015 
7016  Creature* creatureTarget = static_cast<Creature*>(unitTarget);
7017  Player* playerCaster = static_cast<Player*>(m_caster);
7018 
7019  int chance = 5; //base failure chance is 5%
7020 
7021  //TODO investigate if font pickpocketing has higher failure chance then from behind
7022  //if (m_caster->IsFacingTargetsFront(unitTarget))
7023  // chance *= 4; //base chance is 20% from the front
7024 
7025  int casterLevel = int32(m_caster->GetLevel());
7026  int targetLevel = int32(unitTarget->GetLevel());
7027 
7028  //we need to increase the base chance for failure if target is higher level then caster
7029  //incremental chance to fail based on level. maximum is 97% chance if level difference is dramatic (give it 3% chance to succeed?).
7030  if (targetLevel > casterLevel)
7031  chance = int32(std::min(int32(std::floor(((targetLevel - casterLevel) * 2.0) + 0.5) * chance), 97));
7032 
7033  int result = urand() % 100;
7034 
7035  if (result >= chance)
7036  {
7037  // Stealing successful
7038  //BASIC_LOG("Successfull pickpocket result %i for chance %i", result, chance);
7039 
7040  Loot*& loot = unitTarget->m_loot;
7041  if (!loot)
7042  loot = new Loot(playerCaster, creatureTarget, LOOT_PICKPOCKETING);
7043  else
7044  {
7045  if (loot->GetLootType() == LOOT_PICKPOCKETING)
7046  {
7047  if (creatureTarget->GetLootStatus() == CREATURE_LOOT_STATUS_PICKPOCKETED)
7048  {
7049  if (creatureTarget->CanRestockPickpocketLoot())
7050  {
7051  // refill pickpocket
7052  delete loot;
7053  loot = new Loot(playerCaster, creatureTarget, LOOT_PICKPOCKETING);
7054  creatureTarget->SetLootStatus(CREATURE_LOOT_STATUS_NONE, true);
7055  }
7056  else
7057  {
7058  playerCaster->SendLootError(unitTarget->GetObjectGuid(), LOOT_ERROR_ALREADY_PICKPOCKETED);
7059  return;
7060  }
7061  } // else not fully taken
7062  }
7063  else
7064  {
7065  delete loot;
7066  loot = new Loot(playerCaster, creatureTarget, LOOT_PICKPOCKETING);
7067  }
7068  }
7069  loot->ShowContentTo(playerCaster);
7070  }
7071  else // current implementation of SPELL_ATTR_EX_FAILURE_BREAKS_STEALTH
7072  {
7073  //BASIC_LOG("Failed pickpocket result %i for chance %i", result, chance);
7074 
7075  // Reveal action + get attack
7076  m_caster->RemoveAurasWithInterruptFlags(AURA_INTERRUPT_FLAG_INTERACTING);
7077  unitTarget->AttackedBy(m_caster);
7078  }
7079 }

7139 void Spell::EffectAddHonor(SpellEffectIndex /*eff_idx*/)
7140 {

7145  if (m_CastItem)
7146  {

7148  DEBUG_FILTER_LOG(LOG_FILTER_SPELL_CAST, "SpellEffect::AddHonor (spell_id %u) rewards %d honor points (item %u) for player: %u", m_spellInfo->Id, damage / 10, m_CastItem->GetEntry(), ((Player*)unitTarget)->GetGUIDLow());
7149  return;
7150  }
7151 
7152  // do not allow to add too many honor for player (50 * 21) = 1040 at level 70, or (50 * 31) = 1550 at level 80
7153  if (damage <= 50)
7154  {
7155  float honor_reward = MaNGOS::Honor::hk_honor_at_level(unitTarget->GetLevel(), damage);
7156  ((Player*)unitTarget)->RewardHonor(nullptr, 1, honor_reward);
7157  DEBUG_FILTER_LOG(LOG_FILTER_SPELL_CAST, "SpellEffect::AddHonor (spell_id %u) rewards %f honor points (scale) to player: %u", m_spellInfo->Id, honor_reward, ((Player*)unitTarget)->GetGUIDLow());
7158  }
7159  else
7160  {
7161  // maybe we have correct honor_gain in damage already
7162  ((Player*)unitTarget)->RewardHonor(nullptr, 1, (float)damage);
7163  sLog.outError("SpellEffect::AddHonor (spell_id %u) rewards %u honor points (non scale) for player: %u", m_spellInfo->Id, damage, ((Player*)unitTarget)->GetGUIDLow());
7164  }
7165 }

7181 void Spell::EffectEnchantItemPerm(SpellEffectIndex eff_idx)
7182 {
7183  if (m_caster->GetTypeId() != TYPEID_PLAYER)
7184  return;
7185  if (!itemTarget)
7186  return;
7187 
7188  uint32 enchant_id = m_spellInfo->EffectMiscValue[eff_idx];
7189  if (!enchant_id)
7190  return;
7191 
7192  SpellItemEnchantmentEntry const* pEnchant = sSpellItemEnchantmentStore.LookupEntry(enchant_id);
7193  if (!pEnchant)
7194  return;
7195 
7196  // item can be in trade slot and have owner diff. from caster
7197  Player* item_owner = itemTarget->GetOwner();
7198  if (!item_owner)
7199  return;
7200 
7201  Player* p_caster = (Player*)m_caster;
7202 
7203  // Enchanting a vellum requires special handling, as it creates a new item
7204  // instead of modifying an existing one.
7205  ItemPrototype const* targetProto = itemTarget->GetProto();
7206  if (targetProto->IsVellum() && m_spellInfo->EffectItemType[eff_idx])
7207  {
7208  unitTarget = m_caster;
7209  DoCreateItem(eff_idx, m_spellInfo->EffectItemType[eff_idx]);
7210  // Vellum target case: Target becomes additional reagent, new scroll item created instead in Spell::EffectEnchantItemPerm()
7211  // cannot already delete in TakeReagents() unfortunately
7212  p_caster->DestroyItemCount(targetProto->ItemId, 1, true);
7213  return;
7214  }
7215 
7216  // Using enchant stored on scroll does not increase enchanting skill! (Already granted on scroll creation)
7217  if (!(m_CastItem && m_CastItem->GetProto()->Flags & ITEM_FLAG_NO_REAGENT_COST))
7218  p_caster->UpdateCraftSkill(m_spellInfo->Id);
7219 
7220  if (item_owner != p_caster && p_caster->GetSession()->GetSecurity() > SEC_PLAYER && sWorld.getConfig(CONFIG_BOOL_GM_LOG_TRADE))
7221  {
7222  sLog.outCommand(p_caster->GetSession()->GetAccountId(), "GM %s (Account: %u) enchanting(perm): %s (Entry: %d) for player: %s (Account: %u)",
7223  p_caster->GetName(), p_caster->GetSession()->GetAccountId(),
7224  itemTarget->GetProto()->Name1, itemTarget->GetEntry(),
7225  item_owner->GetName(), item_owner->GetSession()->GetAccountId());
7226  }
7227 
7228  // remove old enchanting before applying new if equipped
7229  item_owner->ApplyEnchantment(itemTarget, PERM_ENCHANTMENT_SLOT, false);
7230 
7231  itemTarget->SetEnchantment(PERM_ENCHANTMENT_SLOT, enchant_id, 0, 0, m_caster->GetObjectGuid());
7232 
7233  // add new enchanting if equipped
7234  item_owner->ApplyEnchantment(itemTarget, PERM_ENCHANTMENT_SLOT, true);
7235 }

7237 void Spell::EffectEnchantItemPrismatic(SpellEffectIndex eff_idx)
7238 {
7239  if (m_caster->GetTypeId() != TYPEID_PLAYER)
7240  return;
7241  if (!itemTarget)
7242  return;
7243 
7244  Player* p_caster = (Player*)m_caster;
7245 
7246  uint32 enchant_id = m_spellInfo->EffectMiscValue[eff_idx];
7247  if (!enchant_id)
7248  return;
7249

7251  if (!pEnchant)
7252  return;
7253 
7254  // support only enchantings with add socket in this slot
7255  {

7257  for (unsigned int i : pEnchant->type)
7258  {
7259  if (i == ITEM_ENCHANTMENT_TYPE_PRISMATIC_SOCKET)
7260  {
7261  add_socket = true;
7262  break;
7263  }
7264  }
7265  if (!add_socket)
7266  {
7267  sLog.outError("Spell::EffectEnchantItemPrismatic: attempt apply enchant spell %u with SPELL_EFFECT_ENCHANT_ITEM_PRISMATIC (%u) but without ITEM_ENCHANTMENT_TYPE_PRISMATIC_SOCKET (%u), not suppoted yet.",
7268  m_spellInfo->Id, SPELL_EFFECT_ENCHANT_ITEM_PRISMATIC, ITEM_ENCHANTMENT_TYPE_PRISMATIC_SOCKET);
7269  return;
7270  }
7271  }
7272 
7273  // item can be in trade slot and have owner diff. from caster
7274  Player* item_owner = itemTarget->GetOwner();
7275  if (!item_owner)
7276  return;
7277 
7278  if (item_owner != p_caster && p_caster->GetSession()->GetSecurity() > SEC_PLAYER && sWorld.getConfig(CONFIG_BOOL_GM_LOG_TRADE))
7279  {
7280  sLog.outCommand(p_caster->GetSession()->GetAccountId(), "GM %s (Account: %u) enchanting(perm): %s (Entry: %d) for player: %s (Account: %u)",
7281  p_caster->GetName(), p_caster->GetSession()->GetAccountId(),
7282  itemTarget->GetProto()->Name1, itemTarget->GetEntry(),
7283  item_owner->GetName(), item_owner->GetSession()->GetAccountId());
7284  }
7285 
7286  // remove old enchanting before applying new if equipped
7287  item_owner->ApplyEnchantment(itemTarget, PRISMATIC_ENCHANTMENT_SLOT, false);
7288 
7289  itemTarget->SetEnchantment(PRISMATIC_ENCHANTMENT_SLOT, enchant_id, 0, 0, m_caster->GetObjectGuid());
7290 
7291  // add new enchanting if equipped
7292  item_owner->ApplyEnchantment(itemTarget, PRISMATIC_ENCHANTMENT_SLOT, true);
7293 }

7295 void Spell::EffectEnchantItemTmp(SpellEffectIndex eff_idx)
7296 {
7297  if (m_caster->GetTypeId() != TYPEID_PLAYER)
7298  return;
7299 
7300  Player* p_caster = (Player*)m_caster;
7301 
7302  // Rockbiter Weapon
7303  if (m_spellInfo->SpellFamilyName == SPELLFAMILY_SHAMAN && m_spellInfo->SpellFamilyFlags & uint64(0x0000000000400000))
7304  {
7305  uint32 spell_id;
7306 
7307  // enchanting spell selected by calculated damage-per-sec stored in Effect[1] base value
7308  // Note: damage calculated (correctly) with rounding int32(float(v)) but
7309  // RW enchantments applied damage int32(float(v)+0.5), this create 0..1 difference sometime
7310  switch (damage)
7311  {
7312  // Rank 1
7313  case 2: spell_id = 36744; break; // 0% [ 7% == 2, 14% == 2, 20% == 2]
7314  // Rank 2
7315  case 4: spell_id = 36753; break; // 0% [ 7% == 4, 14% == 4]
7316  case 5: spell_id = 36751; break; // 20%
7317  // Rank 3
7318  case 6: spell_id = 36754; break; // 0% [ 7% == 6, 14% == 6]
7319  case 7: spell_id = 36755; break; // 20%
7320  // Rank 4
7321  case 9: spell_id = 36761; break; // 0% [ 7% == 6]
7322  case 10: spell_id = 36758; break; // 14%
7323  case 11: spell_id = 36760; break; // 20%
7324  default:
7325  sLog.outError("Spell::EffectEnchantItemTmp: Damage %u not handled in S'RW", damage);
7326  return;
7327  }
7328 
7329  SpellEntry const* spellInfo = sSpellTemplate.LookupEntry<SpellEntry>(spell_id);
7330  if (!spellInfo)
7331  {
7332  sLog.outError("Spell::EffectEnchantItemTmp: unknown spell id %i", spell_id);
7333  return;
7334  }
7335 
7336  Spell* spell = new Spell(m_caster, spellInfo, TRIGGERED_OLD_TRIGGERED);
7337  SpellCastTargets targets;
7338  targets.setItemTarget(itemTarget);
7339  spell->SpellStart(&targets);
7340  return;
7341  }
7342 
7343  if (!itemTarget)
7344  return;
7345 
7346  uint32 enchant_id = m_spellInfo->EffectMiscValue[eff_idx];
7347 
7348  if (!enchant_id)
7349  {
7350  sLog.outError("Spell %u Effect %u (SPELL_EFFECT_ENCHANT_ITEM_TEMPORARY) have 0 as enchanting id", m_spellInfo->Id, eff_idx);
7351  return;
7352  }
7353 
7354  SpellItemEnchantmentEntry const* pEnchant = sSpellItemEnchantmentStore.LookupEntry(enchant_id);
7355  if (!pEnchant)
7356  {
7357  sLog.outError("Spell %u Effect %u (SPELL_EFFECT_ENCHANT_ITEM_TEMPORARY) have nonexistent enchanting id %u ", m_spellInfo->Id, eff_idx, enchant_id);
7358  return;
7359  }
7360 
7361  // select enchantment duration
7362  uint32 duration;
7363 
7364  // rogue family enchantments exception by duration
7365  if (m_spellInfo->Id == 38615)
7366  duration = 1800; // 30 mins
7367  // other rogue family enchantments always 1 hour (some have spell damage=0, but some have wrong data in EffBasePoints)
7368  else if (m_spellInfo->SpellFamilyName == SPELLFAMILY_ROGUE)
7369  duration = 3600; // 1 hour
7370  // shaman family enchantments
7371  else if (m_spellInfo->SpellFamilyName == SPELLFAMILY_SHAMAN)
7372  duration = 1800; // 30 mins
7373  // other cases with this SpellVisual already selected
7374  else if (m_spellInfo->SpellVisual[0] == 215)
7375  duration = 1800; // 30 mins
7376  // some fishing pole bonuses
7377  else if (m_spellInfo->SpellVisual[0] == 563)
7378  duration = 600; // 10 mins
7379  // shaman rockbiter enchantments
7380  else if (m_spellInfo->SpellVisual[0] == 0)
7381  duration = 1800; // 30 mins
7382  else if (m_spellInfo->Id == 29702)
7383  duration = 300; // 5 mins
7384  else if (m_spellInfo->Id == 37360)
7385  duration = 300; // 5 mins
7386  // default case
7387  else
7388  duration = 3600; // 1 hour
7389 
7390  // item can be in trade slot and have owner diff. from caster
7391  Player* item_owner = itemTarget->GetOwner();
7392  if (!item_owner)
7393  return;
7394 
7395  if (item_owner != p_caster && p_caster->GetSession()->GetSecurity() > SEC_PLAYER && sWorld.getConfig(CONFIG_BOOL_GM_LOG_TRADE))
7396  {
7397  sLog.outCommand(p_caster->GetSession()->GetAccountId(), "GM %s (Account: %u) enchanting(temp): %s (Entry: %d) for player: %s (Account: %u)",
7398  p_caster->GetName(), p_caster->GetSession()->GetAccountId(),
7399  itemTarget->GetProto()->Name1, itemTarget->GetEntry(),
7400  item_owner->GetName(), item_owner->GetSession()->GetAccountId());
7401  }
7402 
7403  // remove old enchanting before applying new if equipped
7404  item_owner->ApplyEnchantment(itemTarget, TEMP_ENCHANTMENT_SLOT, false);
7405 
7406  itemTarget->SetEnchantment(TEMP_ENCHANTMENT_SLOT, enchant_id, duration * 1000, 0, m_caster->GetObjectGuid());
7407 
7408  // add new enchanting if equipped
7409  item_owner->ApplyEnchantment(itemTarget, TEMP_ENCHANTMENT_SLOT, true);
7410 }

7412 void Spell::EffectTameCreature(SpellEffectIndex /*eff_idx*/)
7413 {
7414  // Caster must be player, checked in Spell::CheckCast
7415  // Spell can be triggered, we need to check original caster prior to caster
7416  Player* plr = static_cast<Player*>(GetAffectiveCaster());
7417 
7418  Creature* creatureTarget = static_cast<Creature*>(unitTarget);
7419 
7420  // cast finish successfully
7421  // SendChannelUpdate(0);
7422  finish();
7423 
7424  Pet* pet = new Pet(HUNTER_PET);
7425 
7426  if (!pet->CreateBaseAtCreature(creatureTarget))
7427  {
7428  delete pet;
7429  return;
7430  }
7431 
7432  pet->SetLoading(true);
7433  pet->SetOwnerGuid(plr->GetObjectGuid());
7434  pet->setFaction(plr->GetFaction());
7435  pet->SetUInt32Value(UNIT_CREATED_BY_SPELL, m_spellInfo->Id);
7436 
7437  if (plr->HasFlag(UNIT_FIELD_FLAGS, UNIT_FLAG_PLAYER_CONTROLLED))
7438  pet->SetFlag(UNIT_FIELD_FLAGS, UNIT_FLAG_PLAYER_CONTROLLED);
7439 
7440  if (plr->IsImmuneToNPC())
7441  pet->SetImmuneToNPC(true);
7442 
7443  if (plr->IsImmuneToPlayer())
7444  pet->SetImmuneToPlayer(true);
7445 
7446  if (plr->IsPvP())
7447  pet->SetPvP(true);
7448 
7449  if (plr->IsPvPFreeForAll())
7450  pet->SetPvPFreeForAll(true);
7451 
7452  if (plr->IsPvPSanctuary())
7453  pet->SetPvPSanctuary(true);
7454 
7455  pet->GetCharmInfo()->SetPetNumber(sObjectMgr.GeneratePetNumber(), true);
7456 
7457  // level of hunter pet can't be less owner level at 5 levels
7458  uint32 cLevel = creatureTarget->GetLevel();
7459  uint32 plLevel = plr->GetLevel();
7460  uint32 level = (cLevel + 5) < plLevel ? (plLevel - 5) : cLevel;
7461  pet->SetCanModifyStats(true);
7462  pet->InitStatsForLevel(level);
7463  pet->InitLevelupSpellsForLevel();
7464  pet->InitTalentForLevel();
7465 
7466  pet->SetHealthPercent(creatureTarget->GetHealthPercent());
7467 
7468  // destroy creature object
7469  creatureTarget->ForcedDespawn();
7470 
7471  // prepare visual effect for levelup
7472  pet->SetUInt32Value(UNIT_FIELD_LEVEL, level - 1);
7473 
7474  // add pet object to the world
7475  pet->GetMap()->Add((Creature*)pet);
7476  pet->AIM_Initialize();
7477 
7478  pet->AI()->SetReactState(REACT_DEFENSIVE);
7479 
7480  // visual effect for levelup
7481  pet->SetUInt32Value(UNIT_FIELD_LEVEL, level);
7482 
7483  // this enables pet details window (Shift+P)
7484  pet->InitPetCreateSpells();
7485 
7486  // this add pet auras
7487  pet->LearnPetPassives();
7488  pet->CastPetAuras(true);
7489  pet->CastOwnerTalentAuras();
7490  pet->UpdateAllStats();
7491 
7492  // caster have pet now
7493  plr->SetPet(pet);
7494 
7495  plr->PetSpellInitialize();
7496  pet->SetLoading(false);
7497 
7498  pet->SavePetToDB(PET_SAVE_AS_CURRENT, plr);
7499 }

7501 void Spell::EffectSummonPet(SpellEffectIndex eff_idx)
7502 {
7503  uint32 petentry = m_spellInfo->EffectMiscValue[eff_idx];
7504 
7505  Pet* NewSummon = new Pet;
7506 
7507  Player* _player = nullptr;
7508 
7509  Position spawnPos(m_targets.m_destPos.x, m_targets.m_destPos.y, m_targets.m_destPos.z, -m_caster->GetOrientation());
7510 
7511  if (m_caster->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_PLAYER)
7512  {
7513  _player = static_cast<Player*>(m_caster);
7514 
7515  switch (m_caster->getClass())
7516  {
7517  case CLASS_HUNTER:
7518  {
7519  if (NewSummon->LoadPetFromDB(_player, spawnPos))
7520  {
7521  OnSummon(NewSummon);
7522  m_spellLog.AddLog(uint32(SPELL_EFFECT_SUMMON_PET), NewSummon->GetPackGUID());
7523  }
7524  else
7525  delete NewSummon;
7526  return;
7527  }
7528  default:
7529  {
7530  if (Pet* OldSummon = m_caster->GetPet())
7531  OldSummon->Unsummon(PET_SAVE_NOT_IN_SLOT, m_caster);
7532 
7533  // Load pet from db; if any to load
7534  if (NewSummon->LoadPetFromDB(_player, spawnPos, petentry))
7535  {
7536  NewSummon->SetHealth(NewSummon->GetMaxHealth());
7537  NewSummon->SetPower(POWER_MANA, NewSummon->GetMaxPower(POWER_MANA));
7538  OnSummon(NewSummon);
7539  m_spellLog.AddLog(uint32(SPELL_EFFECT_SUMMON_PET), NewSummon->GetPackGUID());
7540  return;
7541  }
7542 
7543  NewSummon->setPetType(SUMMON_PET);
7544  }
7545  }
7546  }
7547  else
7548  NewSummon->setPetType(GUARDIAN_PET);
7549 
7550  CreatureInfo const* cInfo = petentry ? ObjectMgr::GetCreatureTemplate(petentry) : nullptr;
7551  if (!cInfo)
7552  {
7553  sLog.outErrorDb("EffectSummonPet: creature entry %u not found for spell %u.", petentry, m_spellInfo->Id);
7554  delete NewSummon;
7555  return;
7556  }
7557 
7558  CreatureCreatePos pos(m_caster->GetMap(), spawnPos.x, spawnPos.y, spawnPos.z, spawnPos.o, m_caster->GetPhaseMask());
7559 
7560  Map* map = m_caster->GetMap();
7561  uint32 pet_number = sObjectMgr.GeneratePetNumber();
7562  if (!NewSummon->Create(map->GenerateLocalLowGuid(HIGHGUID_PET), pos, cInfo, pet_number))
7563  {
7564  delete NewSummon;
7565  return;
7566  }
7567 
7568  NewSummon->SetRespawnCoord(pos);
7569 
7570  // Level of pet summoned
7571  uint32 level = std::max(m_caster->GetLevel() + m_spellInfo->EffectMultipleValue[eff_idx], 1.0f);
7572  if (m_ignoreOwnerLevel)
7573  level = urand(cInfo->MinLevel, cInfo->MaxLevel);
7574  NewSummon->SetOwnerGuid(m_caster->GetObjectGuid());
7575  NewSummon->setFaction(m_caster->GetFaction());
7576  NewSummon->SetUInt32Value(UNIT_FIELD_PET_NAME_TIMESTAMP, uint32(time(nullptr)));
7577  NewSummon->SetUInt32Value(UNIT_CREATED_BY_SPELL, m_spellInfo->Id);
7578 
7579  NewSummon->SetCanModifyStats(true);
7580  NewSummon->InitStatsForLevel(level);
7581  NewSummon->InitPetCreateSpells();
7582  NewSummon->InitLevelupSpellsForLevel();
7583  NewSummon->InitTalentForLevel();
7584 
7585  NewSummon->LearnPetPassives();
7586  NewSummon->CastPetAuras(true);
7587  NewSummon->CastOwnerTalentAuras();
7588  NewSummon->UpdateAllStats();
7589 
7590  if (NewSummon->getPetType() == GUARDIAN_PET)
7591  m_caster->AddGuardian(NewSummon);
7592  else
7593  m_caster->SetPet(NewSummon);
7594  DEBUG_LOG("New Pet has guid %u", NewSummon->GetGUIDLow());
7595 
7596  if (m_caster->HasFlag(UNIT_FIELD_FLAGS, UNIT_FLAG_PLAYER_CONTROLLED))
7597  {
7598  NewSummon->SetUInt32Value(UNIT_FIELD_FLAGS, UNIT_FLAG_PLAYER_CONTROLLED);
7599  NewSummon->SetUInt32Value(UNIT_NPC_FLAGS, UNIT_NPC_FLAG_NONE);
7600  }
7601  else
7602  {
7603  NewSummon->SetFlag(UNIT_FIELD_FLAGS, cInfo->UnitFlags);
7604  NewSummon->SetUInt32Value(UNIT_NPC_FLAGS, cInfo->NpcFlags);
7605  }
7606 
7607  if (m_caster->IsImmuneToNPC())
7608  NewSummon->SetImmuneToNPC(true);
7609 
7610  if (m_caster->IsImmuneToPlayer())
7611  NewSummon->SetImmuneToPlayer(true);
7612 
7613  if (m_caster->IsPvP())
7614  NewSummon->SetPvP(true);
7615 
7616  if (m_caster->IsPvPFreeForAll())
7617  NewSummon->SetPvPFreeForAll(true);
7618 
7619  if (m_caster->IsPvPSanctuary())
7620  NewSummon->SetPvPSanctuary(true);
7621 
7622  map->Add((Creature*)NewSummon);
7623  NewSummon->AIM_Initialize();
7624 
7625  NewSummon->AI()->SetReactState(REACT_DEFENSIVE);
7626 
7627  if (_player)
7628  {
7629  NewSummon->SetByteValue(UNIT_FIELD_BYTES_2, 1, UNIT_BYTE2_FLAG_AURAS);
7630 
7631  NewSummon->GetCharmInfo()->SetPetNumber(pet_number, true);
7632 
7633  // generate new name for summon pet
7634  NewSummon->SetName(sObjectMgr.GeneratePetName(petentry));
7635 
7636  NewSummon->SavePetToDB(PET_SAVE_AS_CURRENT, _player);
7637  _player->PetSpellInitialize();
7638  NewSummon->SetLoading(false);
7639  }
7640  else
7641  {
7642  NewSummon->SetLoading(false);
7643  // Notify Summoner
7644  if (m_originalCaster && (m_originalCaster != m_caster) && (m_originalCaster->AI()))
7645  m_originalCaster->AI()->JustSummoned(NewSummon);
7646  else if (m_caster->AI())
7647  m_caster->AI()->JustSummoned(NewSummon);
7648  }
7649 
7650  if (GenericTransport* transport = m_caster->GetTransport())
7651  transport->AddPetToTransport(m_caster, NewSummon);
7652 
7653  OnSummon(NewSummon);
7654  m_spellLog.AddLog(uint32(SPELL_EFFECT_SUMMON_PET), NewSummon->GetPackGUID());
7655 }

7657 void Spell::EffectLearnPetSpell(SpellEffectIndex eff_idx)
7658 {
7659  if (m_caster->GetTypeId() != TYPEID_PLAYER)
7660  return;
7661 
7662  Player* _player = static_cast<Player*>(m_caster);
7663 
7664  Pet* pet = _player->GetPet();
7665  if (!pet)
7666  return;
7667  if (!pet->IsAlive())
7668  return;
7669 
7670  SpellEntry const* learn_spellproto = sSpellTemplate.LookupEntry<SpellEntry>(m_spellInfo->EffectTriggerSpell[eff_idx]);
7671  if (!learn_spellproto)
7672  return;
7673 
7674  pet->learnSpell(learn_spellproto->Id);
7675 
7676  pet->SavePetToDB(PET_SAVE_AS_CURRENT, _player);
7677  _player->PetSpellInitialize();
7678 
7679  if (WorldObject const* caster = GetCastingObject())
7680  DEBUG_LOG("Spell: %s has learned spell %u from %s", pet->GetGuidStr().c_str(), learn_spellproto->Id, caster->GetGuidStr().c_str());
7681 }
7682 
7683 void Spell::EffectTaunt(SpellEffectIndex eff_idx)
7684 {
7685  if (!unitTarget)
7686  return;
7687 
7688  // this effect use before aura Taunt apply for prevent taunt already attacking target
7689  // for spell as marked "non effective at already attacking target"
7690  if (unitTarget->GetTypeId() != TYPEID_PLAYER)
7691  {
7692  if (unitTarget->GetVictim() == m_caster)
7693  {
7694  SendCastResult(SPELL_FAILED_DONT_REPORT);
7695  return;
7696  }
7697  }
7698 
7699  // Also use this effect to set the taunter's threat to the taunted creature's highest value
7700  if (unitTarget->CanHaveThreatList())
7701  {
7702  float addedThreat = unitTarget->getThreatManager().GetHighestThreat() - unitTarget->getThreatManager().getThreat(m_caster);
7703  unitTarget->getThreatManager().addThreatDirectly(m_caster, addedThreat);
7704  unitTarget->getThreatManager().setCurrentVictimByTarget(m_caster); // force changes the target to caster of taunt
7705  }
7706  // Units without threat lists but with AI are susceptible to attack target interference by taunt effect:
7707  else if (!unitTarget->CanHaveThreatList() && !unitTarget->hasUnitState(UNIT_STAT_CAN_NOT_REACT_OR_LOST_CONTROL))
7708  {
7709  if (UnitAI* ai = unitTarget->AI())
7710  {
7711  // 2.4.3+: "Passive pets will no longer attack due to AoE taunt spells."
7712  if (ai->HasReactState(REACT_PASSIVE) && !unitTarget->GetVictim())
7713  {
7714  if (SpellTargetInfoTable[m_spellInfo->EffectImplicitTargetA[eff_idx]].enumerator != TARGET_ENUMERATOR_SINGLE)
7715  return;
7716 
7717  if (SpellTargetInfoTable[m_spellInfo->EffectImplicitTargetB[eff_idx]].enumerator != TARGET_ENUMERATOR_SINGLE)
7718  return;
7719  }
7720 
7721  ai->AttackStart(m_caster);
7722  }
7723  }
7724 }
7725 
7726 void Spell::EffectWeaponDmg(SpellEffectIndex eff_idx)
7727 {
7728  if (!unitTarget)
7729  return;
7730  if (!unitTarget->IsAlive())
7731  return;
7732 
7733  // multiple weapon dmg effect workaround
7734  // execute only the last weapon damage
7735  // and handle all effects at once
7736  for (int j = 0; j < MAX_EFFECT_INDEX; ++j)
7737  {
7738  switch (m_spellInfo->Effect[j])
7739  {
7740  case SPELL_EFFECT_WEAPON_DAMAGE:
7741  case SPELL_EFFECT_WEAPON_DAMAGE_NOSCHOOL:
7742  case SPELL_EFFECT_NORMALIZED_WEAPON_DMG:
7743  case SPELL_EFFECT_WEAPON_PERCENT_DAMAGE:
7744  if (j > int(eff_idx)) // we must calculate only at last weapon effect
7745  return;
7746  break;
7747  }
7748  }
7749 
7750  // some spell specific modifiers
7751  bool spellBonusNeedWeaponDamagePercentMod = false; // if set applied weapon damage percent mode to spell bonus
7752 
7753  float weaponDamagePercentMod = 1.0f; // applied to weapon damage and to fixed effect damage bonus
7754  float totalDamagePercentMod = 1.0f; // applied to final bonus+weapon damage
7755  bool normalized = false;
7756 
7757  int32 spell_bonus = 0; // bonus specific for spell
7758 
7759  switch (m_spellInfo->SpellFamilyName)
7760  {
7761  case SPELLFAMILY_GENERIC:
7762  {
7763  switch (m_spellInfo->Id)
7764  {
7765  // for spells with divided damage to targets
7766  case 66765: case 66809: case 67331: // Meteor Fists
7767  case 67333: // Meteor Fists
7768  case 69055: // Bone Slice
7769  case 71021: // Saber Lash
7770  {
7771  uint32 count = 0;
7772  for (TargetList::const_iterator ihit = m_UniqueTargetInfo.begin(); ihit != m_UniqueTargetInfo.end(); ++ihit)
7773  if (ihit->effectMask & (1 << eff_idx))
7774  ++count;
7775 
7776  totalDamagePercentMod /= float(count); // divide to all targets
7777  break;
7778  }
7779  }
7780  break;
7781  }
7782  case SPELLFAMILY_ROGUE:
7783  {
7784  // Mutilate (for each hand)
7785  if (m_spellInfo->SpellFamilyFlags & uint64(0x600000000))
7786  {
7787  bool found = false;
7788  // fast check
7789  if (unitTarget->HasAuraState(AURA_STATE_DEADLY_POISON))
7790  found = true;
7791  // full aura scan
7792  else
7793  {
7794  Unit::SpellAuraHolderMap const& auras = unitTarget->GetSpellAuraHolderMap();
7795  for (const auto& aura : auras)
7796  {
7797  if (aura.second->GetSpellProto()->Dispel == DISPEL_POISON)
7798  {
7799  found = true;
7800  break;
7801  }
7802  }
7803  }
7804 
7805  if (found)
7806  totalDamagePercentMod *= 1.2f; // 120% if poisoned
7807  }
7808  // Fan of Knives
7809  else if (m_caster->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_PLAYER && (m_spellInfo->SpellFamilyFlags & uint64(0x0004000000000000)))
7810  {
7811  Item* weapon = ((Player*)m_caster)->GetWeaponForAttack(m_attackType, true, true);
7812  if (weapon && weapon->GetProto()->SubClass == ITEM_SUBCLASS_WEAPON_DAGGER)
7813  totalDamagePercentMod *= 1.5f; // 150% to daggers
7814  }
7815  // Ghostly Strike
7816  else if (m_caster->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_PLAYER && m_spellInfo->Id == 14278)
7817  {
7818  Item* weapon = ((Player*)m_caster)->GetWeaponForAttack(m_attackType, true, true);
7819  if (weapon && weapon->GetProto()->SubClass == ITEM_SUBCLASS_WEAPON_DAGGER)
7820  totalDamagePercentMod *= 1.44f; // 144% to daggers
7821  }
7822  // Hemorrhage
7823  else if (m_caster->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_PLAYER && (m_spellInfo->SpellFamilyFlags & uint64(0x2000000)))
7824  {
7825  Item* weapon = ((Player*)m_caster)->GetWeaponForAttack(m_attackType, true, true);
7826  if (weapon && weapon->GetProto()->SubClass == ITEM_SUBCLASS_WEAPON_DAGGER)
7827  totalDamagePercentMod *= 1.45f; // 145% to daggers
7828  }
7829  break;
7830  }
7831  case SPELLFAMILY_PALADIN:
7832  {
7833  // Judgement of Command - receive benefit from Spell Damage and Attack Power
7834  if (m_spellInfo->SpellFamilyFlags & uint64(0x00020000000000))
7835  {
7836  float ap = m_caster->GetTotalAttackPowerValue(BASE_ATTACK);
7837  int32 holy = m_caster->SpellBaseDamageBonusDone(GetSpellSchoolMask(m_spellInfo));
7838  if (holy < 0)
7839  holy = 0;
7840  spell_bonus += int32(ap * 0.08f) + int32(holy * 13 / 100);
7841  }
7842  break;
7843  }
7844  case SPELLFAMILY_HUNTER:
7845  {
7846  // Kill Shot
7847  if (m_spellInfo->SpellFamilyFlags & uint64(0x80000000000000))
7848  {
7849  // 0.4*RAP added to damage (that is 0.2 if we apply PercentMod (200%) to spell_bonus, too)
7850  spellBonusNeedWeaponDamagePercentMod = true;
7851  spell_bonus += int32(0.2f * m_caster->GetTotalAttackPowerValue(RANGED_ATTACK));
7852  }
7853  break;
7854  }
7855  case SPELLFAMILY_SHAMAN:
7856  {
7857  // Skyshatter Harness item set bonus
7858  // Stormstrike
7859  if (m_spellInfo->SpellFamilyFlags & uint64(0x001000000000))
7860  {
7861  if (Aura* aura = m_caster->GetOverrideScript(5634))
7862  m_caster->CastSpell(nullptr, 38430, TRIGGERED_OLD_TRIGGERED, nullptr, aura);
7863  }
7864  break;
7865  }
7866  case SPELLFAMILY_DEATHKNIGHT:
7867  {
7868  // Blood Strike, Heart Strike, Obliterate
7869  // Blood-Caked Strike
7870  if (m_spellInfo->SpellFamilyFlags & uint64(0x0002000001400000) ||
7871  m_spellInfo->SpellIconID == 1736)
7872  {
7873  uint32 count = 0;
7874  Unit::SpellAuraHolderMap const& auras = unitTarget->GetSpellAuraHolderMap();
7875  for (const auto& aura : auras)
7876  {
7877  if (aura.second->GetSpellProto()->Dispel == DISPEL_DISEASE &&
7878  aura.second->GetCasterGuid() == m_caster->GetObjectGuid())
7879  ++count;
7880  }
7881 
7882  if (count)
7883  {
7884  // Effect 1(for Blood-Caked Strike)/3(other) damage is bonus
7885  float bonus = count * CalculateSpellEffectValue(m_spellInfo->SpellIconID == 1736 ? EFFECT_INDEX_0 : EFFECT_INDEX_2, unitTarget) / 100.0f;
7886  // Blood Strike, Blood-Caked Strike and Obliterate store bonus*2
7887  if (m_spellInfo->SpellFamilyFlags & uint64(0x0002000000400000) ||
7888  m_spellInfo->SpellIconID == 1736)
7889  bonus /= 2.0f;
7890 
7891  totalDamagePercentMod *= 1.0f + bonus;
7892  }
7893  }
7894  // Glyph of Blood Strike
7895  if (m_spellInfo->SpellFamilyFlags & uint64(0x0000000000400000) &&
7896  m_caster->HasAura(59332) &&
7897  unitTarget->HasAuraType(SPELL_AURA_MOD_DECREASE_SPEED))
7898  {
7899  totalDamagePercentMod *= 1.2f; // 120% if snared
7900  }
7901  // Glyph of Death Strike
7902  if (m_spellInfo->SpellFamilyFlags & uint64(0x0000000000000010) &&
7903  m_caster->HasAura(59336))
7904  {
7905  int32 rp = m_caster->GetPower(POWER_RUNIC_POWER) / 10;
7906  if (rp > 25)
7907  rp = 25;
7908  totalDamagePercentMod *= 1.0f + rp / 100.0f;
7909  }
7910  // Glyph of Plague Strike
7911  if (m_spellInfo->SpellFamilyFlags & uint64(0x0000000000000001) &&
7912  m_caster->HasAura(58657))
7913  {
7914  totalDamagePercentMod *= 1.2f;
7915  }
7916  break;
7917  }
7918  }
7919 
7920  int32 fixed_bonus = 0;
7921  for (int j = 0; j < MAX_EFFECT_INDEX; ++j)
7922  {
7923  switch (m_spellInfo->Effect[j])
7924  {
7925  case SPELL_EFFECT_WEAPON_DAMAGE:
7926  case SPELL_EFFECT_WEAPON_DAMAGE_NOSCHOOL:
7927  fixed_bonus += damagePerEffect[j];
7928  break;
7929  case SPELL_EFFECT_NORMALIZED_WEAPON_DMG:
7930  fixed_bonus += damagePerEffect[j];
7931  normalized = true;
7932  break;
7933  case SPELL_EFFECT_WEAPON_PERCENT_DAMAGE:
7934  weaponDamagePercentMod *= float(damagePerEffect[j]) / 100.0f;
7935 
7936  // applied only to prev.effects fixed damage
7937  fixed_bonus = int32(fixed_bonus * weaponDamagePercentMod);
7938  break;
7939  default:
7940  break; // not weapon damage effect, just skip
7941  }
7942  }
7943 
7944  // apply weaponDamagePercentMod to spell bonus also
7945  if (spellBonusNeedWeaponDamagePercentMod)
7946  spell_bonus = int32(spell_bonus * weaponDamagePercentMod);
7947 
7948  // non-weapon damage
7949  int32 bonus = spell_bonus + fixed_bonus;
7950 
7951  bool addDamage = false; // hack in place until effect handler is split up
7952  switch (m_spellInfo->DmgClass)
7953  {
7954  case SPELL_DAMAGE_CLASS_MELEE:
7955  case SPELL_DAMAGE_CLASS_RANGED: addDamage = true; break;
7956  case SPELL_DAMAGE_CLASS_MAGIC: break; // TODO: Add behaviour for spell behaviour
7957  case SPELL_DAMAGE_CLASS_NONE: break; // do nothing
7958  }
7959 
7960  if (m_spellInfo->Effect[eff_idx] == SPELL_EFFECT_WEAPON_DAMAGE_NOSCHOOL)
7961  addDamage = true;
7962 
7963  if (addDamage)
7964  {
7965  // apply to non-weapon bonus weapon total pct effect, weapon total flat effect included in weapon damage
7966  if (bonus)
7967  {
7968  UnitMods unitMod;
7969  switch (m_attackType)
7970  {
7971  default:
7972  case BASE_ATTACK: unitMod = UNIT_MOD_DAMAGE_MAINHAND; break;
7973  case OFF_ATTACK: unitMod = UNIT_MOD_DAMAGE_OFFHAND; break;
7974  case RANGED_ATTACK: unitMod = UNIT_MOD_DAMAGE_RANGED; break;
7975  }
7976 
7977  float weapon_total_pct = m_caster->GetModifierValue(unitMod, TOTAL_PCT);
7978  bonus = int32(bonus * weapon_total_pct);
7979  }
7980 
7981  // + weapon damage with applied weapon% dmg to base weapon damage in call
7982  bonus += int32(m_caster->CalculateDamage(m_attackType, normalized) * weaponDamagePercentMod);
7983  }
7984 
7985  // total damage
7986  bonus = int32(bonus * totalDamagePercentMod);
7987 
7988  // prevent negative damage
7989  m_damagePerEffect[eff_idx] = CalculateSpellEffectDamage(unitTarget, bonus);
7990 
7991  // Hemorrhage
7992  if (m_spellInfo->SpellFamilyName == SPELLFAMILY_ROGUE && (m_spellInfo->SpellFamilyFlags & uint64(0x2000000)))
7993  {
7994  if (m_caster->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_PLAYER)
7995  ((Player*)m_caster)->AddComboPoints(unitTarget, 1);
7996  }
7997  // Mangle (Cat): CP
7998  else if (m_spellInfo->IsFitToFamily(SPELLFAMILY_DRUID, uint64(0x0000040000000000)))
7999  {
8000  if (m_caster->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_PLAYER)
8001  ((Player*)m_caster)->AddComboPoints(unitTarget, 1);
8002  }
8003 
8004 }
8005 
8006 void Spell::EffectThreat(SpellEffectIndex /*eff_idx*/)
8007 {
8008  if (!unitTarget || !unitTarget->IsAlive() || !m_caster->IsAlive())
8009  return;
8010 
8011  if (!unitTarget->CanHaveThreatList())
8012  return;
8013 
8014  if (!m_caster->IsInCombat() || !unitTarget->IsInCombat())
8015  {
8016  if (unitTarget->AI())
8017  unitTarget->AI()->AttackStart(m_caster);
8018  else
8019  unitTarget->EngageInCombatWith(m_caster);
8020  }
8021 
8022  unitTarget->AddThreat(m_caster, float(damage), false, GetSpellSchoolMask(m_spellInfo), m_spellInfo);
8023 }
8024 
8025 void Spell::EffectHealMaxHealth(SpellEffectIndex /*eff_idx*/)
8026 {
8027  if (!unitTarget)
8028  return;
8029  if (!unitTarget->IsAlive())
8030  return;
8031 
8032  uint32 heal = m_caster->GetMaxHealth();
8033 
8034  m_healing += heal;
8035 }

8037 void Spell::EffectInterruptCast(SpellEffectIndex eff_idx)
8038 {
8039  if (!unitTarget)
8040  return;
8041  if (!unitTarget->IsAlive())
8042  return;
8043 
8044  uint32 interruptedSpellId = 0;
8045  // TODO: not all spells that used this effect apply cooldown at school spells
8046  // also exist case: apply cooldown to interrupted cast only and to all spells
8047  for (uint32 i = CURRENT_FIRST_NON_MELEE_SPELL; i < CURRENT_MAX_SPELL; ++i)
8048  {
8049  if (Spell* spell = unitTarget->GetCurrentSpell(CurrentSpellTypes(i)))
8050  {
8051  SpellEntry const* curSpellInfo = spell->m_spellInfo;
8052  // check if we can interrupt spell
8053  if (spell->IsInterruptible())
8054  {
8055  unitTarget->LockOutSpells(GetSpellSchoolMask(curSpellInfo), unitTarget->CalculateAuraDuration(m_spellInfo, (1 << eff_idx), GetSpellDuration(m_spellInfo), m_caster));
8056  unitTarget->InterruptSpell(CurrentSpellTypes(i), false);
8057  interruptedSpellId = curSpellInfo->Id;
8058  }
8059  }
8060  }
8061 
8062  if (interruptedSpellId)
8063  m_spellLog.AddLog(uint32(SPELL_EFFECT_INTERRUPT_CAST), unitTarget->GetPackGUID(), interruptedSpellId);
8064 }

8066 void Spell::EffectSummonObjectWild(SpellEffectIndex eff_idx)
8067 {
8068  uint32 gameobject_id = m_spellInfo->EffectMiscValue[eff_idx];
8069 
8070  GameObject* pGameObj = new GameObject;
8071 
8072  WorldObject* target = m_eventTarget;
8073  if (!target)
8074  target = m_trueCaster;
8075 
8076  float x, y, z;
8077  if (m_targets.m_targetMask & TARGET_FLAG_DEST_LOCATION)
8078  m_targets.getDestination(x, y, z);
8079  else
8080  m_trueCaster->GetClosePoint(x, y, z, DEFAULT_WORLD_OBJECT_SIZE);
8081 
8082  Map* map = target->GetMap();
8083  uint32 lowGuid = map->GenerateLocalLowGuid(HIGHGUID_GAMEOBJECT);
8084  if (!pGameObj->Create(lowGuid, lowGuid, gameobject_id, map,
8085  m_trueCaster->GetPhaseMask(), x, y, z, target->GetOrientation()))
8086  {
8087  delete pGameObj;
8088  return;
8089  }
8090 
8091  pGameObj->SetRespawnTime(m_duration > 0 ? m_duration / IN_MILLISECONDS : 0);
8092  pGameObj->SetSpellId(m_spellInfo->Id);
8093  pGameObj->SetSpawnerGuid(m_trueCaster->GetObjectGuid());
8094 
8095  // Wild object not have owner and check clickable by players
8096  map->Add(pGameObj);
8097  pGameObj->AIM_Initialize();
8098 
8099  // Notify Summoner
8100  if (!m_trueCaster->IsGameObject())
8101  {
8102  // Store the GO to the caster
8103  m_caster->AddWildGameObject(pGameObj);
8104 
8105  if (m_originalCaster && (m_originalCaster != m_caster) && (m_originalCaster->AI()))
8106  m_originalCaster->AI()->JustSummoned(pGameObj);
8107  else if (m_caster->AI())
8108  m_caster->AI()->JustSummoned(pGameObj);
8109  }
8110 
8111  OnSummon(pGameObj);
8112  m_spellLog.AddLog(uint32(SPELL_EFFECT_SUMMON_OBJECT_WILD), pGameObj->GetPackGUID());
8113 
8114  if (GameObject* linkedGO = pGameObj->GetLinkedTrap())
8115  {
8116  OnSummon(linkedGO);
8117  m_spellLog.AddLog(uint32(SPELL_EFFECT_SUMMON_OBJECT_WILD), linkedGO->GetPackGUID());
8118  }
8119 }

11047  //}

11190  if (effectTargetType == TARGET_TYPE_UNIT || effectTargetType == TARGET_TYPE_UNIT_DEST)

11192  else if (effectTargetType == TARGET_TYPE_GAMEOBJECT || (effectTargetType == TARGET_TYPE_LOCK && gameObjTarget))
11193  m_trueCaster->GetMap()->ScriptsStart(SCRIPT_TYPE_SPELL, m_spellInfo->Id, m_trueCaster, gameObjTarget);
11194 }

11196 void Spell::EffectSanctuary(SpellEffectIndex /*eff_idx*/)
11197 {
11198  if (!unitTarget)
11199  return;
11200 
11201  unitTarget->InterruptSpellsCastedOnMe(true);
11202  InstanceData* instance = unitTarget->GetInstanceData();
11203  if (instance && sWorld.getConfig(CONFIG_BOOL_INSTANCE_STRICT_COMBAT_LOCKDOWN) && instance->IsEncounterInProgress())
11204  {
11205  unitTarget->AttackStop(true, false, false);
11206  unitTarget->getHostileRefManager().addThreatPercent(-100);
11207  }
11208  else
11209  unitTarget->CombatStop(false, false);
11210 
11211  // Vanish allows to remove all threat and cast regular stealth so other spells can be used
11212  if (m_spellInfo->IsFitToFamily(SPELLFAMILY_ROGUE, uint64(0x0000000000000800)))
11213  ((Player*)unitTarget)->RemoveSpellsCausingAura(SPELL_AURA_MOD_ROOT);
11214 }

11230 void Spell::EffectDuel(SpellEffectIndex eff_idx)
11231 {
11232  if (!m_caster || !unitTarget || m_caster->GetTypeId() != TYPEID_PLAYER || unitTarget->GetTypeId() != TYPEID_PLAYER)
11233  return;
11234 
11235  Player* caster = (Player*)m_caster;
11236  Player* target = (Player*)unitTarget;
11237 
11238  // caster or target already have requested duel
11239  if (caster->duel || target->duel || !target->GetSocial() || target->GetSocial()->HasIgnore(caster->GetObjectGuid()))
11240  return;
11241 
11242  // Players can only fight a duel with each other outside (=not inside dungeons and not in capital cities)
11243  AreaTableEntry const* casterAreaEntry = GetAreaEntryByAreaID(caster->GetAreaId());
11244  if (casterAreaEntry && !(casterAreaEntry->flags & AREA_FLAG_DUEL))
11245  {
11246  SendCastResult(SPELL_FAILED_NO_DUELING); // Dueling isn't allowed here
11247  return;
11248  }
11249 
11250  AreaTableEntry const* targetAreaEntry = GetAreaEntryByAreaID(target->GetAreaId());
11251  if (targetAreaEntry && !(targetAreaEntry->flags & AREA_FLAG_DUEL))
11252  {
11253  SendCastResult(SPELL_FAILED_NO_DUELING); // Dueling isn't allowed here
11254  return;
11255  }
11256 
11257  // CREATE DUEL FLAG OBJECT
11258  GameObject* pGameObj = new GameObject;
11259 
11260  uint32 gameobject_id = m_spellInfo->EffectMiscValue[eff_idx];
11261 
11262  Map* map = m_caster->GetMap();
11263  float x = (m_caster->GetPositionX() + unitTarget->GetPositionX()) * 0.5f;
11264  float y = (m_caster->GetPositionY() + unitTarget->GetPositionY()) * 0.5f;
11265  float z = m_caster->GetPositionZ();
11266  m_caster->UpdateAllowedPositionZ(x, y, z);
11267  uint32 lowGuid = map->GenerateLocalLowGuid(HIGHGUID_GAMEOBJECT);
11268  if (!pGameObj->Create(lowGuid, lowGuid, gameobject_id, map, m_caster->GetPhaseMask(), x, y, z, m_caster->GetOrientation()))
11269  {
11270  delete pGameObj;
11271  return;
11272  }
11273 
11274  pGameObj->SetUInt32Value(GAMEOBJECT_FACTION, m_caster->GetFaction());
11275  pGameObj->SetUInt32Value(GAMEOBJECT_LEVEL, m_caster->GetLevel() + 1);
11276 
11277  pGameObj->SetRespawnTime(m_duration > 0 ? m_duration / IN_MILLISECONDS : 0);
11278  pGameObj->SetSpellId(m_spellInfo->Id);
11279  pGameObj->SetSpawnerGuid(m_trueCaster->GetObjectGuid());
11280 
11281  m_caster->AddGameObject(pGameObj);
11282  map->Add(pGameObj);
11283  pGameObj->AIM_Initialize();
11284 
11285  // END
11286 
11287  // Send request
11288  WorldPacket data(SMSG_DUEL_REQUESTED, 8 + 8);
11289  data << pGameObj->GetObjectGuid();
11290  data << caster->GetObjectGuid();
11291  caster->GetSession()->SendPacket(data);
11292  target->GetSession()->SendPacket(data);
11293 
11294  // create duel-info
11295  DuelInfo* duel = new DuelInfo;
11296  duel->initiator = caster;
11297  duel->opponent = target;
11298  duel->startTime = 0;
11299  duel->startTimer = 0;
11300  caster->duel = duel;
11301 
11302  DuelInfo* duel2 = new DuelInfo;
11303  duel2->initiator = caster;
11304  duel2->opponent = caster;
11305  duel2->startTime = 0;
11306  duel2->startTimer = 0;
11307  target->duel = duel2;
11308 
11309  caster->SetGuidValue(PLAYER_DUEL_ARBITER, pGameObj->GetObjectGuid());
11310  target->SetGuidValue(PLAYER_DUEL_ARBITER, pGameObj->GetObjectGuid());
11311 
11312  m_spellLog.AddLog(uint32(SPELL_EFFECT_DUEL), target->GetPackGUID());
11313 }
11314 
11315 void Spell::EffectStuck(SpellEffectIndex /*eff_idx*/)
11316 {
11317  if (m_caster->GetTypeId() != TYPEID_PLAYER)
11318  return;
11319 
11320  if (!sWorld.getConfig(CONFIG_BOOL_CAST_UNSTUCK))
11321  return;
11322 
11323  Player* player = (Player*)m_caster;
11324 
11325  DEBUG_LOG("Spell Effect: Stuck");
11326  DETAIL_LOG("Player %s (guid %u) used auto-unstuck feature at map %u (%f, %f, %f)", player->GetName(), player->GetGUIDLow(), player->GetMapId(), player->GetPositionX(), player->GetPositionY(), player->GetPositionZ());
11327 
11328  if (player->IsTaxiFlying())
11329  return;
11330 
11331  // If the player is dead, it will return them to the graveyard closest to their corpse.
11332  if (player->HasFlag(PLAYER_FLAGS, PLAYER_FLAGS_GHOST))
11333  {
11334  player->RepopAtGraveyard();
11335  return;
11336  }
11337 
11338  // If the player is alive, and their hearthstone is in their inventory, and their hearthstone
11339  // is cooled down, it will activate their hearthstone. The 30 minute hearthstone cooldown is activated as usual.
11340  if (player->IsSpellReady(8690) && player->HasItemCount(6948, 1, false))
11341  player->CastSpell(nullptr, 8690, TRIGGERED_OLD_TRIGGERED | TRIGGERED_INSTANT_CAST); // always needs to be instant
11342  else
11343  {
11344  if (player->GetMap()->IsDungeon()) // teleport to safe location at entrance - avoids abusing of terrain bugs
11345  {
11346  AreaTrigger const* trigger = sObjectMgr.GetMapEntranceTrigger(player->GetMapId());
11347  player->NearTeleportTo(trigger->target_X, trigger->target_Y, trigger->target_Z, player->GetOrientation());
11348  }
11349  else
11350  {
11351  // If the player is alive, but their hearthstone is either not in their inventory (e.g. in the bank) or
11352  // their hearthstone is on cooldown, then the game will try to "nudge" the player in a seemingly random direction.
11353  // @todo This check could possibly more accurately find a safe position to port to, has the potential for porting underground.
11354  float x, y, z;
11355  player->GetNearPoint(player, x, y, z, DEFAULT_WORLD_OBJECT_SIZE, 10.0f, player->GetOrientation());
11356  player->NearTeleportTo(x, y, z, player->GetOrientation());
11357  }
11358  }
11359 }
11360 
11361 void Spell::EffectSummonPlayer(SpellEffectIndex /*eff_idx*/)
11362 {
11363  if (!unitTarget || !unitTarget->IsPlayer())
11364  return;
11365 
11366  // Evil Twin (ignore player summon, but hide this for summoner)
11367  if (unitTarget->GetDummyAura(23445))
11368  return;
11369 
11370  float x, y, z;
11371  m_caster->GetPosition(x, y, z);
11372 
11373  static_cast<Player*>(unitTarget)->SetSummonPoint(m_caster->GetMapId(), x, y, z, m_caster->GetObjectGuid());
11374 
11375  WorldPacket data(SMSG_SUMMON_REQUEST, 8 + 4 + 4);
11376  data << m_caster->GetObjectGuid(); // summoner guid
11377  data << uint32(m_caster->GetZoneId()); // summoner zone
11378  data << uint32(MAX_PLAYER_SUMMON_DELAY * IN_MILLISECONDS); // auto decline after msecs
11379  static_cast<Player*>(unitTarget)->GetSession()->SendPacket(data);
11380 }

11382 void Spell::EffectActivateObject(SpellEffectIndex effIdx)
11383 {
11384  if (!gameObjTarget)
11385  return;
11386 
11387  uint32 misc_value = m_spellInfo->EffectMiscValue[effIdx];
11388 
11389  GameObjectActions action = GameObjectActions(m_spellInfo->EffectMiscValue[effIdx]);
11390 
11391  switch (action)
11392  {
11393  case GameObjectActions::ANIMATE_CUSTOM_0:
11394  case GameObjectActions::ANIMATE_CUSTOM_1:
11395  case GameObjectActions::ANIMATE_CUSTOM_2:
11396  case GameObjectActions::ANIMATE_CUSTOM_3:
11397  gameObjTarget->SendGameObjectCustomAnim(gameObjTarget->GetObjectGuid(), uint32(action) - uint32(GameObjectActions::ANIMATE_CUSTOM_0));
11398  break;
11399  case GameObjectActions::DISTURB: // What's the difference with Open?
11400  case GameObjectActions::OPEN:
11401  switch (m_spellInfo->Id)
11402  {
11403  case 24731:
11404  case 40964: // Fel Crystalforge: Create 1 Flask
11405  case 40965: // Fel Crystalforge: Create 5 Flasks
11406  case 40968: // Bash'ir Crystalforge: Create 1 Flask
11407  case 40970: // Bash'ir Crystalforge: Create 5 Flasks
11408  case 42868:
11409  case 45222: // Zul'Aman Object Visual - This spell is a custom GO cast spell and similar to Ritual of Souls where only channel start should be sent
11410  gameObjTarget->SendGameObjectCustomAnim(gameObjTarget->GetObjectGuid());
11411  break;
11412  case 36546: // no delay meant to happen - activate trap immediately
11413  case 38054:
11414  case 39844:
11415  gameObjTarget->Use(m_caster, m_spellInfo);
11416  break;
11417  case 46638: // Brutallus SWP - closes door
11418  gameObjTarget->ResetDoorOrButton();
11419  break;
11420  default:
11421  if (m_caster)
11422  gameObjTarget->Use(m_caster);
11423  break;
11424  }
11425  break;
11426  case GameObjectActions::OPEN_AND_UNLOCK:
11427  gameObjTarget->UseDoorOrButton(0, false);
11428  [[fallthrough]];
11429  case GameObjectActions::UNLOCK:
11430  case GameObjectActions::LOCK:
11431  gameObjTarget->ApplyModFlag(GAMEOBJECT_FLAGS, GO_FLAG_LOCKED, action == GameObjectActions::LOCK);
11432  break;
11433  case GameObjectActions::CLOSE:
11434  case GameObjectActions::REBUILD:
11435  if (m_spellInfo->Id == 46610)
11436  gameObjTarget->Use(m_caster, m_spellInfo);
11437  else
11438  gameObjTarget->ResetDoorOrButton(m_caster);
11439  break;
11440  case GameObjectActions::DESPAWN:
11441  gameObjTarget->ForcedDespawn();
11442  break;
11443  case GameObjectActions::MAKE_INERT:
11444  case GameObjectActions::MAKE_ACTIVE:
11445  switch (m_spellInfo->Id)
11446  {
11447  case 24734: // Summon Templar Random
11448  case 24744: // Summon Templar (fire)
11449  case 24756: // Summon Templar (air)
11450  case 24758: // Summon Templar (earth)
11451  case 24760: // Summon Templar (water)
11452  case 24763: // Summon Duke Random
11453  case 24765: // Summon Duke (fire)
11454  case 24768: // Summon Duke (air)
11455  case 24770: // Summon Duke (earth)
11456  case 24772: // Summon Duke (water)
11457  case 24784: // Summon Royal Random
11458  case 24786: // Summon Royal (fire)
11459  case 24788: // Summon Royal (air)
11460  case 24789: // Summon Royal (earth)
11461  case 24790: // Summon Royal (water)
11462  {
11463  uint32 npcEntry = 0;
11464  uint32 templars[] = { 15209, 15211, 15212, 15307 };
11465  uint32 dukes[] = { 15206, 15207, 15208, 15220 };
11466  uint32 royals[] = { 15203, 15204, 15205, 15305 };
11467 
11468  switch (m_spellInfo->Id)
11469  {
11470  case 24734: npcEntry = templars[urand(0, 3)]; break;
11471  case 24763: npcEntry = dukes[urand(0, 3)]; break;
11472  case 24784: npcEntry = royals[urand(0, 3)]; break;
11473  case 24744: npcEntry = 15209; break;
11474  case 24756: npcEntry = 15212; break;
11475  case 24758: npcEntry = 15307; break;
11476  case 24760: npcEntry = 15211; break;
11477  case 24765: npcEntry = 15206; break;
11478  case 24768: npcEntry = 15220; break;
11479  case 24770: npcEntry = 15208; break;
11480  case 24772: npcEntry = 15207; break;
11481  case 24786: npcEntry = 15203; break;
11482  case 24788: npcEntry = 15204; break;
11483  case 24789: npcEntry = 15205; break;
11484  case 24790: npcEntry = 15305; break;
11485  }
11486 
11487  gameObjTarget->SummonCreature(npcEntry, gameObjTarget->GetPositionX(), gameObjTarget->GetPositionY(), gameObjTarget->GetPositionZ(), gameObjTarget->GetAngle(m_caster), TEMPSPAWN_TIMED_OOC_OR_DEAD_DESPAWN, MINUTE * IN_MILLISECONDS);
11488  gameObjTarget->SetLootState(GO_JUST_DEACTIVATED);
11489  break;
11490  }
11491  case 40176: // Simon Game pre-game Begin, blue
11492  case 40177: // Simon Game pre-game Begin, green
11493  case 40178: // Simon Game pre-game Begin, red
11494  case 40179: // Simon Game pre-game Begin, yellow
11495  case 40283: // Simon Game END, blue
11496  case 40284: // Simon Game END, green
11497  case 40285: // Simon Game END, red
11498  case 40286: // Simon Game END, yellow
11499  case 40494: // Simon Game, switched ON
11500  case 40495: // Simon Game, switched OFF
11501  case 40512: // Simon Game, switch...disable Off switch
11502  gameObjTarget->SetFlag(GAMEOBJECT_FLAGS, GO_FLAG_NO_INTERACT);
11503  break;
11504  case 40632: // Summon Gezzarak the Huntress
11505  case 40640: // Summon Karrog
11506  case 40642: // Summon Darkscreecher Akkarai
11507  case 40644: // Summon Vakkiz the Windrager
11508  case 41004: // Summon Terokk
11509  gameObjTarget->SetLootState(GO_JUST_DEACTIVATED);
11510  break;
11511  case 46085: // Place Fake Fur
11512  {
11513  float x, y, z;
11514  gameObjTarget->GetClosePoint(x, y, z, gameObjTarget->GetObjectBoundingRadius(), 2 * INTERACTION_DISTANCE, frand(0, M_PI_F * 2));
11515 
11516  // Note: event script is implemented in script library
11517  gameObjTarget->SummonCreature(25835, x, y, z, gameObjTarget->GetOrientation(), TEMPSPAWN_TIMED_OOC_OR_DEAD_DESPAWN, 15000);
11518  gameObjTarget->SetFlag(GAMEOBJECT_FLAGS, GO_FLAG_IN_USE);
11519  break;
11520  }
11521  case 46592: // Summon Ahune Lieutenant
11522  {
11523  uint32 npcEntry = 0;
11524 
11525  switch (gameObjTarget->GetEntry())
11526  {
11527  case 188049:
11528  case 188137:
11529  case 188138:
11530  npcEntry = 26116; break; // Frostwave Lieutenant (Ashenvale)
11531  case 188134:
11532  case 188135:
11533  case 188139:
11534  npcEntry = 26178; break; // Hailstone Lieutenant (Desolace)
11535  case 188143:
11536  case 188144:
11537  npcEntry = 26204; break; // Chillwind Lieutenant (Stranglethorn)
11538  case 188145:
11539  case 188146:
11540  case 188147:
11541  npcEntry = 26214; break; // Frigid Lieutenant (Searing Gorge)
11542  case 188148:
11543  case 188149:
11544  case 188150:
11545  npcEntry = 26215; break; // Glacial Lieutenant (Silithus)
11546  case 188151:
11547  case 188152:
11548  case 188153:
11549  case 188154:
11550  npcEntry = 26216; break; // Glacial Templar (Hellfire Peninsula)
11551  }
11552 
11553  gameObjTarget->SummonCreature(npcEntry, gameObjTarget->GetPositionX(), gameObjTarget->GetPositionY(), gameObjTarget->GetPositionZ(), gameObjTarget->GetAngle(m_caster), TEMPSPAWN_TIMED_OOC_OR_DEAD_DESPAWN, MINUTE * IN_MILLISECONDS);
11554  gameObjTarget->SetLootState(GO_JUST_DEACTIVATED);
11555  break;
11556  }
11557  }
11558  gameObjTarget->ApplyModFlag(GAMEOBJECT_FLAGS, GO_FLAG_NO_INTERACT, action == GameObjectActions::MAKE_INERT);
11559  break;
11560  case GameObjectActions::CLOSE_AND_LOCK:
11561  gameObjTarget->ResetDoorOrButton(m_caster);
11562  gameObjTarget->SetFlag(GAMEOBJECT_FLAGS, GO_FLAG_LOCKED);
11563  break;
11564  case GameObjectActions::DESTROY:
11565  gameObjTarget->UseDoorOrButton(0, true);
11566  break;
11567  case GameObjectActions::USE_ART_KIT_0:
11568  case GameObjectActions::USE_ART_KIT_1:
11569  case GameObjectActions::USE_ART_KIT_2:
11570  case GameObjectActions::USE_ART_KIT_3:
11571  {
11572  GameObjectTemplateAddon const* templateAddon = gameObjTarget->GetTemplateAddon();
11573 
11574  uint32 artKitIndex = uint32(action) - uint32(GameObjectActions::USE_ART_KIT_0);
11575 
11576  uint32 artKitValue = 0;
11577  if (templateAddon != nullptr)
11578  artKitValue = templateAddon->artKits[artKitIndex];
11579 
11580  if (artKitValue == 0)
11581  sLog.outError("GameObject %d hit by spell %d needs `artkit%d` in `gameobject_template_addon`", gameObjTarget->GetEntry(), m_spellInfo->Id, artKitIndex);
11582  else
11583  gameObjTarget->SetGoArtKit(artKitValue);
11584 
11585  break;
11586  }
11587  default:
11588  sLog.outError("Spell %d has unhandled action %d in effect %d", m_spellInfo->Id, int32(action), int32(effIdx));
11589  break;
11590  }
11591 }

11593 void Spell::EffectApplyGlyph(SpellEffectIndex eff_idx)
11594 {
11595  if (m_caster->GetTypeId() != TYPEID_PLAYER)
11596  return;
11597 
11598  Player* player = (Player*)m_caster;
11599 
11600  // apply new one
11601  if (uint32 glyph = m_spellInfo->EffectMiscValue[eff_idx])
11602  {
11603  if (GlyphPropertiesEntry const* gp = sGlyphPropertiesStore.LookupEntry(glyph))
11604  {
11605  if (GlyphSlotEntry const* gs = sGlyphSlotStore.LookupEntry(player->GetGlyphSlot(m_glyphIndex)))
11606  {
11607  if (gp->TypeFlags != gs->TypeFlags)
11608  {
11609  SendCastResult(SPELL_FAILED_INVALID_GLYPH);
11610  return; // glyph slot mismatch
11611  }
11612  }
11613 
11614  // remove old glyph
11615  player->ApplyGlyph(m_glyphIndex, false);
11616  player->SetGlyph(m_glyphIndex, glyph);
11617  player->ApplyGlyph(m_glyphIndex, true);
11618  player->SendTalentsInfoData(false);
11619  }
11620  }
11621 }

11623 void Spell::EffectEnchantHeldItem(SpellEffectIndex eff_idx)
11624 {
11625  // this is only item spell effect applied to main-hand weapon of target player (players in area)
11626  if (!unitTarget || unitTarget->GetTypeId() != TYPEID_PLAYER)
11627  return;
11628 
11629  Player* item_owner = (Player*)unitTarget;
11630  Item* item = item_owner->GetItemByPos(INVENTORY_SLOT_BAG_0, EQUIPMENT_SLOT_MAINHAND);
11631 
11632  if (!item)
11633  return;
11634 
11635  // must be equipped
11636  if (!item ->IsEquipped())
11637  return;
11638 
11639  if (m_spellInfo->EffectMiscValue[eff_idx])
11640  {
11641  uint32 enchant_id = m_spellInfo->EffectMiscValue[eff_idx];
11642  int32 duration = m_duration; // Try duration index first...
11643  if (!duration)
11644  duration = m_currentBasePoints[eff_idx]; // Base points after...
11645  if (!duration)
11646  duration = 10; // 10 seconds for enchants which don't have listed duration
11647 
11648  SpellItemEnchantmentEntry const* pEnchant = sSpellItemEnchantmentStore.LookupEntry(enchant_id);
11649  if (!pEnchant)
11650  return;
11651 
11652  // Always go to temp enchantment slot
11653  EnchantmentSlot slot = TEMP_ENCHANTMENT_SLOT;
11654 
11655  // Enchantment will not be applied if a different one already exists
11656  if (item->GetEnchantmentId(slot) && item->GetEnchantmentId(slot) != enchant_id)
11657  return;
11658 
11659  // Apply the temporary enchantment
11660  item->SetEnchantment(slot, enchant_id, duration * IN_MILLISECONDS, 0, m_caster->GetObjectGuid());
11661  item_owner->ApplyEnchantment(item, slot, true);
11662  }
11663 }

11665 void Spell::EffectDisEnchant(SpellEffectIndex /*eff_idx*/)
11666 {
11667  if (m_caster->GetTypeId() != TYPEID_PLAYER)
11668  return;
11669 
11670  Player* p_caster = (Player*)m_caster;
11671  if (!itemTarget || !itemTarget->GetProto()->DisenchantID)
11672  return;
11673 
11674  p_caster->UpdateCraftSkill(m_spellInfo->Id);
11675 
11676  Loot*& loot = itemTarget->m_loot;
11677  if (!loot)
11678  loot = new Loot(p_caster, itemTarget, LOOT_DISENCHANTING);
11679  else
11680  {
11681  if (loot->GetLootType() != LOOT_DISENCHANTING)
11682  {
11683  delete loot;
11684  loot = new Loot(p_caster, itemTarget, LOOT_DISENCHANTING);
11685  }
11686  }
11687 
11688  loot->ShowContentTo(p_caster);
11689 
11690  // item will be removed at disenchanting end
11691 }

11693 void Spell::EffectInebriate(SpellEffectIndex /*eff_idx*/)
11694 {

11696  return;
11697

11701  if (drunkValue > 100)
11702  {
11703  drunkValue = 100;
11704 
11705  if (roll_chance_i(25))
11706  player->CastSpell(player, 67468, TRIGGERED_NONE); // Drunken Vomit
11707  }
11708 
11709  player->SetDrunkValue(drunkValue, m_CastItem ? m_CastItem->GetEntry() : 0);
11710 }

11712 void Spell::EffectFeedPet(SpellEffectIndex eff_idx)
11713 {
11714  if (m_caster->GetTypeId() != TYPEID_PLAYER)
11715  return;
11716 
11717  Player* _player = (Player*)m_caster;
11718 
11719  Item* foodItem = m_targets.getItemTarget();
11720  if (!foodItem)
11721  return;
11722 
11723  Pet* pet = _player->GetPet();
11724  if (!pet)
11725  return;
11726 
11727  if (!pet->IsAlive())
11728  return;
11729

11731  if (benefit <= 0)
11732  return;
11733 
11734  m_spellLog.AddLog(uint32(SPELL_EFFECT_FEED_PET), foodItem->GetEntry());
11735  // send log now before remove it from player inventory
11736  m_spellLog.SendToSet();
11737 
11738  uint32 count = 1;
11739  _player->DestroyItemCount(foodItem, count, true);
11740  // TODO: fix crash when a spell has two effects, both pointed at the same item target
11741 
11742  m_caster->CastCustomSpell(nullptr, m_spellInfo->EffectTriggerSpell[eff_idx], &benefit, nullptr, nullptr, TRIGGERED_OLD_TRIGGERED);
11743 }
