11763 void Spell::EffectSummonObject(SpellEffectIndex eff_idx)
11764 {
11765  uint32 go_id = m_spellInfo->EffectMiscValue[eff_idx];
11766 
11767  uint8 slot;
11768  switch (m_spellInfo->Effect[eff_idx])
11769  {
11770  case SPELL_EFFECT_SUMMON_OBJECT_SLOT1: slot = 0; break;
11771  case SPELL_EFFECT_SUMMON_OBJECT_SLOT2: slot = 1; break;
11772  case SPELL_EFFECT_SUMMON_OBJECT_SLOT3: slot = 2; break;
11773  case SPELL_EFFECT_SUMMON_OBJECT_SLOT4: slot = 3; break;
11774  default: return;
11775  }
11776 
11777  if (ObjectGuid guid = m_caster->m_ObjectSlotGuid[slot])
11778  {
11779  if (GameObject* obj = m_caster ? m_caster->GetMap()->GetGameObject(guid) : nullptr)
11780  {
11781  obj->SetLootState(GO_JUST_DEACTIVATED);
11782  m_caster->RemoveGameObject(obj, false, m_spellInfo->Id != obj->GetSpellId());
11783  }
11784  m_caster->m_ObjectSlotGuid[slot].Clear();
11785  }
11786 
11787  GameObject* pGameObj = new GameObject;
11788 
11789  float x, y, z;
11790  // If dest location if present
11791  if (m_targets.m_targetMask & TARGET_FLAG_DEST_LOCATION)
11792  m_targets.getDestination(x, y, z);
11793  // Summon in random point all other units if location present
11794  else
11795  m_caster->GetClosePoint(x, y, z, DEFAULT_WORLD_OBJECT_SIZE);
11796 
11797  Map* map = m_caster->GetMap();
11798  uint32 lowGuid = map->GenerateLocalLowGuid(HIGHGUID_GAMEOBJECT);
11799  if (!pGameObj->Create(lowGuid, lowGuid, go_id, map,
11800  m_caster->GetPhaseMask(), x, y, z, m_caster->GetOrientation()))
11801  {
11802  delete pGameObj;
11803  return;
11804  }
11805 
11806  pGameObj->SetUInt32Value(GAMEOBJECT_LEVEL, m_caster->GetLevel());
11807  pGameObj->SetRespawnTime(m_duration > 0 ? m_duration / IN_MILLISECONDS : 0);
11808  pGameObj->SetSpellId(m_spellInfo->Id);
11809  pGameObj->SetSpawnerGuid(m_trueCaster->GetObjectGuid());
11810  m_caster->AddGameObject(pGameObj);
11811 
11812  map->Add(pGameObj);
11813  pGameObj->AIM_Initialize();
11814 
11815  m_caster->m_ObjectSlotGuid[slot] = pGameObj->GetObjectGuid();
11816 
11817  // Notify Summoner
11818  if (m_originalCaster && (m_originalCaster != m_caster) && (m_originalCaster->AI()))
11819  m_originalCaster->AI()->JustSummoned(pGameObj);
11820  else if (m_caster->AI())
11821  m_caster->AI()->JustSummoned(pGameObj);
11822 
11823  OnSummon(pGameObj);
11824  m_spellLog.AddLog(m_spellInfo->Effect[eff_idx], pGameObj->GetPackGUID());
11825 
11826  if (GameObject* linkedGO = pGameObj->GetLinkedTrap())
11827  {
11828  OnSummon(linkedGO);
11829  m_spellLog.AddLog(m_spellInfo->Effect[eff_idx], linkedGO->GetPackGUID());
11830  }
11831 }
11832 
11833 void Spell::EffectResurrect(SpellEffectIndex eff_idx)
11834 {
11835  if (!unitTarget && !corpseTarget)
11836  return;
11837 
11838  switch (m_spellInfo->Id)
11839  {
11840  case 8342: // Defibrillate (Goblin Jumper Cables) has 33% chance on success
11841  case 22999: // Defibrillate (Goblin Jumper Cables XL) has 50% chance on success
11842  case 54732: // Defibrillate (Gnomish Army Knife) has 67% chance on success
11843  {
11844  uint32 failChance = 0;
11845  uint32 failSpellId = 0;
11846  switch (m_spellInfo->Id)
11847  {
11848  case 8342: failChance = 67; failSpellId = 8338; break;
11849  case 22999: failChance = 50; failSpellId = 23055; break;
11850  case 54732: failChance = 33; failSpellId = 0; break;
11851  }
11852 
11853  if (roll_chance_i(failChance))
11854  {
11855  if (failSpellId)
11856  m_caster->CastSpell(m_caster, failSpellId, TRIGGERED_OLD_TRIGGERED, m_CastItem);
11857  return;
11858  }
11859  break;
11860  }
11861  default: break;
11862  }
11863 
11864  uint32 effectId = m_spellInfo->Effect[eff_idx];
11865  Player* player = nullptr;
11866 
11867  if (unitTarget) // thread safe version
11868  {
11869  if (unitTarget->IsAlive() || unitTarget->GetTypeId() != TYPEID_PLAYER || !unitTarget->IsInWorld())
11870  return;
11871 
11872  player = static_cast<Player*>(unitTarget);
11873  }
11874 
11875  if (unitTarget)
11876  m_spellLog.AddLog(uint32(m_spellInfo->Effect[eff_idx]), unitTarget->GetPackGUID());
11877  else if (corpseTarget)
11878  m_spellLog.AddLog(uint32(m_spellInfo->Effect[eff_idx]), corpseTarget->GetPackGUID());
11879 
11880  Player::QueueOrAddResurrectRequest(corpseTarget, m_caster, player, m_spellInfo, damage, eff_idx, false);
11881 }

11886  return;
11887 
11888  if (unitTarget->m_extraAttacks)
11889  return;
11890 
11891  unitTarget->m_extraAttacks = damage;
11892  m_spellLog.AddLog(uint32(SPELL_EFFECT_ADD_EXTRA_ATTACKS), unitTarget->GetPackGUID(), damage);
11893 }

11926 void Spell::EffectReputation(SpellEffectIndex eff_idx)
11927 {
11928  if (!unitTarget || unitTarget->GetTypeId() != TYPEID_PLAYER)
11929  return;
11930 
11931  Player* _player = (Player*)unitTarget;
11932 
11933  int32 rep_change = m_currentBasePoints[eff_idx];
11934  uint32 faction_id = m_spellInfo->EffectMiscValue[eff_idx];
11935 
11936  FactionEntry const* factionEntry = sFactionStore.LookupEntry(faction_id);
11937 
11938  if (!factionEntry)

11974 void Spell::EffectSelfResurrect(SpellEffectIndex eff_idx)
11975 {
11976  if (m_caster->GetTypeId() != TYPEID_PLAYER)
11977  return;
11978  Player* player = static_cast<Player*>(m_caster);
11979 
11980  uint32 health;
11981  uint32 mana = 0;
11982 
11983  // flat case
11984  if (damage < 0)
11985  {
11986  health = uint32(-damage);
11987  mana = m_spellInfo->EffectMiscValue[eff_idx];
11988  }
11989  // percent case
11990  else
11991  {
11992  health = uint32(damage / 100.0f * player->GetMaxHealth());
11993  if (player->GetMaxPower(POWER_MANA) > 0)
11994  mana = uint32(damage / 100.0f * player->GetMaxPower(POWER_MANA));
11995  }
11996 
11997  player->ResurrectPlayer(0.0f);
11998 
11999  player->SetHealth(health);
12000  player->SetPower(POWER_MANA, mana);
12001  player->SetPower(POWER_RAGE, 0);
12002  player->SetPower(POWER_ENERGY, player->GetMaxPower(POWER_ENERGY));
12003 
12004  player->SpawnCorpseBones();
12005 }

12112 void Spell::EffectPullTowards(SpellEffectIndex eff_idx)
12113 {
12114  if (!unitTarget)
12115  return;
12116 
12117  float x, y, z, dist;
12118 
12119  if (m_spellInfo->Effect[eff_idx] == SPELL_EFFECT_PULL_TOWARDS)
12120  {
12121  z = m_caster->GetPositionZ();
12122  dist = unitTarget->GetDistance(m_caster, false);
12123  x = m_caster->GetPositionX();
12124  y = m_caster->GetPositionY();
12125  }
12126  else // SPELL_EFFECT_PULL_TOWARDS_DEST
12127  {
12128  m_targets.getDestination(x, y, z);
12129  dist = sqrt(unitTarget->GetDistance2d(x, y, DIST_CALC_NONE));
12130  }
12131 
12132  if (damage && dist > damage)
12133  dist = float(damage);
12134 
12135  if (dist < 0.1f)
12136  return;
12137 
12138  // Projectile motion
12139  float speedXY = float(m_spellInfo->EffectMiscValue[eff_idx]) * 0.1f;
12140  float time = dist / speedXY;
12141  float speedZ = ((z - unitTarget->GetPositionZ()) + 0.5f * time * time * Movement::gravity) / time;
12142  float angle = unitTarget->GetAngle(x, y);
12143 
12144  unitTarget->KnockBackWithAngle(angle, speedXY, speedZ);
12145 }

12313 void Spell::EffectTransmitted(SpellEffectIndex eff_idx)
12314 {
12315  uint32 name_id = m_spellInfo->EffectMiscValue[eff_idx];
12316 
12317  switch (m_spellInfo->Id)
12318  {
12319  case 29886: // Create Soulwell
12320  if (m_caster->HasAura(18692))
12321  name_id = 183510;
12322  else if (m_caster->HasAura(18693))
12323  name_id = 183511;
12324  break;
12325  default:
12326  break;
12327  }
12328 
12329  GameObjectInfo const* goinfo = ObjectMgr::GetGameObjectInfo(name_id);
12330 
12331  if (!goinfo)
12332  {
12333  sLog.outErrorDb("Gameobject (Entry: %u) not exist and not created at spell (ID: %u) cast", name_id, m_spellInfo->Id);
12334  return;
12335  }
12336 
12337  float fx, fy, fz;
12338 
12339  if (m_targets.m_targetMask & TARGET_FLAG_DEST_LOCATION)
12340  m_targets.getDestination(fx, fy, fz);
12341  // FIXME: this can be better check for most objects but still hack
12342  else if (m_spellInfo->EffectRadiusIndex[eff_idx] && m_spellInfo->speed == 0)
12343  {
12344  float dis = GetSpellRadius(sSpellRadiusStore.LookupEntry(m_spellInfo->EffectRadiusIndex[eff_idx]));
12345  m_caster->GetClosePoint(fx, fy, fz, DEFAULT_WORLD_OBJECT_SIZE, dis);
12346  }
12347  else
12348  {
12349  float min_dis = GetSpellMinRange(sSpellRangeStore.LookupEntry(m_spellInfo->rangeIndex));
12350  float max_dis = GetSpellMaxRange(sSpellRangeStore.LookupEntry(m_spellInfo->rangeIndex));
12351  float dis = rand_norm_f() * (max_dis - min_dis) + min_dis;
12352 
12353  // special code for fishing bobber (TARGET_LOCATION_CASTER_FISHING_SPOT), should not try to avoid objects
12354  // nor try to find ground level, but randomly vary in angle
12355  if (goinfo->type == GAMEOBJECT_TYPE_FISHINGNODE)
12356  {
12357  // calculate angle variation for roughly equal dimensions of target area
12358  float max_angle = (max_dis - min_dis) / (max_dis + m_caster->GetObjectBoundingRadius());
12359  float angle_offset = max_angle * (rand_norm_f() - 0.5f);
12360  m_caster->GetNearPoint2d(fx, fy, dis + m_caster->GetObjectBoundingRadius(), m_caster->GetOrientation() + angle_offset);
12361 
12362  SpellCastResult err = SPELL_FAILED_SUCCESS;
12363  float waistHeight = GetModelMidpoint(m_caster->GetDisplayId()) * m_caster->GetObjectScale();
12364 
12365  if (!m_caster->GetTerrain()->IsAboveWater(fx, fy, m_caster->GetPositionZ() + waistHeight + 0.5f, &fz))
12366  err = SPELL_FAILED_NOT_FISHABLE;
12367  else if (m_caster->GetPositionZ() < (fz - waistHeight))
12368  err = SPELL_FAILED_ONLY_ABOVEWATER;
12369  else if (!m_caster->IsWithinLOS(fx, fy, fz))
12370  err = SPELL_FAILED_LINE_OF_SIGHT;
12371 
12372  if (err != SPELL_FAILED_SUCCESS)
12373  {
12374  SendCastResult(err);
12375  SendChannelUpdate(0);
12376  return;
12377  }
12378  }
12379  else
12380  m_caster->GetClosePoint(fx, fy, fz, DEFAULT_WORLD_OBJECT_SIZE, dis);
12381  }
12382 
12383  Map* cMap = m_caster->GetMap();
12384 
12385  // if gameobject is summoning object, it should be spawned right on caster's position
12386  if (goinfo->type == GAMEOBJECT_TYPE_SUMMONING_RITUAL)
12387  {
12388  m_caster->GetPosition(fx, fy, fz);
12389  }
12390 
12391  GameObject* pGameObj = new GameObject;
12392  uint32 lowGuid = cMap->GenerateLocalLowGuid(HIGHGUID_GAMEOBJECT);
12393  if (!pGameObj->Create(lowGuid, lowGuid, name_id, cMap,
12394  m_caster->GetPhaseMask(), fx, fy, fz, m_caster->GetOrientation()))
12395  {
12396  delete pGameObj;
12397  return;
12398  }
12399 
12400  int32 duration = m_duration;
12401 
12402  switch (goinfo->type)
12403  {
12404  case GAMEOBJECT_TYPE_FISHINGNODE:
12405  {
12406  m_caster->SetChannelObject(pGameObj);
12407  m_caster->AddGameObject(pGameObj); // will removed at spell cancel
12408 
12409  // end time of range when possible catch fish (FISHING_BOBBER_READY_TIME..GetDuration(m_spellInfo))
12410  // start time == fish-FISHING_BOBBER_READY_TIME (0..GetDuration(m_spellInfo)-FISHING_BOBBER_READY_TIME)
12411  int32 lastSec = 0;
12412  switch (urand(0, 3))
12413  {
12414  case 0: lastSec = 3; break;
12415  case 1: lastSec = 7; break;
12416  case 2: lastSec = 13; break;
12417  case 3: lastSec = 17; break;
12418  }
12419 
12420  duration = duration - lastSec * IN_MILLISECONDS + FISHING_BOBBER_READY_TIME * IN_MILLISECONDS;
12421  break;
12422  }
12423  case GAMEOBJECT_TYPE_SUMMONING_RITUAL:
12424  {
12425  if (m_caster->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_PLAYER)
12426  {
12427  Player* player = (Player*)m_caster;
12428  pGameObj->AddUniqueUse(player);
12429  pGameObj->SetActionTarget(player->GetSelectionGuid());
12430  m_caster->AddGameObject(pGameObj); // will removed at spell cancel
12431  }
12432  break;
12433  }
12434  case GAMEOBJECT_TYPE_SPELLCASTER:
12435  {
12436  m_caster->AddGameObject(pGameObj);
12437  break;
12438  }
12439  // Other GO types have startOpen attribute but only GAMEOBJECT_TYPE_BUTTON is used by spells
12440  case GAMEOBJECT_TYPE_BUTTON:
12441  {
12442  // Change GO state if it is supposed to be already activated at summoning
12443  pGameObj->SetGoState((goinfo->button.startOpen ? GO_STATE_ACTIVE : GO_STATE_READY));
12444  break;
12445  }
12446  case GAMEOBJECT_TYPE_FISHINGHOLE:
12447  case GAMEOBJECT_TYPE_CHEST:
12448  default:
12449  break;
12450  }
12451 
12452  pGameObj->SetRespawnTime(duration > 0 ? duration / IN_MILLISECONDS : 0);
12453 
12454  pGameObj->SetOwnerGuid(m_caster->GetObjectGuid());
12455 
12456  pGameObj->SetUInt32Value(GAMEOBJECT_LEVEL, m_caster->GetLevel());
12457  pGameObj->SetSpellId(m_spellInfo->Id);
12458  pGameObj->SetSpawnerGuid(m_trueCaster->GetObjectGuid());
12459 
12460  DEBUG_LOG("AddObject at SpellEfects.cpp EffectTransmitted");
12461  // m_caster->AddGameObject(pGameObj);
12462  // m_ObjToDel.push_back(pGameObj);
12463 
12464  cMap->Add(pGameObj);
12465  pGameObj->AIM_Initialize();
12466 
12467  // Notify Summoner
12468  if (m_originalCaster && (m_originalCaster != m_caster) && (m_originalCaster->AI()))
12469  m_originalCaster->AI()->JustSummoned(pGameObj);
12470  else if (m_caster->AI())
12471  m_caster->AI()->JustSummoned(pGameObj);
12472 
12473  OnSummon(pGameObj);
12474  m_spellLog.AddLog(uint32(SPELL_EFFECT_TRANS_DOOR), pGameObj->GetPackGUID());
12475 
12476  if (GameObject* linkedGO = pGameObj->GetLinkedTrap())
12477  {
12478  OnSummon(linkedGO);
12479  m_spellLog.AddLog(uint32(SPELL_EFFECT_TRANS_DOOR), linkedGO->GetPackGUID());
12480  }
12481 }
12482

12505 void Spell::EffectMilling(SpellEffectIndex /*eff_idx*/)
12506 {
12507  if (m_caster->GetTypeId() != TYPEID_PLAYER || !itemTarget)
12508  return;
12509 
12510  Player* p_caster = (Player*)m_caster;
12511 
12512  if (sWorld.getConfig(CONFIG_BOOL_SKILL_MILLING))
12513  {
12514  uint32 SkillValue = p_caster->GetSkillValuePure(SKILL_INSCRIPTION);
12515  uint32 reqSkillValue = itemTarget->GetProto()->RequiredSkillRank;
12516  p_caster->UpdateGatherSkill(SKILL_INSCRIPTION, SkillValue, reqSkillValue);
12517  }
12518 
12519  Loot*& loot = itemTarget->m_loot;
12520  delete loot;
12521 
12522  loot = new Loot(p_caster, itemTarget, LOOT_MILLING);
12523 
12524  loot->ShowContentTo(p_caster);
12525 }

12531 void Spell::EffectSpiritHeal(SpellEffectIndex /*eff_idx*/)
12532 {
12533  // TODO player can't see the heal-animation - he should respawn some ticks later
12534  if (!unitTarget || unitTarget->IsAlive())
12535  return;
12536  if (unitTarget->GetTypeId() != TYPEID_PLAYER)
12537  return;
12538  if (!unitTarget->IsInWorld())
12539  return;
12540  // check spell id; aura on player and area id (Wintergrasp)
12541  if (m_spellInfo->Id == 22012 && !unitTarget->HasAura(2584))
12542  if (unitTarget->GetAreaId() != 4197)
12543  return;
12544 
12545  if (Player* player = static_cast<Player*>(unitTarget))
12546  {
12547  player->ResurrectPlayer(1.0f);
12548  player->SpawnCorpseBones();
12549 
12550  if (player->getClass() == CLASS_HUNTER)
12551  {
12552  Pet* pet = new Pet;
12553  if (!pet->LoadPetFromDB(player, pet->GetPetSpawnPosition(player), 0, 0, false, 100, true))
12554  {
12555  delete pet;
12556  return;
12557  }
12558  }
12559  // resurrects last active minion - Imp, Voidwalker, Succubus, Felhunter, or Felguard
12560  // if Doomguard or Infernal were last active minion, or previous minion died before Warlock - Imp summoned instead
12561  else if (player->getClass() == CLASS_WARLOCK)
12562  player->CastSpell(player, player->GetBGPetSpell() ? player->GetBGPetSpell() : 688, TRIGGERED_OLD_TRIGGERED);
12563  }
12564 }

12566 // remove insignia spell effect
12567 void Spell::EffectSkinPlayerCorpse(SpellEffectIndex /*eff_idx*/)
12568 {
12569  DEBUG_LOG("Effect: SkinPlayerCorpse");
12570  Player* playerCaster = m_caster->IsPlayer() ? (Player*)m_caster : nullptr;
12571  if (!playerCaster)
12572  return;
12573 
12574  Unit* target = unitTarget;
12575  if (!target && corpseTarget)
12576  target = sObjectAccessor.FindPlayer(corpseTarget->GetOwnerGuid());
12577 
12578  if (!target)
12579  {
12580  Corpse* bones = sObjectAccessor.ConvertCorpseForPlayer(corpseTarget->GetOwnerGuid(), true);
12581  if (!bones)
12582  return;
12583 
12584  // Now we must make bones lootable, and send player loot
12585  bones->SetFlag(CORPSE_FIELD_DYNAMIC_FLAGS, CORPSE_DYNFLAG_LOOTABLE);
12586 
12587  // We store the level of our player in the gold field
12588  // We retrieve this information at Player::SendLoot()
12589  bones->lootRecipient = playerCaster;
12590 
12591  Loot*& bonesLoot = bones->m_loot;
12592  if (!bonesLoot)
12593  bonesLoot = new Loot(playerCaster, bones, LOOT_INSIGNIA);
12594  else
12595  {
12596  if (bonesLoot->GetLootType() != LOOT_INSIGNIA)
12597  {
12598  delete bonesLoot;
12599  bonesLoot = new Loot(playerCaster, bones, LOOT_INSIGNIA);
12600  }
12601  }
12602 
12603  bonesLoot->ShowContentTo(playerCaster);
12604 
12605  DEBUG_LOG("Effect SkinPlayerCorpse: corpse owner was not found");
12606  return;
12607  }
12608 
12609  static_cast<Player*>(target)->RemovedInsignia(static_cast<Player*>(m_caster));
12610 }

12612 void Spell::EffectStealBeneficialBuff(SpellEffectIndex eff_idx)
12613 {
12614  DEBUG_LOG("Effect: StealBeneficialBuff");
12615 
12616  if (!unitTarget || unitTarget == m_caster) // can't steal from self
12617  return;
12618 
12619  std::list <std::pair<SpellAuraHolder*, uint32> > dispelList;
12620  // Create dispel mask by dispel type
12621  uint32 dispelMask = GetDispellMask(DispelType(m_spellInfo->EffectMiscValue[eff_idx]));
12622  Unit::SpellAuraHolderMap const& auras = unitTarget->GetSpellAuraHolderMap();
12623  for (const auto& aura : auras)
12624  {
12625  SpellAuraHolder* holder = aura.second;
12626  if (holder && (1 << holder->GetSpellProto()->Dispel) & dispelMask)
12627  {
12628  // Need check for passive? this
12629  if (holder->IsPositive() && !holder->IsPassive() && !holder->GetSpellProto()->HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR_EX4_CANNOT_BE_STOLEN))
12630  dispelList.emplace_back(holder, holder->GetStackAmount());
12631  }
12632  }
12633  std::list<std::pair<SpellAuraHolder*, uint32> > successList;
12634  std::list <uint32> failList;
12635  ProcessDispelList(dispelList, successList, failList);
12636  // Ok if exist some buffs for dispel try dispel it
12637  // Really try steal and send log
12638  // Really try steal and send log
12639  if (!successList.empty())
12640  {
12641  int32 count = successList.size();
12642  WorldPacket data(SMSG_SPELLSTEALLOG, 8 + 8 + 4 + 1 + 4 + count * 5);
12643  data << unitTarget->GetPackGUID(); // Victim GUID
12644  data << m_caster->GetPackGUID(); // Caster GUID
12645  data << uint32(m_spellInfo->Id); // Dispell spell id
12646  data << uint8(0); // not used
12647  data << uint32(count); // count
12648  for (auto& spellstealSpell : successList)
12649  {
12650  SpellEntry const* spellInfo = spellstealSpell.first->GetSpellProto();
12651  data << uint32(spellInfo->Id); // Spell Id
12652  data << uint8(0); // 0 - steals !=0 transfers
12653  unitTarget->RemoveAurasDueToSpellBySteal(spellstealSpell.first, m_caster);
12654  }
12655  m_caster->SendMessageToSet(data, true);
12656  }
12657  // Send fail log to client
12658  if (!failList.empty())
12659  {
12660  // Failed to dispel
12661  WorldPacket data(SMSG_DISPEL_FAILED, 8 + 8 + 4 + 4 * failList.size());
12662  data << m_caster->GetObjectGuid(); // Caster GUID
12663  data << unitTarget->GetObjectGuid(); // Victim GUID
12664  data << uint32(m_spellInfo->Id); // Dispel spell id
12665  for (uint32& j : failList)
12666  data << uint32(j); // Spell Id
12667  m_caster->SendMessageToSet(data, true);
12668  }
12669 }

12855 void Spell::EffectBind(SpellEffectIndex eff_idx)
12856 {
12857  if (!unitTarget || unitTarget->GetTypeId() != TYPEID_PLAYER)
12858  return;
12859 
12860  Player* player = (Player*)unitTarget;
12861 
12862  uint32 area_id = m_spellInfo->EffectMiscValue[eff_idx];
12863  WorldLocation loc;
12864  if (m_spellInfo->EffectImplicitTargetA[eff_idx] == TARGET_LOCATION_DATABASE ||
12865  m_spellInfo->EffectImplicitTargetB[eff_idx] == TARGET_LOCATION_DATABASE)
12866  {
12867  SpellTargetPosition const* st = sSpellMgr.GetSpellTargetPosition(m_spellInfo->Id);
12868  if (!st)
12869  {
12870  sLog.outError("Spell::EffectBind - unknown Teleport coordinates for spell ID %u", m_spellInfo->Id);
12871  return;
12872  }
12873 
12874  loc.mapid = st->target_mapId;
12875  loc.coord_x = st->target_X;
12876  loc.coord_y = st->target_Y;
12877  loc.coord_z = st->target_Z;
12878  loc.orientation = st->target_Orientation;
12879  if (!area_id)
12880  area_id = sTerrainMgr.GetAreaId(loc.mapid, loc.coord_x, loc.coord_y, loc.coord_z);
12881  }
12882  else
12883  {
12884  player->GetPosition(loc);
12885  if (!area_id)
12886  area_id = player->GetAreaId();
12887  }
12888 
12889  player->SetHomebindToLocation(loc, area_id);
12890 
12891  // binding
12892  WorldPacket data(SMSG_BINDPOINTUPDATE, (4 + 4 + 4 + 4 + 4));
12893  data << float(loc.coord_x);
12894  data << float(loc.coord_y);
12895  data << float(loc.coord_z);
12896  data << uint32(loc.mapid);
12897  data << uint32(area_id);
12898  player->SendDirectMessage(data);
12899 
12900  DEBUG_LOG("New Home Position for %s: XYZ: %f %f %f on Map %u", player->GetGuidStr().c_str(), loc.coord_x, loc.coord_y, loc.coord_z, loc.mapid);
12901 
12902  // zone update
12903  data.Initialize(SMSG_PLAYERBOUND, 8 + 4);
12904  data << m_caster->GetObjectGuid();
12905  data << uint32(area_id);
12906  player->SendDirectMessage(data);
12907 }

13033 void Spell::EffectCreateTamedPet(SpellEffectIndex eff_idx)
13034 {
13035  if (!unitTarget || unitTarget->getClass() != CLASS_HUNTER)
13036  return;
13037 
13038  uint32 creatureEntry = m_spellInfo->EffectMiscValue[eff_idx];
13039 
13040  CreatureInfo const* cInfo = ObjectMgr::GetCreatureTemplate(creatureEntry);
13041  if (creatureEntry && !cInfo)
13042  {
13043  sLog.outErrorDb("EffectCreateTamedPet: Creature entry %u not found for spell %u.", creatureEntry, m_spellInfo->Id);
13044  return;
13045  }
13046 
13047  Pet* newTamedPet = new Pet(HUNTER_PET);
13048  CreatureCreatePos pos(unitTarget, unitTarget->GetOrientation());
13049 
13050  Map* map = unitTarget->GetMap();
13051  uint32 petNumber = sObjectMgr.GeneratePetNumber();
13052  if (!newTamedPet->Create(map->GenerateLocalLowGuid(HIGHGUID_PET), pos, cInfo, petNumber))
13053  {
13054  delete newTamedPet;
13055  return;
13056  }
13057 
13058  newTamedPet->SetRespawnCoord(pos);
13059 
13060  newTamedPet->SetOwnerGuid(unitTarget->GetObjectGuid());
13061  newTamedPet->SetUInt32Value(UNIT_NPC_FLAGS, UNIT_NPC_FLAG_NONE);
13062  newTamedPet->setFaction(unitTarget->GetFaction());
13063  newTamedPet->SetUInt32Value(UNIT_FIELD_PET_NAME_TIMESTAMP, uint32(time(nullptr)));
13064  newTamedPet->SetUInt32Value(UNIT_CREATED_BY_SPELL, m_spellInfo->Id);
13065 
13066  newTamedPet->GetCharmInfo()->SetPetNumber(petNumber, true);
13067 
13068  if (unitTarget->IsPvP())
13069  newTamedPet->SetPvP(true);
13070 
13071  if (unitTarget->IsPvPFreeForAll())
13072  newTamedPet->SetPvPFreeForAll(true);
13073 
13074  if (unitTarget->IsPvPSanctuary())
13075  newTamedPet->SetPvPSanctuary(true);
13076 
13077  newTamedPet->SetCanModifyStats(true);
13078 
13079  map->Add((Creature*)newTamedPet);
13080 
13081  newTamedPet->InitStatsForLevel(unitTarget->GetLevel());
13082  newTamedPet->InitPetCreateSpells();
13083  newTamedPet->InitLevelupSpellsForLevel();
13084  newTamedPet->InitTalentForLevel();
13085

13114 uint32 Spell::GetUsableHealthStoneItemType(Unit* target)
13115 {
13116  if (!target || target->GetTypeId() != TYPEID_PLAYER)
13117  return 0;
13118 
13119  uint32 itemtype = 0;
13120  uint32 rank = 0;
13121  Unit::AuraList const& mDummyAuras = target->GetAurasByType(SPELL_AURA_DUMMY);
13122  for (auto mDummyAura : mDummyAuras)
13123  {
13124  if (mDummyAura->GetId() == 18692)
13125  {
13126  rank = 1;
13127  break;
13128  }
13129  if (mDummyAura->GetId() == 18693)
13130  {
13131  rank = 2;
13132  break;
13133  }
13134  }
13135 
13136  static uint32 const itypes[][3] =
13137  {
13138  { 5512, 19004, 19005}, // Minor Healthstone
13139  { 5511, 19006, 19007}, // Lesser Healthstone
13140  { 5509, 19008, 19009}, // Healthstone
13141  { 5510, 19010, 19011}, // Greater Healthstone
13142  { 9421, 19012, 19013}, // Major Healthstone
13143  {22103, 22104, 22105}, // Master Healthstone
13144  {36889, 36890, 36891}, // Demonic Healthstone
13145  {36892, 36893, 36894} // Fel Healthstone
13146  };
13147 
13148  switch (m_spellInfo->Id)
13149  {
13150  case 6201:
13151  itemtype = itypes[0][rank]; break; // Minor Healthstone
13152  case 6202:
13153  itemtype = itypes[1][rank]; break; // Lesser Healthstone
13154  case 5699:
13155  itemtype = itypes[2][rank]; break; // Healthstone
13156  case 11729:
13157  itemtype = itypes[3][rank]; break; // Greater Healthstone
13158  case 11730:
13159  itemtype = itypes[4][rank]; break; // Major Healthstone
13160  case 27230:
13161  itemtype = itypes[5][rank]; break; // Master Healthstone
13162  case 47871:
13163  itemtype = itypes[6][rank]; break; // Demonic Healthstone
13164  case 47878:
13165  itemtype = itypes[7][rank]; break; // Fel Healthstone
13166  }
13167  return itemtype;
13168 }
